<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="ROM" stage="Rev" version="D">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:48:49Z" when="2009-10-02 03:48:49Z" stage="Draft">1st draft by C. Grimes; July-Aug 2005; advisor for this book C. Grimes; Resources: HCE, GNT, NRSV, NLT, CEV, Message, Morris (1987), Moo, SSA, TH; advisor check in Darwin with Mus &amp; June, August 2005, + read-thru with Barbara's comments; BT by Barbara, BT reviewed and cleaned up by Chuck; UNS checked by Mus &amp; June 16-18 Sept 2005 in Kupang; UNS suggestions evaluated by Chuck Oct 2005; consultant checked by Marge Crofts 10-13 Oct 2005 in Kupang; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Barbara, Adriana; refined exegesis Feb 2009; refined Aug 09;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:51:22Z" when="2014-02-24 10:51:22Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 10-13 October 2005 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Report KM Roman1.doc</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-14 03:18:00Z" when="2015-01-14 03:18:00Z" stage="Consult">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible at UBB with Chuck, Lena, Rina, and Oma. Bt cleaned up a bit too.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Roma</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat<bt>Paulus' letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi orang parcaya di kota<bt>to the believers in the city of</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Roma<bt>Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saloom<bt>Peace/Greetings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ini surat dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang beta ko jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan. Ais Dia angka sang beta jadi Kristus pung orang suru-suru ko pi kasi tau orang di mana-mana so'al Dia pung Kabar Bae.<bt>This letter is from me, Paulus. God1 has chosen me to be Yesus Kristus' *apostle/commissioned person. Cuz (elaboration), He appointed me to become Kristus' servant/slave (person habitually ordered around) to go tell people all over the place about His *Good News. [EXEG: the function of ‘Kristus’ as per TBT article is spelled out in following verses, so doesn't need to be explicated here. It would skew the information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doulos: slave, LXX servant of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">doulos: slave, LXX servant of the Lord. habitual servant, personal retainer like Hawaiian &amp; Rotinese kings had (relationship, not job) apóstolos: special messenger<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: Paul, a servant of Jesus Christ, called to be an apostle, set apart for the gospel of God,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ini surat dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ini surat dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang beta ko jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan. Kristus tu, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang iko Dia pung janji. Abis, beta jadi Kristus pung orang suru-suru ko pi kasi tau orang di mana-mana so'al Dia pung Kabar Bae. Te Dia yang angka sang beta ko kasi jalan itu tugas.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2-3" />Dolu-dolu, Tuhan Allah su ator memang ko Dia pung jubir dong tulis so'al itu Kabar Bae di Dia pung Tulisan Barisi. Te dalam itu Tulisan tu, Tuhan janji mau kirim datang Dia pung Ana Yesus, ko jadi manusia. Ma sakarang Dia pung janji tu su jadi, tagal Yesus su datang jadi manusia yang dari raja Daud pung turunan.<bt>Long ago, God1 had arranged beforehand so His spokespersons (*prophets) wrote about that Good News in His Clean/Holy Writings. Cuz (elaboration) in that aforementioned Writing, God promised to send His Child, Yesus, to become human. But now His promise has happened/been fulfilled, because Yesus came becoming a human who was a descendant of raja Daud. [EXEG: Gk “which he promised beforehand”; Dhao “His promise happened/was fulfilled” Are these equivalent? A: Complex circle of irrealis-realis in vs.1-4. He promised beforehand (the gospel concerning His Son) … This was fulfilled in JC … I, Paul, am JC's servant (vs.1).] [NOTE: problem with earlier version /manusia biasa/ intended to contrast with deity, but some UNS's were assuming the contrast was with nobility (also a legitimate reading), and so it set up problems.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive + (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive + (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perì: topic of the Good News"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">perì: topic of the Good News katà sárka: as far as being human is concerned, on the human side<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>NRSV: which he promised beforehand through his prophets in the holy scriptures, the gospel concerning his Son, who was descended from David according to the flesh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Yesus bukan cuma orang biasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma Yesus bukan cuma orang biasa sa, te Dia tu, raja Daud pung turunan.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ma di sablá laen, Tuhan Allah kasi tunju bukti bilang, Yesus Kristus, ju jadi Dia pung Ana sandiri. Te Yesus pung Roh tu, batúl-batúl barisi, sama ke Tuhan Allah. Deng Tuhan ju pake Dia pung kuasa ko kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati. Tagal itu, kotong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah pung Ana tu, andia Yesus, kotong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang kotong.<bt>But on the other side/hand, God1 showed proof that, Yesus Kristus, also was His own Child. Cuz (elaboration) Yesus' Spirit is truly clean/holy/pure, just like God. And God2 also used His power to cause Yesus to live again from His death. Because of that, we know that God's Child is Yesus, our-inc Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc. [EXEG: SSA; Roh here is grammatically Jesus' spirit not the H.S. Indo Christian conventions require it to be capitalised. But then this makes the common understanding lean towards it being the H.S. Any mention of spirit relating to Jesus is going to default to H.S.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà pneuma hagiosúnees: not used for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">katà pneuma hagiosúnees: not used for the Holy Spirit in the New Testament; contrasts with katà sárka NRSV: and was declared to be Son of God with power according to the spirit of holiness by resurrection from the dead, Jesus Christ our Lord,<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma di sablá laen, Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma di sablá laen, Tuhan Allah kasi tunju bukti, bilang, Yesus Kristus, ju jadi Dia pung Ana sandiri. Te Tuhan su pake Dia pung kuasa ko kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati. Deng Yesus pung Roh tu, batúl-batúl barisi. Deng Dia su jadi kotong pung Bos.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta, te Dia pili sang beta jadi Dia pung utusan ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán di mana-mana. Te Dia mau ko orang bukan Yahudi dong ju parcaya sang Dia, deng idop iko Dia pung mau. Beta ju mau ko orang dari samua suku-bangsa parcaya sang Kristus deng idop iko Dia pung mau.<bt>Yesus showed his good liver/heart (*grace) to me, cuz/for (elaboration) He chose me to be His *apostle to tell His message/request all over the place. Cuz (elaboration) He wants that non Yahudi people also believe in Him, and live according to His will. I also want people from all ethnic groups to believe in Kristus and live according to His will. [EXEG: SSA, HCE. On switch from ‘we’ to ‘I’, SSA, Moo, and others consider this to be what is called an ‘epistolary “we”’ or an ‘editorial “we”’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV undertranslated ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV undertranslated ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chárin: privilege hypèr tò onómatos autou:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">chárin: privilege hypèr tò onómatos autou: goes with the whole sentence, the reason why Paul and his friends are motivated is that they know what sort of person (onómatos) Jesus is.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: through whom we have received grace and apostleship to bring about the obedience of faith among all the Gentiles for the sake of his name,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Bagitu ju deng bosong di kota Roma. Bosong datang dari banya suku-bangsa di banya tampa. Yesus Kristus su pili ame sang bosong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari su! Mari maso jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Like that also with you-pl in Roma city. You came from many ethnic groups in many places. Yesus Kristus has chosen you saying, &lt;&lt;Come on! Come enter and become My person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: including yourselves who are called"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: including yourselves who are called to belong to Jesus Christ,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Andia ko beta kirim ini surat kasi bosong di Roma, deng kasi inga bilang, Tuhan Allah ada sayang sang bosong. Dia ju minta ko bosong jadi Dia pung orang yang idop barisi.<bt>That is why I am sending this letter to you in Roma, and reminding [you] that, God1 loves you. He also requests that you become His people who live holy/cleanly. [STYLE: Message]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta sambayang ko Tuhan Allah, kotong pung Bapa, deng Yesus Kristus, kotong pung Bos, kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae, deng kasi bosong idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I pray that God1, our-inc Father, and Yesus Kristus, our Boss, show Their good livers (*grace), and enable you to live safely (external), peacefully (relationships), and calmly (inner being). [EXEG: Morris' and others comments that /eirene/ is restricted in this context to inner peace have no support from the immediate context, from standard Gk lexicons (e.g. BAGD, LN, etc.), nor from the meaning of Heb. /shalom/ with which they acknowledge this greeting is in parallel. The restriction seems to be someone's fabrication that gets repeated, rather than one than has a solid basis. See Chuck's PPT word study on /eirene/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To all God's beloved in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: To all God's beloved in Rome, who are called to be saints: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus sambayang kasi sang dia pung tamán dong<bt>Paulus prays for his friends</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta buka beta pung surat ni, deng minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Yesus Kristus ada karjá di bosong pung hati. Beta ju minta tarima kasi, tagal orang yang tenga di pamarenta Roma pung da'era samua, ada ba'omong so'al bosong pung parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>I open this letter of mine by thanking God1, because Yesus Kristus is working in your livers/hearts. I also say thank you, because people who live in all the Roma government's areas, are talking about your faith in Yesus. [EXEG: Gk. “throughout” the world is hyperbole. KM clarifies this as meaning “throughout the Roman world/empire”; ALT vague hyperbole “people everywhere” is also acceptable, but check that it is taken as hyperbole, not literally (e.g. is this saying that in Paul's time, their faith had been proclaimed in Semau and Ndao?).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Prooton: first, but there isn't any"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Prooton: first, but there isn't any "second"; take it as "first of all" or "let me begin" NRSV: First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for all of you, because your faith is proclaimed throughout the world.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Beta sambayang sonde putus-putus kasi sang bosong. Batúl! Tuhan sandiri tau bilang, apa yang beta omong ni, batúl. Dia ju tau beta karjá deng ponu samangat, ko kasi tau orang so'al Dia pung Ana pung Carita Bae.<bt>I pray without stopping for you-pl. That's true! God2 himself knows that, what I say here, is true. He also knows I work with full enthusiasm, to tell people about His Child's Good Story.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en tooi pneúmatí mou: Gk idiom--Paul's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">en tooi pneúmatí mou: Gk idiom--Paul's inner being, his total being, without holding back NRSV: For God, whom I serve with my spirit by announcing the gospel of his Son, is my witness that without ceasing I remember you always in my prayers,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan sandiri tau, bilang, apa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan sandiri tau, bilang, apa yang beta omong tu, batúl. Dia tau beta karjá deng ponu samangat, ko kasi tau orang so'al Dia pung Ana pung Carita Bae. Dia ju tau, bilang, beta sambayang sonde putus-putus kasi sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Tiap kali beta sambayang, beta minta bagini: &lt;&lt;Tuhan, beta sandiri sonde tau dia pung jalan karmana. Ma kalo iko Tuhan pung mau, na, buka jalan ko beta bisa pi lia beta pung tamán dong di Roma.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every time I pray, I request like this: &lt;&lt;God2, I myself don't know how it can be/happen. But if [it is] according to God2's will, na, open the path so I can go see my friends in Roma.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poos: somehow euodootheésomai: I will be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">poos: somehow euodootheésomai: I will be helped on my way there<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>NRSV: asking that by God's will I may somehow at last succeed in coming to you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Beta sambayang bagitu, te beta rindu mau lia sang bosong, ko beta bisa bagi kasi bosong kuasa dari Tuhan pung Roh, ko biar bosong jadi Tuhan pung orang yang batahan lebe kuat.<bt>I pray for you like that, cuz/for (elaboration) I long/yearn to see you-pl, so that I can give/divide up among you power from God2's Spirit, so that you become God2's people who endure more strongly</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stjrichthjnai: established, stronger in the sense"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">stjrichthjnai: established, stronger in the sense of more firm and unchanging in attitude or belief . NRSV: For I am longing to see you so that I may share with you some spiritual gift to strengthen [establish] you-<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta pung maksud bagini: kalo beta jadi datang ko tenga deng bosong, beta mau kasi kuat bosong pung hati, ko bosong pung parcaya bisa lebe kuat. Deng beta mau ko bosong ju kasi kuat beta pung hati.<bt>My intent is like this: if it works out for me to come and stay with you-pl, I want to strengthen your livers/hearts, so that your faith can be stronger. And I want for you-pl also to strengthen my liver/heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: or rather so that we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: or rather so that we may be mutually encouraged by each other's faith, both yours and mine.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta suka ko bosong tau bilang, su banya kali beta pung maksud mau pi lia sang bosong di Roma sana. Ma sampe sakarang balóm tau jadi-jadi ju. Naa, kalo beta jadi datang, beta harap ada banya orang yang masi parcaya kuat sang Kristus, sama ke di tampa laen dong. Deng bagitu, beta pung karjá ada hasil bae.<bt>Loved siblings! I want you-pl to know that, already many times my intention was to come see you in Roma over.there. But until now it hasn't been able to happen. Naa [+shift], if/when I manage to come, I hope there will be many people still believing strongly in Kristus, the same as in other places. In that way, by work will have good results/yield/success/harvest. [EXEG: “that I may have some fruit among you” From what he has already said about building them up/ making their faith stronger, a harvest of an increase in their knowledge and faith (SSA, NCV, Morris, CR) seems more likely than just the conversion of more people (CEV).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balóm tau jadi ju = hasn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">balóm tau jadi ju = hasn't been able to happen, stronger than /balóm jadi-jadi/ = hasn't worked out ; ***discuss UNS suggestion ; *** 2009 changed to broader meaning &amp; revised note</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphoí: fellow believers, the way Christians"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">adelphoí: fellow believers, the way Christians talk to each other karpòn: fruit, results, outcome; win converts, have something tangible happen<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>NRSV: I want you to know, brothers and sisters, that I have often intended to come to you (but thus far have been prevented), in order that I may reap some harvest among you as I have among the rest of the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, kalo beta jadi datang, beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Naa, kalo beta jadi datang, beta harap ada banya orang jadi parcaya sang Kristus, sama ke hasil bae yang beta dapa di tampa laen dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14-15" />Biar karmana ju, beta rasa beta musti kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang samua orang. Bae itu orang yang pake bahasa Yunani ko, orang kafir yang pake bahasa laen ko, orang bésar ko, orang kici ko, orang sakola ko, deng orang sonde sakola ju. Andia ko beta su siap mau pi Roma sana ko lia ame sang bosong.<bt>No matter what, I feel I must tell God1's Good News to all people. Both to those people who speak Greek or, kafir (without major/civilised religion) who use other languages or, big/important people or, little/no social status or, schooled people, or non schooled people or [whatever]. That's why I am ready to go to Roma over.there to see you-pl. [EXEG: Gk Greeks and barbarians evokes several aspects, so we've explicated more that one.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Helleesín: Greeks = civilized and cultured"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Helleesín: Greeks = civilized and cultured vs. savage sophois: educated vs. ignorant<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>opheilétees: under obligation próthymon: eager, really want to help, enthusiastic, psyched<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>NRSV: I am a debtor both to Greeks and to barbarians, both to the wise and to the foolish -hence my eagerness to proclaim the gospel to you also who are in Rome</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bae itu orang yang pake bahasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bae itu orang yang pake bahasa Yunani ko, orang yang sonde tau adat ko,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Kabar Bae ada pung kuasa ko kasi salamat samua orang<bt>That Good News of God2's, has power to save all people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta sonde malu sadiki ju so'al Tuhan Yesus pung Kabar Bae. Te kalo orang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, itu Kabar ada pung kuasa dari Dia ko kasi salamat sang itu orang dari dia pung sala-sala. Naa, orang Yahudi dong dapa tau ini hal lebe dolo, ais baru suku-bangsa laen dong.<bt>I am not even a bit embarassed about Lord Yesus' Good News. Cuz (elaboration) if a person believes in God, that News has power from Him to save that person from his wrongs. Naa, [+shift] the Yahudi people got to know this matter first, and after.that.then other ethnic groups.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaischýnomai: feel shame because I trusted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">epaischýnomai: feel shame because I trusted something and it let me down prooton: probably time, not importance<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>NRSV: For I am not ashamed of the gospel; it is the power of God for salvation to everyone who has faith, to the Jew first and also to the Greek.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 8:38</note><v n="17" />Itu Kabar ju kasi tunju Tuhan pung jalan ko bekin batúl orang sala. Itu samua bisa jadi, asal orang parcaya sang Dia. Te ada tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>That News also shows God2's way for making right people who are wrong/guilty people. It all is able to happen/come into being, as long as people believe in Him. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings saying, [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu Kabar ju kasi tunju karmana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Itu Kabar ju kasi tunju karmana Tuhan bekin batúl orang sala. Itu samua ba'akar di orang pung parcaya. Te ada tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Orang musti parcaya sang Tuhan Allah dolo,<bt>&lt;&lt;People must believe in God1 first,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">baru dong bisa babae deng Dia.<bt>only then can they be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te kalo dong idop parcaya sang Dia,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if they live believing in Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">baru dong dapa idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>only then can they obtain true life/can truly live.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dikaiosýnee: God's activity in putting people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">dikaiosýnee: God's activity in putting people in the right. Not God's character. No article. (CHECK PARALLELS FROM HERE.) NRSV: For in it the righteousness of God is revealed through faith for faith; as it is written, “The one who is righteous will live by faith.”<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Habakuk 2:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan mara sang orang yang sonde mau kanál sang Dia<bt>God2 is angry with people who don't want to know Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi tau bagini: ada orang yang sonde toe sang Dia. Deng ada yang bekin hal jahat macam-macam. Ma Tuhan sonde tarima dong pung bekin-bekin tu. Di dong pung dalam hati, ini orang dong su tau mana yang batúl. Biar bagitu ju, ma dong maen bekin tarús hal-hal yang sonde batúl dong. Dong buju-buju orang sampe itu orang dong ju sonde tau mana yang batúl lai. Andia ko Tuhan mau kasi turun hukuman sang dong dari langit.<bt>But God1 has told/made known/explained like this: there are people who don't give.a.hoot about Him. And there are those who do all.sorts of evil things. And God2 doesn't accept/not put up with/rejects those deeds of theirs. In their inner livers/consciences, these people already know what is right/true/correct. Even that being the case, nevertheless they continue to habitually do things which are not right/correct/true. They keep trying to cajole/ persuade/convince people to.point.that those people also don't know what is right/correct/true anymore. That's why God will send down punishment to them from the sky. [EXEG: Gk “katechóntoon” polysemy 1) have, possess, 2) occupy, 3) suppress, prevent, hold down, hold back, restrain, hinder. Most agree sense #3 is intended here. It is a willful act against truth, and by implication those who hold it “they don't know the truth because of you”. KM “keep trying to cajole/ persuade/convince” covers suppressing by means of both words and actions. HCE, Message: God's angry displeasure erupts...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Message: God's angry displeasure erupts... ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Message: God's angry displeasure erupts... *** (2009) Note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asebeian: indifference to God, ungodliness ap'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">asebeian: indifference to God, ungodliness ap' ouranou: from heaven = from God himself (like "instructions from Washington")<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>katechóntoon: suppressing; they don't know the truth because of you. NRSV: For the wrath of God is revealed from heaven against all ungodliness and wickedness of those who by their wickedness suppress the truth.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal, di dong pung dalam hati,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Padahal, di dong pung dalam hati, dong su tau mana yang batúl. Ma dong bekin tarús hal-hal yang sonde batúl dong. Dong ju tepa orang ko dong sonde tau mana yang batúl. (@@placement of ju? truth/truth about God?)</Message></Annotation><v n="19-20" />Ini orang dong sonde ada pung alasan ko bela diri, te hal-hal yang orang bisa tau so'al Tuhan Allah tu, su jalás. Ko Dia sandiri yang su kasi tunju na! Beta pung maksud bagini: mulai dari Dia bekin langit deng bumi sampe sakarang, kalo orang mau mangarti so'al Tuhan pung diri, deng Dia pung kuasa yang sonde putus-putus, bisa sa! Biar Tuhan sandiri sonde kantara, ma kotong manusia masi bisa kanál sang Dia dari apa yang Dia bekin. Andia ko beta bilang, itu orang jahat dong sonde ada pung alasan ko bisa bela diri lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde tau apa-apa so'al Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>These people don't have any reason/excuse/basis to defend themselves, cuz (elaboration) things which people can know about God, are already clear. For He himself is the one who has shown (it/them) [+obvious]! My meaning/intent is like this: beginning from Him making/creating the sky and earth until now, if people want to understand about God's self/being, and His never-ending power/authority, of course they can! Even though God2 himself isn't visible, nevertheless we-inc humans still can know Him from what He does/makes. That's why I say, those evil people don't have any reason/excuse/basis to be able to defend themselves anymore saying, “I don't know anything about God.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin-bekin = often has negative overtones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">bekin-bekin = often has negative overtones *** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dióti: the reason NRSV: For what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">dióti: the reason NRSV: For what can be known about God is plain to them, because God has shown it to them. Ever since the creation of the world his eternal power and divine nature, invisible though they are, have been understood and seen through the things he has made. So they are without excuse;<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma dong sonde ada pung alasan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma dong sonde ada pung alasan ko bela diri, te samua hal yang orang bisa tau so'al Tuhan tu, su jalás. Ko Tuhan Allah sandiri yang su kasi tau na! Beta pung maksud bagini: dari dolu sampe sakarang, kalo orang mau mangarti so'al Tuhan pung diri, deng Dia pung kuasa yang sonde putus-putus, bisa sa! Biar Tuhan sandiri sonde kantara, ma kotong manusia masi bisa kanál sang Dia dari apa yang Dia bekin. Ini su jadi bagitu dari dolu-dolu, mulai dari Dia bekin langit deng bumi. Andia ko beta bilang, itu orang jahat dong sonde ada pung alasan ko bisa bela diri lai.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jadi, biar dong tau so'al Tuhan, ma dong sonde mau mangaku sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan tu, kotong pung Allah!&gt;&gt; Dong ju sonde mau minta tarima kasi sang Dia. Ais dong pung pikiran jadi kaco, sampe dong sonde mangarti apa yang batúl lai. Dong jadi bingung deng karang-karang macam-macam so'al Tuhan pung diri. Deng dong pung hati jadi galáp.<bt>So (consequently), even though they know about God2, they nevertheless don't want to acknowledge Him saying, &lt;&lt;That God2, is our Allah!&gt;&gt; They also don't want to thank Him. So/Then, their thinking has become chaotic/confused, to the point that they don't understand anything that is right/true/correct anymore. They become confused and make.up (implied: falsely) all sorts of things, about God2's self/being. And their hearts/livers became dark. [EXEG: NLT - "And they began to think up foolish ideas of what God was like."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emataioótheesan: nonsense, foolishness, no value eskotísthee:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">emataioótheesan: nonsense, foolishness, no value eskotísthee: failure to think right about moral issues. Not ignorance<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>asýnetos: stupid, empty headed, intellect without understanding NRSV: for though they knew God, they did not honor him as God or give thanks to him, but they became futile in their thinking, and their senseless minds were darkened.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, dong pung pikiran jadi kaco,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ais, dong pung pikiran jadi kaco, sampe dong karang-karang macam-macam, so'al Tuhan pung diri. Te dong sonde mangarti apa-apa yang batúl lai, sampe jadi bingung, deng dong pung hati jadi galáp.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 4:17-18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Dong sandiri-sandiri suka angka-angka diri bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, orang yang mangarti banya hal!&gt;&gt; Biar dong pikir bagitu, ma dia pung batúl, dong tu, bodo ke karbó.<bt>They each lift.up=praise themselves saying, &lt;&lt;I here, am a person who understands many things (=wise)!&gt;&gt; But even though they think like that, the truth is, they, are as stupid as waterbuffalo (=Max degree of stupid). [shows speaker attitude]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sophoì: wise (opposite ends of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">sophoì: wise (opposite ends of the wisdom scale) emoorántheesan: they have turned into fools<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>NRSV: Claiming to be wise, they became fools;</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ais dong sonde sémba sang Tuhan Allah yang talalu hebat, te dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde parlú Tuhan macam bagitu!&gt;&gt; Ma dong mulai sémba patong macam-macam, model ke manusia. Ais itu, dong ju sémba patong model ke burung, ke binatang laen, sampe ju model ke ular dong. Deng bagitu, dong tola buang sang Tuhan yang sonde tau mati, ko ganti deng barang yang bisa mati!<bt>So/Then, they don't worship God1 who is extremely amazing, cuz/for (elaboration) they say, &lt;&lt;We-exc don't need a God2 like that!&gt;&gt; But they began to worship various statues, patterned after humans. After that, they also worshipped statues patterned like birds, like other animals, even to being patterned like snakes (category). In doing that, they push.away/reject God2 who lives forever, to exchange/replace [Him] with things that can die! [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: SSA suggests that this is a “downward spiral of idolatry” - it got worse and worse, progressing from humans to animals...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barang mati = inanimate ; barang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">barang mati = inanimate ; barang yang bisa mati = mortal ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and they exchanged the glory"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: and they exchanged the glory of the immortal God for images resembling a mortal human being or birds or four-footed animals or reptiles.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, dong sonde sémba sang Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ais, dong sonde sémba sang Tuhan Allah yang talalu hebat, te dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde parlú Tuhan macam bagitu!&gt;&gt; Ma dong sémba patong macam-macam, model ke manusia ko, ke burung ko, ke binatang ko, ke ular dong ko. Deng bagitu, dong tola buang sang Tuhan yang idop sampe salamanya, ko ganti deng barang yang bisa mati!</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:16-18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Andia ko Tuhan kasi tenga pi parsetan sang dong, ko biar dong bekin iko dong pung mau-mau sa. Dia kasi biar ko dong bekin iko hal jahat macam-macam yang ba'akar di dong pung hati. Sampe-sampe dong sonde tau malu lai. Ais dong bekin kamomos macam-macam deng dong pung badan sandiri, deng babekin bagitu ju deng orang laen pung badan.<bt>That's why God2 just abandons them (dismissively, let them do whatever--almost a curse word), so that they follow their own desires. He allows for them to do according to all sorts of evils things which are rooted in their livers/hearts. To the point that eventually they don't know how to be embarrassed/ashamed anymore. Then they did all.sorts of defilement with their own bodies, and mutually.did them like that also with other people's bodies. [STYLE: HCE] [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful of trying to reduce too much redundancy and wind up undertranslating important points here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dong pung mau-mau = segala macam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">dong pung mau-mau = segala macam nafsu/kapingin ; babekin = mutual do</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paredooken: he lets them be taken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">paredooken: he lets them be taken over by their desires NRSV: Therefore God gave them up in the lusts of their hearts to impurity, to the degrading of their bodies among themselves,<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Di dong pung dalam hati, dong su tau ajaran yang batúl so'al Tuhan Allah, ma dong sonde mau toe. Dong pung pikiran su ancor-ancor, ais dong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada lebe bae, biar botong bekin macam-macam sa, sampe rusak-rusak, te sonde ada risiko apa-apa!&gt;&gt; Dong sémba sang barang yang Tuhan bekin, ma dong sonde mau sémba sang Tuhan yang bekin itu barang samua! Dong bekin diri ke orang alim, padahal kosong, sonde ada isi!<bt>In their hearts/livers, they already knew things which were true/correct about God1, but they didn't want to care (=they didn't give a damn). Their thinking was destroyed, so they thought saying, &lt;&lt;It's better, let us-exc just do whatever [negative implications-up to no good], to the point that everything is broken/defiled, cuz (reason) there's no risk/ consequences whatsoever!&gt;&gt; They worshipped things which God2 had made, but they didn't want to worship God2 who made all those things! They made themselves out to be devout/pious/religious, but.in.actual.fact [it was] empty, there was no content/substance! [EXEG: last sentence is high-level summary of exchanging something of substance for an empty lie, which is otherwise lost.] [NOTE to daughter translations: If /risiko/ which works well for Kupang, sets up too many problems, try /Ais dong ganti itu ajaran batul, deng ajaran putar-balek./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko jang ada ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">ko jang ada ***</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Te yang batúl, kotong manusia musti puji-puji deng kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah tarús-tarús! Naa, itu baru pantas!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) what is correct/true/in actual fact, we-inc humans must keep praising and honouring/showing respect to God2 continually! Now that's what is appropriate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: because they exchanged the truth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: because they exchanged the truth about God for a lie and worshiped and served the creature rather than the Creator, who is blessed forever! Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Tagal dong pung jahat, andia ko Tuhan kasi tenga pi, ko dong bekin kamomos bagitu, iko dong pung mau-mau sa. Ais dong maen hohongge macam-macam, deng sonde tau malu. Dong pung bini sonde suka tidor deng dong pung laki lai, ma suka yang sonde wajar sa. Te parampuan batidor deng parampuan!<bt>Because of that evil of theirs, that's.why God2 allowed/permitted, that they do difilement like that, according to their desires/passions. So they habitually did all sorts of sexual.playing.around/promiscuity, and had no shame. Their wives didn't like to sleep with their husbands anymore, but just liked what isn't natural. Females reciprocally slept with (=sexual) females! [+speaker attitude marker--who could imagine?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="how to distinguish between sexual and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">how to distinguish between sexual and social?? ; batidor = banae = mount</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For this reason God gave"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For this reason God gave them up to degrading passions. Their women exchanged natural intercourse for unnatural,</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Laki-laki bagitu ju! Dong sonde suka tidor deng dong pung bini lai, ma batidor deng laki-laki sa! Sonde tau malu sadiki ju! Andia ko dong kaná hukuman yang pantas! Te dong su serong jao dari jalan yang batúl.<bt>Males did like that too! They didn't like to sleep with their wives anymore, but they just reciprocally slept with males! They didn't know even a little bit of shame! That's why they get/experience a punishment that is appropriate! Cuz (elaboration) they had strayed/shifted far from the path that is right/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and in the same way"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: and in the same way also the men, giving up natural intercourse with women, were consumed with passion for one another. Men committed shameless acts with men and received in their own persons the due penalty for their error.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dong ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae, sonde usa ta'ika deng Tuhan.&gt;&gt; Andia ko Tuhan kasi tenga pi parsetan, ko dong bekin iko dong pung mau-mau sa! Jadi dong cuma tau pikir yang rusak-rusak sa! Ais dong bekin hal-hal yang tar karu-karuang pung!<bt>They were thinking saying, &lt;&lt;It's better, not to be tied/linked to God2.&gt;&gt; That's why God2 just let them do whatever (dismissively), so that they did according to their own desires/passions! So (consequently), they only knew how to think about things that were ruined/broken (moral)! So/Then they did things that were not even remotely permissible/imaginable/appropriate.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="karu-karuang = harba-biruk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">karu-karuang = harba-biruk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ton theon echein en epignoosei: acknowledge"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">ton theon echein en epignoosei: acknowledge God (BAGD 1.7.1) NRSV: And since they did not see fit to acknowledge God, God gave them up to a debased mind and to things that should not be done.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dong pung idop jadi ponu deng jahat macam-macam. Dong sonde tau bekin yang bae, ma cuma tau bekin jahat sa. Dong balalas. Dong basimpan hati. Dong tukang camburu. Dong bunu orang. Dong suka maen bakanjar. Dong putar-balek. Dong tukang tipu. Dong tukang badodol.<bt>Their lives became full of all.sorts of evil. They didn't know to do what is good, but they only knew how to do evil. They were greedy. They were vengeful. They were envious. They murdered people. They liked to habitually argue. They lied/deceived. They were habitual con artists. They were habitual gossips.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éridos: not just fighting, but partisanship"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">éridos: not just fighting, but partisanship and factions dólou: deception, trickery<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>NRSV: They were filled with every kind of wickedness, evil, covetousness, malice. Full of envy, murder, strife, deceit, craftiness, they are gossips,</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dong suka omong bekin rusak orang laen pung nama. Dong binci sang Tuhan. Dong kurang ajar. Dong suka pandang enteng orang. Dong suka angka-angka diri. Dong suka cari akal busuk macam-macam. Dong suka bamalawan orang tua dong.<bt>They liked to talk ruining other people's names/reputations. They hated God2. They acted inappropriately/rudely. They like to look down on people. They liked to lift.up=exalt themselves. They like to find all sorts of rotten ideas/schemes. They liked to reciprocally oppose/rebel against their parents/elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** short sentences to carry accusation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** short sentences to carry accusation</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: slanderers, God-haters, insolent, haughty, boastful,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: slanderers, God-haters, insolent, haughty, boastful, inventors of evil, rebellious toward parents,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Dong sonde mau tau apa yang batúl. Dong langgar dong pung janji sandiri, sampe orang sonde bisa parcaya sang dong lai. Dong sonde tau sayang orang. Dong sonde ada pung rasa kasian sang orang sadiki ju.<bt>They didn't want to know what was right/true. They violated their own promises, to.the.point that people couldn't believe/trust them anymore. They didn't know how to love/pity people. They didn't have even a bit of pity/compassion/mercy for people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="farék"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">farék</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: foolish, faithless, heartless, ruthless."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: foolish, faithless, heartless, ruthless.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Dong su tau Tuhan Allah pung atoran yang bilang, orang yang bekin jahat macam bagitu dong, pantas kaná hukuman mati. Biar dong su tau itu atoran, ma dong masi bekin jahat yang sonde karu-karuang pung. Bukan bagitu sa, ma dong maen tusu-tusu sang orang laen, ko dong ju iko bekin jahat bagitu. Itu su talalu!<bt>They knew God1's regulation that says, people who do evil like that, are appropriate to be given the death penalty/punished by death. Even though they knew that regulation, they nevertheless still did evil that wasn't fitting/imaginable/permissible. And not just that, but they also habitually inciting/persuading/ provoking other people, so that they would also go along doing evil like that. That's just too much!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** begitu &gt; itu atoran"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** begitu &gt; itu atoran</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: They know God's decree, that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: They know God's decree, that those who practice such things deserve to die-yet they not only do them but even applaud others who practice them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan ju mara sang bangsa Yahudi yang Dia su pili<bt>God2 also is/gets angry with the Yahudi ethnic group whom He had chosen</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Lu su dengar so'al jahat macam-macam tadi, aa? Ais mangkali lu ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Itu orang dong pung jahat su talalu!&gt;&gt; Kalo lu su pikir bagitu, awas ó! Te lu sandiri ju jahat bagitu. Andia ko lu sonde ada pung alasan ko bela diri, biar lu tu, sapa. Kalo lu ada bilang, orang laen dong jahat deng pantas kaná hukum, jang lupa bilang, lu ju ada lempar sala di lu pung diri sandiri. Te lu bekin jahat bagitu ju!<bt>You-sg heard about all sorts of evil just then (=that I just listed), right? So then perhaps/probably you are thinking saying, &lt;&lt;Awe'! [+critical] The evil of those people is just too much!&gt;&gt; If you are thinking like that, be careful ó! Cuz (elaboration) you-sg yourself are also evil like that. That's why you don't have a reason/excuse to defend yourself, regardless of who ever you might be. If you are saying that, other people are evil and it is appropriate that they be punished, don't forget that, you also are throwing wrong =accusing your own self. Cuz/for (elaboration) you-sg also have obviously done evil like that! [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anapologeetos: CHECK PARALLELS LITERALLY: Therefore, you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">anapologeetos: CHECK PARALLELS LITERALLY: Therefore, you who judge another person are without excuse, whoever you are, because by the reason for which you judge another person, you judge yourself, because you do the same things.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:1, Lukas 6:37</note><v n="2" />Ma kotong tau kalo Tuhan kasi hukum orang yang bekin jahat dong, pasti Dia putus dong pung parkara deng adil.<bt>But we-inc know that if God2 punishes people who do evil, surely He decides their litigations/cases/ disputes/issues justly/fairly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But we know that the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But we know that the judgment of God is true about those who practise such things.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kotong tau satu hal so'al"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma kotong tau satu hal so'al orang yang bekin jahat dong. Andia: Tuhan putus deng adil orang pung parkara.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ko karmana? Mangkali lu ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang bekin jahat dong, pantas kaná Tuhan pung hukuman.&gt;&gt; Padahal lu ada bekin jahat sama ke dong. Ma lu ada pikir, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde kaná Tuhan pung hukuman.&gt;&gt; Ko dia pung pasal apa?<bt>Or what/how? Probably you-sg are thinking saying, &lt;&lt;People who do evil, are.appropriate/fitting to get God2's punishment.&gt;&gt; Whereas in fact you are doing evil like them. But you are thinking, &lt;&lt;I won't get God2's punishment.&gt;&gt; So what chapter is that from? (=idiom, expressing you are not thinking correctly, sort of ‘where do you get that idea from?’) [NOTE to daughter translations: /Ko dia pung pasal apa?/ is an idiom, meaning something like /pikiran begitu muncul dari mana?/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do you think, you who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do you think, you who judge those who do such things, and you do the same, that you will escape the judgment of God?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tuhan Allah ada kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang lu. Deng Dia talalu sabar so'al lu pung bekin-bekin. Ma akurang ko lu lia sang Dia deng mata sablá? Mangkali lu sonde mangarti bilang, Dia kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang lu, ko lu kasi tenga lu pung sala-sala dong, deng kambali pi sang Dia.<bt>God1 is showing His good liver/heart to you-sg. And He is exceeding patient about your deeds [NOTE: grammatical construction of "deeds" here has negative overtones]. But why are you looking at Him with one eye (=idiom; looking at him disparagingly, with.contempt)? Probably you don't understand that, He is showing His good liver/heart to you, so that you leave/abandon your sins, and return to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapu-sapu/urut dada deng lu pung bekin-bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">sapu-sapu/urut dada deng lu pung bekin-bekin = way too patient (Idiom)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Or do you despise the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Or do you despise the riches of his kindness/goodness, and forbearance/tolerance, and longsuffering/patience, not knowing that the kindness/goodness of God leads you to repentance?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma lu ni, kapala batu deng sonde mau dengar! Deng lu sonde mau kasi tenga lu pung sala sadiki ju! Jadi lu ada bekin ko lu pung hukuman tamba barát lai. Te nanti kalo dunya su kiamat, Tuhan mau nilei samua orang pung idop. Deng samua orang nanti tau bilang, Tuhan putus orang pung parkara deng batúl. Itu waktu, Dia hukum barát sang lu, tagal Dia sonde tarima lu pung bekin-bekin.<bt>But you here, are stubborn and don't want to listen/obey! And you don't want to leave even a tiny bit of your sins! So (consequently), you are making it so your punishment increases even heavier. Cuz (elaboration) later when the end of the world has come, God will evaluate all people's lives. And all people will later know that, God decides people's cases/disputes in a correct/true manner. At that time, He will punish you heavily, because He doesn't accept/put up with those deeds [+negative] of yours.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** nilei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** nilei</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you have a hard"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you have a hard and stubborn/unrepentant heart. So then, you are making your own punishment even greater on the Day when God's wrath and right judgments will be revealed.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Lu ada idop karmana, na, nanti Tuhan balas iko lu pung bekin.<bt>However you are living, na, later God2 will reciprocate/respond according to your deed/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who will give back to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who will give back to every person according to what he has done.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 62:12, Kata-kata Mutiara 24:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Te orang yang bekin hal bae tarús-tarús, nanti Dia kasi sang dong, idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Dong yang tarima hormat, nama bae, deng idop tarús-tarús deng Dia.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) people who continually do good things, later He will give them, true life which doesn't end. They are the ones who will receive honor, a good name, and live continually with Him. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** neg &gt; pos in 1st"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** neg &gt; pos in 1st sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Eternal life to those who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Eternal life to those who by patiently continuing to do good, are looking for glory and honor and immortality.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma Tuhan sonde tarima orang yang bekin jahat. Dia mara batúl sang dong, te dong cuma tau bamalawan sa. Dong sonde bekin iko hal yang batúl, te dong cuma tau bekin iko hal yang jahat sa.<bt>But God2 doesn't accept/put up with people who do evil. He gets/is really angry at them, cuz/for (elaboration) they only know how to reciprocally oppose each.other. They don't do according to/obey things which are right/correct/true, cuz/for (elaboration) they only know how to just do according to/obey things which are evil. [EXEG: Gk /eritheia/ can mean 1) selfish ambition, or 2) rebellious, hostile. In the immediate context of vs.8 plus the larger context of chapters 1-2, the second sense is a better fit. HCE, LN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But anger and wrath to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But anger and wrath to those who are selfish / unsubmissive / rebellious / contentious, and do not obey the truth, but obey unrighteousness.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan sonde tarima orang jahat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma Tuhan sonde tarima orang jahat pung bekin. Dia mara batúl sang dong, te dong cuma tau bamalawan sa. Dong sonde bekin hal yang batúl, te dong cuma tau bekin hal yang jahat sa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Samua orang yang ada bekin jahat dong, nanti kaná susa deng calaka. Biar orang Yahudi ko, orang bukan Yahudi ko, dong samua kaná abis.<bt>All people who are doing evil, later will be afflicted with difficulty and misfortune. Regardless of whether Yahudi people or, not Yahudi people or [whoever], they will all get it [+negative]. [EXEG (in both 9 &amp; 10): We haven't been able to figure out how to get “Jews first” in without either skewing it way out of focus with a separate proposition, or else using a polysemous particle /dolo/ that carries baggage, and doesn't fit the current structure unless we go more literal in the sentence structure. In the immediate context and the run of the book, the higher point is that both groups get either anguish and distress (vs.9), or glory, honour, and peace (vs.10). Morris (on 9) the Jew is “the first recipient of judgment”; but SSA ‘first’ means ‘especially, certainly’; Moo “directed particularly to the Jew”; TH “not chronological”. It is undertranslated like the CEV and TH, but the order of the two groups implies the Jews are prior (in focus, worldview prominence, or precedence). If there is a good solution, it should probably only go in once so as to not be heavy. Footnote added.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added, footnote added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added, footnote added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Tribulation/trouble and anguish/pain/distress to every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Tribulation/trouble and anguish/pain/distress to every person who does evil, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;kasi orang Yahudi dolo, deng kasi orang bukan Yahudi ju.&gt;&gt; Di ayat 9 dia pung maksud bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua nanti kaná susa, lebe-lebe orang Yahudi, ma orang bukan Yahudi ju.&gt;&gt; Di ayat 10 dia pung maksud bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti Tuhan angka tinggi-tinggi sang samua yang bekin hal bae, lebe-lebe orang Yahudi, ma orang bukan Yahudi ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Yunani Bible writes saying, “to the Yahudi people first/foremost, and to non Yahudi people too”. In verse 9 it means “Everyone will experience trouble/difficulty, particularly the Yahudi people, but also the non Yahudi people.” In verse 10 it means, “Later God2 will glorify/elevate on high everyone who does good things, particularly the Yahudi people, but also the non Yahudi people.”</bt></note><v n="10" />Ma samua orang yang ada bekin hal bae, nanti Tuhan angka tinggi-tinggi sang dong, deng kasi hormat sang dong ko dong idop aman deng dame. Biar dong orang Yahudi ko, orang bukan Yahudi ko, dong samua dapa abis.<bt>But all people who are doing good things, later God2 will *glorify them (=elevate on high), and give honor to them so that they live in safety (situation) and peace (relationships). Regardless of whether they are Yahudi people or, not Yahudi people or [whatever], they will all obtain it [+positive]. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But glory, honor, and peace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But glory, honor, and peace to everyone that does good, to the Jew first, and also to the Gentile.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-26 08:52:16Z" /></Annotation><v n="11" />Te Tuhan sonde pili-pili muka na!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2 obviously doesn't choose faces (=show preferences/bias)! [DISCOURSE: in 9-11 there is chiasmus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because God does not show"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because God does not show preferences [judges everyone by the same standard].</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 10:17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tuhan pung Atoran tu, jato kaná sang samua orang. Naa! Kalo ada orang yang sonde tau itu Atoran, yang bekin sala, nanti dia tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah. Deng kalo ada orang yang su tau itu Atoran, ma dia bekin sala, nanti Tuhan pake itu Atoran lai ko putus dia pung hukuman. Dong ju nanti tapisa buang dari Tuhan, tagal dong su langgar Dia pung Atoran.<bt>God's Regulations/Law [+that we know about], applies to all people. So then! If there is a person who doesn't know that Law, who does wrong, s/he will be separated off/cut off from God2. And if there is a person who already knows that Law, but he does wrong, later God will use that Law again to decide his punishment. They will also be separated off/cut off from God2, because they have transgressed/violated that Law of His. [EXEG: This is a safe middle ground rendering, reflected in most translations. 1) it deliberately preserves a kind of ambiguity presented in the Gk and debated among the commentators as to whether this is meaning a) the Torah Law given to Moses, or b) a universal law of God justice [as implied by vs.14]; 2) it reflects what all commentators agree about a) universal sinfulness, and b) universal punishment; 3) it reflects the different outcomes for the 2 groups from the Gk (don't force the two to be identical-they are not in the Gk), but makes explicit that the end result is the same; 4) the whole verse (higher level) is structured in parallel as is the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="putus bale = decide back on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">putus bale = decide back on *** KT perish (frm John &amp; 2 Cor; see note as Jn 3:16)<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because as many as have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because as many as have sinned without the Law will also die without the Law. And as many as have sinned with the Law will also die with the Law. apolountai: perish; in the sense of eternal destruction, not just normal death, "dey goin get cut off from God"<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Kalo mau babae deng Tuhan Allah, sonde cukup deng cuma dengar Dia pung Atoran to'. Te orang ju musti bekin iko Dia pung Atoran, baru Dia mau tarima sang dong. Jang cuma dengar sa!<bt>If want to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God1, it's not enough/sufficient to only just hear His Law. Cuz (elaboration) people must also do according to His Law, only then is He willing to accept them. Don't just only listen! [DISCOURSE: Last sentence to emphasise the point Paul is making. Repetition and recap are common features of RL discourse. We probably don't do enough of it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te orang ju musti bekin iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te orang ju musti bekin iko Dia pung Atoran, baru dong bisa babae deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akroatai: &quot;nuff&quot; is an intransitive verb,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">akroatai: "nuff" is an intransitive verb, not an adjective, so it takes "no" LITERALLY: Because it is not the hearers of the Law who are justified before God, but the doers of the Law are justified.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Biar orang bukan Yahudi dong sonde tau Tuhan pung Atoran pung isi, ma dari dong sandiri ada yang bekin iko itu Atoran. Te dong pung hati sandiri yang kasi tau sang dong, mana yang batúl, deng mana yang sala.<bt>Even though people who are not Yahudi don't know the contents of God2's Law, nevertheless there are people from among them who do according to/obey that Law. Cuz/for (elaboration) their own heart's are what tells them, which (of choices) is right/correct/true, and which is wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV undertranslated!!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV undertranslated!!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when the Gentiles, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when the Gentiles, who do not have the Law, do by nature the things the Law says, they, who do not have the Law, are a Law for themselves.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang bukan Yahudi dong sonde tau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Orang bukan Yahudi dong sonde tau Tuhan pung Atoran pung isi. Padahal dari dong sandiri ada yang bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, te dong pung hati sandiri yang kasi tau sang dong, mana yang batúl, deng mana yang sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Deng bagitu, dong kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan pung Atoran ada tatulis dalam dong pung hati, sama ke banáng yang Tuhan tanún di dong pung hati. Dong pung dalam hati sandiri yang nilei apa yang dong bekin. Ais dong pung pikiran sandiri yang tudu kalo dong ada bekin sala, deng kasi tau kalo dong ada bekin batúl.<bt>In that way, they show that, God2's Law is written in their hearts/livers, like a thread which God2 wove in their hearts/livers [STYLE: Message: “woven into the very fabric of our creation”.] Their own consciences (=inner hearts) are what evaluates/judges what they do. So/Then, their own thinking is what accuses/ condemns if/when they do wrong, and lets them know/tells/affirms if/when they do right/correctly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They show the requirement of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They show the requirement of the Law written on their hearts, their consciences bearing witness, and their thoughts meanwhile accusing or excusing them,</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Jadi nanti kalo Tuhan su angka sang Yesus Kristus jadi Tukang Putus Parkara, Dia mau pareksa sampe alus-alus hal-hal rahasia yang tasambunyi dalam orang pung hati. Beta ajar bagitu, sama ke yang ada di Tuhan pung Kabar Bae.<bt>So (consequently), later when God2 has already lifted.up/appointed Yesus Kristus to be the Habitual Decider of Litigations (*judge), He wants to carefully/finely examine all the secrets which are hidden in people's hearts/livers. I teach like that, just like that which is in God2's Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** end of world removed (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** end of world removed (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: in the day when God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: in the day when God will judge the secrets of people according to my Good News through Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Biar orang Yahudi bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, ma itu sonde kasi salamat sang dong [\s2]<bt>Even if Yahudi people do according to/obey God2's Law, nevertheless that doesn't save them [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran sa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran sa, sonde kasi salamat sang orang Yahudi [\s2]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi bosong yang orang Yahudi, karmana? Bosong suka angka-angka diri bilang, bosong sandiri sa yang pegang Tuhan pung Atoran yang Dia kasi turun lewat ba'i Musa, aa? Bosong ju suka mulu bésar so'al bosong pung hubungan deng Tuhan.<bt>So (consequently) you-pl who are Yahudi people, how is it? You-pl like to keep elevating/praising yourselves saying, you-pl are the only ones who hold God2's Law which He handed down via Gf Musa, right? You-pl also like to big.mouth=boast about your relationship with God2. [NOTE: Gk is 2s, but go to 2p for genre.; EXEG: “in God” bragging (negatively valued) about unique relationship with God, fitting high-level themes. NRSV, NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if you call yourself"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if you call yourself a Jew, and you depend on the Law, and brag about God,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong suka angka diri, bilang, bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bosong suka angka diri, bilang, bosong orang Yahudi. Bosong parcaya sang Tuhan pung Atoran. Bosong suka mulu bésar so'al bosong pung hubungan deng Tuhan.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Batúl! Bosong su tau Tuhan pung mau. Bosong su tau mana yang paling bae. Bosong su tau ini hal dong samua, tagal guru dong su ajar sang bosong dari Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>That's right! You already know God2's will. You already know what is the best/most good. You already know all these things, because teachers have taught you from God2's Law. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and know his will, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and know his will, and approve the things that are more excellent/superior/best, because you are instructed from the Law,</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Bosong parcaya diri bilang, bosong bisa kasi tunju jalan sang orang yang sonde tau mau pi mana. Bosong anggap diri sama ke taráng yang bacaya kasi samua orang yang idop dalam galáp.<bt>You believe in yourselves (=have confidence) that, you can show the way for people who don't know where they want to go [implies morally or in life]. You consider yourselves like light that shines for all people who live in darkness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and are sure that you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and are sure that you are a guide for the blind, a light for those who are in darkness,</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Tagal bosong bapegang Tuhan pung Atoran, bosong pikir bosong tau samua-samua, deng bosong su pegang samua yang batúl, aa? Andia ko bosong pikir bosong bisa ajar orang bodo deng ana kici yang sonde tau apa-apa.<bt>Because you hold firmly to God2's Law, you think you know everything [NOTE: grammatical construction suggests "everything there is to know"], and you already possess/hold everything that is true/correct, right? That's why you think you can teach ignorant/unschooled/stupid people and small children who don't know anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV seems to have missed the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV seems to have missed the Gk ‘toddlers’, rendering it as ‘young people’</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: an instructor of the foolish,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: an instructor of the foolish, a teacher of babies/the young, who has in the Law the full content of knowledge and truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jadi beta mau tanya bagini: bosong suka ajar orang laen dong, ma akurang ko bosong sandiri sonde mau balajar apa-apa?! Bosong suka nae mimbar, ko parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang jang pancuri.&gt;&gt; Ma akurang ko bosong sandiri pancuri?!<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: you-pl like to teach other people, but why do you yourselves not want to learn anything?! You like to get up in the pulpit, to command saying, “People shouldn't steal.” But why is it that you yourselves steal?! [EXEG: SSA: rhetorical questions as accusations.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma akurang ko ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">ma akurang ko =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, you who teach another,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, you who teach another, don't you teach yourself? You who preach that a person should not steal, do you steal?</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Bosong ajar bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang maen serong deng orang yang bukan lu pung laki ko lu pung bini.&gt;&gt; Ma akurang ko bosong sandiri maen serong?! Bosong binci mati sang barang sosonggo dong, ma akurang ko bosong sandiri se'ok barang dari ruma sosonggo?!<bt>You teach saying, &lt;&lt;Don't play.around.sexually with people who are not your-sg husband or your-sg wife.&gt;&gt; But why is that you yourselves play.around.sexually?! You extremely hate traditional.worship things, but why is it that you yourselves steal things from the traditional.worship houses?! [NOTE to daughter translations: if team is confused /barang sosonggo/ = BI /barang berhala/; /ruma sosonggo/ = BI /rumah berhala/. If no lexical equivalent for /se'ok/ try /curi diam-diam/ or /curi sambunyi-sambunyi/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="se'ok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">se'ok</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hierosyleis: profane their temples? plunder their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">hierosyleis: profane their temples? plunder their temples? How honest are you: do you profit from the things you denounce? LITERALLY: You who say a person should not commit adultery, do you commit adultery? You who hate/detest idols, do you rob temples?<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Bosong omong bésar so'al Tuhan pung Atoran, ma akurang ko bosong sandiri langgar itu Atoran, deng bekin malu sang Tuhan bagitu?!<bt>You speak.big=brag about God2's Law, but why is it that you yourselves violate that Law, and make God2 ashamed/embarrassed in that way?!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You who boast in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You who boast in the Law, do you dishonor God by breaking the Law?</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te dari dolu, ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal bosong orang Yahudi pung jahat, andia ko orang laen dong suka bekin hina sang Tuhan Allah pung nama bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) from long ago, it was written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings saying, &lt;&lt;Because of you-pl Yahudi people's evil, that's why the other/foreign (=non Yahudi) people often despise God's good name.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Tagal bosong, andia ko orang bukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">&lt;&lt;Tagal bosong, andia ko orang bukan Yahudi dong suka bekin hina sang Tuhan Allah pung nama bae.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the name of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the name of God is blasphemed by the Gentiles because of you, as it is written.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Biar orang Yahudi dong sunat, itu ju sonde kasi salamat sang dong [\s2]<bt>Even if Yahudi people get *circumcised, that also doesn't save them [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sunat ju sonde kasi salamat sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Sunat ju sonde kasi salamat sang orang Yahudi [\s2]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Bosong yang orang Yahudi musti sunat iko Tuhan pung Atoran, aa? Itu jadi tanda bilang, bosong yang ada pung hak tarima Tuhan pung janji. Ma kalo bosong langgar Tuhan pung Atoran, Tuhan sonde tarima sang bosong. Bosong jadi sama ke orang bukan Yahudi, deng sama ke orang yang sonde parná sunat.<bt>You-pl who are Yahudi people must be circumcised according to God2's Law, right? That is a sign that, you are the ones who have the rights to receive God2's promise/s. But if you violate God2's Law, God2 doesn't accept you. You become like people who are not Yahudi people, and like people who were never circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because circumcision is good for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because circumcision is good for something if you keep the Law, but if you are a Law breaker, your circumcision becomes as uncircumcision.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo bosong bekin iko Tuhan pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Kalo bosong bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, bosong musti sunat ko jadi tanda, bilang, bosong orang Yahudi yang ada pung hak tarima Tuhan pung janji. Ma kalo bosong langgar Tuhan pung Atoran, Tuhan sonde tarima sang bosong. Bosong jadi sama ke orang bukan Yahudi, deng sama ke orang yang sonde parná sunat.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Pikir bae-bae! Te kalo orang yang sonde sunat bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, nanti Tuhan tarima sang dia, sama ke dia orang Yahudi yang su sunat, to?<bt>Think carefully! Cuz (elaboration) if a person who is not circumcised acts/does according to God2's Law, later God will accept him, the same as if he were a Yahudi person who was already circumcised, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, if he who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, if he who is not circumcised keeps the righteousness of the Law, won't his uncircumcision become as circumcision?</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ma ati-ati, ó! Te kalo orang bukan Yahudi yang sonde sunat, bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, nanti dong kasi tunju apa? Dong kasi tunju bosong pung sala bilang, bosong orang Yahudi yang su sunat, ada langgar Tuhan pung Atoran, biar bosong su pegang itu Atoran dari dolu-dolu.<bt>But, be careful, ó! Cuz/for (elaboration) if non Yahudi people who are not circumcised, do according to God's Law, later they reveal/show what? They reveal your-pl wrongs saying, you Yahudi people who are circumcised, are violating God2's Law, even though you have held/possessed that Law from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And shall not uncircumcision [Gentiles],"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And shall not uncircumcision [Gentiles], which is by nature, if it keep the Law, judge you [Jews], who by the letter [Law] and circumcision transgress the Law?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jang pikir bilang, orang yang jadi ba'i Abraham pung turunan, deng yang su sunat di kulit, itu yang bekin dia jadi Tuhan pung orang yang batúl. Sonde!<bt>Don't think that, a person who is Gf/Ff Abraham's descendant, and who has been circumcised on/in the skin, that is what makes him become God2's true person. No!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he is not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he is not a Jew who is one outwardly, neither is the circumcision that which is outward in the flesh.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang pikir, bilang, orang yang jadi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jang pikir, bilang, orang yang jadi ba'i Abraham pung turunan, deng yang su sunat di kulit, itu yang bekin dia jadi orang Yahudi yang batúl.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Yang jadi Tuhan pung orang yang batúl, andia orang yang babae deng Tuhan. Te sunat yang batúl, yang bekin orang jadi Tuhan pung ana tu, bukan tanda di kulit, ma tanda di hati yang Tuhan pung Roh ada bekin. Tuhan yang angka puji sang orang macam bagitu, bukan manusia yang angka puji.<bt>Those who are/become God2's true people, are the people who are in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. Cuz/for (elaboration) true circumcision, which makes people become God2's child(ren), is not a sign on the skin, but a sign in the heart/liver which God2's Spirit makes. It is God2 who lifts.up=praises people like that, not humans who lift.up=praise [them]. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But he is a Jew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But he is a Jew who is one inwardly, and circumcision is from the heart, by the Spirit, and not from the letter. The praise for that is not from people, but from God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yang jadi orang Yahudi yang batúl,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Yang jadi orang Yahudi yang batúl, andia orang yang dengar-dengar Tuhan pung Roh. Itu sama ke tanda sunat di dia pung hati. Bukan Atoran yang ada tulis dalam buku yang bekin orang jadi Tuhan pung ana. Yang jadi orang Yahudi yang batúl, andia orang yang babae deng Tuhan.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 30:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Biar orang Yahudi ada hak tarima pusaka dari Tuhan pung janji, itu ju sonde kasi salamat sang dong [\s2]<bt>Even if/though Yahudi people have the right to receive the inheritance from God2's promise, that also doesn't save them [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hak tarima pusaka dari Tuhan pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Hak tarima pusaka dari Tuhan pung janji, ju sonde kasi salamat sang orang Yahudi [\s2]</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Kalo bagitu, jadi orang Yahudi yang sunat tu, dia pung ontong apa? Mangkali bosong pikir bilang, orang Yahudi dapa lebe banya deng lebe bae, dari orang bukan Yahudi dong, to?<bt>If that's the case, what's the benefit/advantage of becoming a *circumcised Yahudi person? Probably you are thinking saying, the Yahudi people will get more (quantity) and better (quality) than the non Yahudi people, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what advantage does the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what advantage does the Jew have? Or what value is there in circumcision?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Batúl! Jadi orang Yahudi ada pung ontong dalam banya hal. Partama, tagal Tuhan Allah kasi tugas sang orang Yahudi ko tulis deng jaga bae-bae Dia pung Kata-kata.<bt>True! Being a Yahudi person has advantages in many things/ways. First, because God1 gave the job/responsibility to the Yahudi people to write and carefully safeguard His Words. [#1-MESSAGE] [EXEG: (Morris) “First of all leads us to expect a list, but Paul never gets past his first;...” UNSs asked about this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Much indeed, in every way."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Much indeed, in every way. First, because the [message/words/sayings/promises] of God [was/were] [entrusted/committed] to them.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Batúl! Jadi orang Yahudi ada pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Batúl! Jadi orang Yahudi ada pung ontong dalam banya hal. Partama, tagal Tuhan Allah kasi tugas sang orang Yahudi ko tulis deng jaga Dia pung Kata-kata/pasán / sarakan/titip Dia pung Kata-kata (kasi) sang orang Yahudi dong. / parcaya sang orang Yahudi dong, ko jaga/piara Dia pung pasán deng bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jadi karmana? Mangkali bosong ada pikir kata, Tuhan sonde bisa bekin iko apa yang Dia omong, tagal ada orang Yahudi saparu yang sonde parcaya sang Dia, ko?<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Perhaps you-pl are thinking that, God2 is not able to do according to what He said, because there are some Yahudi people who don't believe Him, or (what)?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What if some of them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What if some of them did not [believe/have faith]? Will their [unbelief/unfaithfulness] [cancel/nullify] the faithfulness of God?</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Sonde mungkin! Te biar samua orang di ini dunya tukang putar-balek, ma Tuhan sandiri omong yang batúl tarús! Inga te ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi so'al Tuhan pung diri bilang,<bt>Impossible/no way! Cuz (elaboration) even if/though all the people in this world are habitual twisters-turners =decievers/liars, nevertheless God2 himself continues to speak what is true! Remember that it is written in the Clean/Holy Writings about God2's self saying, [NOTE to daughter translations: if /so'al Tuhan pung diri/ is problematic, just use /so'al Tuhan/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan tu, omong batúl, biar samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan tu, omong batúl, biar samua orang di ini dunya tukang putar-balek! Te ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi so'al Tuhan pung diri, bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada orang yang lempar sala bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who accuse saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde putus parkara deng adil.<bt>He doesn't judge disputes with fairness/justice.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma nanti dong dapa tau bilang,<bt>But later they will come to know that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">apa yang Dia omong tu, memang batúl.<bt>what He says, is really true.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia pasti manáng,<bt>He will surely win,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dia sonde mungkin omong sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>because it is not possible for Him to speak wrongly.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: context of Ps. 51 is David acknowledging the justice of God's judgement against him. But the wording and Pauline purpose here are different from Ps. 51, following the LXX, not the Hebrew, introducing the "win/prevail" term.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of course not! God must"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of course not! God must be true, even though every person is a liar. As it is written, "That you might be [shown to be right/proved right] in what you say, and might win when you are [judged/on trial]."</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 51:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma kalo kotong ada bekin sala, ais, itu kasi tunju lebe taráng sang samua orang bilang, apa yang Tuhan bekin tu, memang batúl. Kalo bagitu, kotong mau bilang apa? Mau bilang, Tuhan sonde adil kalo Dia kasi hukum sang kotong, ko? (Te ada orang saparu yang omong bagitu na.)<bt>But if we-inc are doing wrong, then, that shows more clearly to all people saying, that which God did there, is really correct. If that's the case, what can we-inc say? Should [we] say, God isn't fair/just if He punishes us, or (what)? (Cuz (elaboration) there are some people who talk like that.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if our [unrighteousness/wrongdoing/injustice] shows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if our [unrighteousness/wrongdoing/injustice] shows the righteousness of God more clearly, what shall we say? Is God unjust to [punish us/brings his wrath on us/brings his anger on us]? (I am talking like a human being.)</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Sonde mungkin! Tuhan sonde sala kalo Dia kasi hukum sang kotong. Te Dia ada pung hak ko kasi hukum orang yang bekin sala di ini dunya.<bt>Impossible/no way! God2 isn't wrong if He punishes us. Cuz/for (elaboration) He has the right to punish people who do wrong in this world. [EXEG: Morris argues against TEV, (NLT), saying “ Some understand the question as “If God is not just, how can he judge the world?” (GNB), but this does not seem to be what the Greek means and it is not convincing. There is no theoretical reason why an unjust deity should not preside in an unjust judgment. Paul's point is rather that, assuming as all do that God will judge the world, some must be punished. Unless this happens, what occurs will not be judgment. It is the exercise of wrath, not the character of God, that is the point of it all.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) Helong (overtranslation): If/when He did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">(al) Helong (overtranslation): If/when He did not punish/judge us for doing wrong then he is not fair/just/straight. But when he punishes us it shows that he is straight, therefore he has the right to judge everything that does wrong in the world.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Of course not! Then how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Of course not! Then how can God [judge/condemn] the world?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Naa! Kalo beta omong kosong, itu kasi tunju bilang, Tuhan pung hukuman tu, batúl. Kalo beta su kasi tunju Dia pung hebat bagitu, akurang ko Dia pareksa beta pung idop, ais putus beta pung parkara bilang, apa yang beta bekin tu, sala?<bt>So then! If I speak.emptily=lie, that shows that, God2's punishment is true/correct. If I have already shown His amazingness like that, then why does/will He examine my life and decide my case saying, what I have done, is wrong/sin? [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** examine my life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** examine my life</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because if the truth of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because if the truth of God has increased through my lie, for his glory, then why am I judged to be a sinner?</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Jang bagitu! Te kalo mau iko pikiran bagitu, bosong iko orang yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar ko kotong bekin jahat lebe banya, ko biar yang bae ju batamba banya!&gt;&gt; Orang yang omong bagitu, pantas kaná hukum. Ma ada orang yang omong bekin rusak beta pung nama bilang, beta ada ajar orang bagitu.<bt>Don't do that! Cuz (elaboration) if you want to follow thinking like that, you-pl follow people who say, &lt;&lt;Just let us-inc do more evil, so that that which is good also becomes more!&gt;&gt; People who speak like that, deserve to be punished. But there are people who speak destroying my name saying, I teach people that. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Kalo kotong bekin jahat lebe banya,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">&lt;&lt;Kalo kotong bekin jahat lebe banya, nanti yang bae ju jadi lebe banya!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoon to krima endikon estin: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">hoon to krima endikon estin: the people, not the statement. LITERALLY: And not instead (as some slanderously report and affirm that we say), Let us do evil, that good may come? The condemnation for [that/them] is just.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sonde ada satu orang ju yang hati lurus batúl, te samua bekin sala abis<bt>There is not a single person who is truly straight livered/righteous, cuz (elaboration) absolutely everyone has done wrong</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde ada satu orang ju yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Sonde ada satu orang ju yang bekin iko Tuhan pung mau tarús, te samua bekin sala abis</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Jadi karmana? Bosong pikir kotong yang orang Yahudi lebe bae dari orang bukan Yahudi dong? Sonde mungkin! Te beta su kasi tunju sang bosong bilang, samua orang jato sala, biar dia orang Yahudi ko, orang bukan Yahudi ko.<bt>So (consequently), how is it? Do you-pl think those of us-inc who are Yahudi people are better than the non Yahudi people? Impossible/no way! Cuz/for (elaboration) I have shown you that, everybody falls into sin (entrenched phrase), regardless of whether s/he is a Yahudi person or, a non Yahudi person or [whatever kind of person]. [EXEG: SSA, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then? Are we better"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then? Are we better than they? No, in no way. For we have already proved that both Jews and Gentiles are all under sin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te beta su kasi tunju sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te beta su kasi tunju sang bosong, bilang, sala pung kuasa kaná sang samua orang,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sonde ada orang yang idop lurus tarús.<bt>&lt;&lt;There is no person who lives straight/righteous continually.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu ju!<bt>Not a single one!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;There"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "There is none righteous, no not one.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Sonde ada orang yang mangarti batúl so'al Tuhan.<bt>There is no person who truly understands about God2.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu ju yang cari kanál sang Tuhan.<bt>Not even a single one who seeks to know2 God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is none that understands,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is none that understands, there is none that seeks for God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Dong samua su serong dari jalan idop yang lurus.<bt>They all have strayed/diverged off track from the life path that is straight.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais dong su sonde laku-laku lai.<bt>So they aren't profitable/popular/acceptable anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sonde ada orang yang kasi tunju hati bae.<bt>There is no person who show a good liver/heart (=good/kind/generous/gracious).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu ju!<bt>Not a single one!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They have all turned away,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They have all turned away, they have together become [unprofitable/worthless]. There is nobody that does good/kind/benevolent, no, not one.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:10-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 14:1-3, 53:1-3</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Dong pung omong, baboo busuk,<bt>What they say, has a rotten stench,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke kubur yang orang su gali ulang.<bt>like a grave which people have dug up again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong pung mulu cuma tau kasi kaluar putar-balek sa.<bt>Their mouths only know how to speak out twisting-turning=decei/liest.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong pung kata-kata yang kaluar dari dong pung mulu,<bt>Their words which come out from their months,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke ular pung racon.<bt>are like a snake's poison.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Their throat is an open"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Their throat is an open grave. They have used deceit with their tongues. The poison of snakes is under their lips.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 5:10, 140:4</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Dong pung mulu cuma tau maki orang,<bt>Their mouths only know how to curse people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng omong yang busuk ko bekin saki hati orang sa,<bt>and speak that which is rotten to just make people have sick.livers/hearts = hatred,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te itu yang kaluar dari dong pung hati busuk.<bt>cuz/for (elaboration) that is what comes out from their rotten livers/hearts.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whose mouth is full of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whose mouth is full of cursing and bitterness.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 10:7</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Dong sonde taku-taku mau bunu orang.<bt>They're not afraid/hesitant to kill people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Their feet are swift to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Their feet are swift to shed blood.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Dong pi mana, na,<bt>Wherever they go, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong suka bekin kaco di situ,<bt>they habitually make chaos there,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bekin susa macam-macam sang orang.<bt>and cause all sorts of difficulty to people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: [Destruction/ruin] and [misery/distress/trouble] are in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: [Destruction/ruin] and [misery/distress/trouble] are in their paths.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Dong idop sonde tau badame,<bt>They live without knowing how to live.in.mutual.peace/right relationships,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng sonde tau idop deng hati tanáng.<bt>and without knowing how to live with calm livers/hearts. [EXEG: explicating 2 of 3 senses of Gk. /eirene/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They have not known the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They have not known the way of peace.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:15-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 59:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Dong sonde bisa tahan diri,<bt>They cannot control/restrain themselves,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal sonde ada rasa taku sang Tuhan sadiki ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>because they do not have even a bit of fear toward God.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: following NLT “They have no fear of God to restrain them.” which they cross reference to Ps. 36:1 with the same wording (apparently they see “before their eyes” as a Hebrew idiom?). Morris also links this with Ps. 36:1, but comments on “before their eyes” being linked with “fear” as “curious”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: There is no fear of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: There is no fear of God before their eyes.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 36:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Naa! Kotong tau bilang, Tuhan kasi Dia pung Atoran sang orang yang musti tondo deng itu Atoran dong. Deng bagitu, dong sonde ada pung alasan apa-apa lai. Nanti samua orang di ini dunya musti mangada sang Tuhan Allah, ko Dia putus dong pung parkara bilang, dong sala, ko sonde.<bt>So then! We-inc know that, God2 gave/gives His Law to people who must bow/be.under.subject.to that Law. In that way, they don't have excuses anymore. Later all people in this world must face God1, so that He decides their case, saying they are wrong/guilty, or not. [EXEG: on Gk. /hypodikos/ focusing on the judging process, rather than the resulting punishment, see NRSV, SSA, LN.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if UNS's can't get WHY they have no more excuse, try /...apa-apa lai, ko bela diri, bilang, dong tu, orang hati lurus./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now we know that whatever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now we know that whatever the Law says, it says to those who are [under/subject to] the Law, that every mouth may be [stopped/silenced], and all the world may become [guilty/ answerable/ accountable/ subject to judgment/ liable to punishment] before God.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Andia ko sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan cap sang beta bilang, orang hati lurus, tagal beta bekin iko Dia pung Atoran samua.&gt;&gt; Sonde bisa! Te Tuhan pung Atoran yang kasi tunju bilang, kotong samua ada bekin sala.<bt>That's why there is not even a single person who can speak saying, “God2 has stamped/branded/ categoraised me as a straight livered/righteous person, because I do according to/obey all of God2's Laws.” Can't [say it]! Cuz/for (elaboration) it's God2's Law which shows that, we-inc all do wrong. [EXEG: NLT: For the more we know God's law, the clearer it becomes that we aren't obeying it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(Te Tuhan pung Atoran yang kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">(Te Tuhan pung Atoran yang kasi tunju, bilang, kotong samua ada bekin sala. / Te kalo kotong tau Tuhan pung Atoran deng bae, su jadi lebe jalás, bilang, kotong su langgar na!)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For that reason, no [person/human]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For that reason, no [person/human] can be [justified/made right] before [him/God] by the deeds of the Law. For by the Law the knowledge of sin comes.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 143:2, Galatia 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus dolo, baru Tuhan Allah cap sang kotong orang hati lurus<bt>We-inc must believe in Lord Yesus first, only then will Lord God stamp/categorise us as straight livered/righteous people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jang bingung so'al Tuhan pung rancana yang tunju jalan ko kotong bisa babae kambali deng Dia. Yang batúl, kotong bisa babae deng Dia, ma bukan tagal bekin iko Dia pung Atoran. Te Dia pung Atoran sandiri ada tulis bagitu, deng Dia pung jubir dolu-dolu dong ju kasi tau bagitu dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi.<bt>Dont' be confused about God2's plan which shows the path so that we can return to a reciprocally good relationship with Him. In actual fact, we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, but not because of following His Law. Cuz/for (elaboration) in His Law itself it is written like that, and His spokespersons (*prophets) from long ago also told like that in God2's Clean/Holy Writings. [NOTE to daughter translations: most vernaculars don't have an easy /rancana/ word like KM does. Try something like /jalan/ or /cara/.] [EXEG: NLT - But now God has shown us a different way of being right in his sight-not by obeying the law but by the way promised in the Scriptures long ago.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now, the righteousness of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now, the righteousness of God is shown without the Law. The Law and the Prophets testify to that.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Tuhan Allah cap kotong orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia waktu kotong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Dia sonde pili-pili muka, te Dia bekin bagitu kasi sang samua orang yang parcaya sang Yesus.<bt>God1 stamps/categorises us as straight livered/righteous people who are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him when we-inc believe in Yesus Kristus. He doesn't choose faces (=discriminate), cuz/for (elaboration) He does like that for all people who believe in Yesus like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Even the righteousness of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Even the righteousness of God which is by faith in Jesus Christ toward all who believe. For there is no difference.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Tuhan tu, barisi. Deng Tuhan pung sarat, andia kotong ju musti barisi, baru Dia bisa tarima ame sang kotong. Ma samua orang bekin sala. Andia ko biar samua orang coba-coba bekin diri babae deng Tuhan, ma kotong sonde bisa sampe di Tuhan pung sarat yang tinggi tu.<bt>God2 is clean/holy/pure. And God2's requirement is that we-inc also must be clean/holy/pure, only then can He receive/accept us. But all people do wrong/sin. That is why even though everyone keeps trying to make themselves in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, nevertheless we-inc can't arrive/reach/get to the point of God2's high requirement [that-specific]. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: SSA discusses Gk “have sinned” as a “gnomic or timeless aorist” expressing a general truth, so in Timor lgs best to not use perfective /su/; NLT, Message] [NOTE: discussions in Bible reading groups made it clear that people were not understanding the second half of the verse. Restructured 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-15 01:07:22Z" /></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te samua orang bekin sala. Andia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te samua orang bekin sala. Andia ko sonde ada orang yang bisa bekin diri batúl, iko Tuhan pung ukur yang hebat.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-26 08:54:45Z">2014</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For all have sinned, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For all have sinned, and [come short of/fall short of/lack] the glory of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan Allah sandiri yang kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae deng putus bilang, kotong su sonde sala lai. Dia tarima sang kotong bagitu, tagal Yesus Kristus su tabús ame kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>But even though that's the case, nevertheless God himself is the one who showed His good liver/heart (=grace), and decided that, we are no longer wrong/guilty. He accepts us like that, because Yesus Kristus has *redeemed/paid to set free us from our sins. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They are justified by his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They are justified by his free [grace/gift], through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju sang Yesus ko jadi korban tutu malu yang hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala dong. Ma kotong musti parcaya sang Dia bilang, Dia tarima ame kotong pung hukuman. Jadi Dia kasi tumpa Dia pung dara, deng mati ganti sang kotong. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah kasi tunju bilang, apa yang Dia putus ame tu, batúl. Dolu, Dia talalu sabar, ais Dia pili ko lupa buang sala-sala yang orang bekin dolu. Ma kalo Dia sonde hukum orang yang sala, Dia sonde adil. Jadi Dia buka jalan ko biar Yesus Kristus bisa pikol ame kotong orang sala pung hukuman. Sakarang, Dia kasi tunju sang samua orang bilang, Dia bekin yang bae tarús. Ais samua orang sala, yang parcaya sang Yesus, Dia putus ko cap sang dong ke orang hati lurus.<bt>God1 has chosen/designated Yesus to be a covering-embarrassment/guilt (=paying penalty) sacrifice which erases away our-inc wrongs. But we-inc must believe in Him that, He accepted/received our punishment. So (consequently), He spilled His blood [NOTE: a culturally significant phrase, e.g. used to acknowledge the service/sacrifice of war heroes or others dying for a cause], and died in exhange for us. In that way, God shows that, what He has decided, is right/correct/true. Previously He was extremely patient, so He chose to completely forget the wrongs which people did previously. [NOTE to daughter translations: if vernacular equivalent of /korban tutu malu/ is restricted to sexual offenses, try /pili Yesus jadi korban ko bayar kotong pung denda/.] But if He does not judge/punish wrong/guilty people, He is not just. So (consequently) He opened the way/means so that Yesus Kristus could bear we wrong/guilty people's punishment. Now He shows all people that, He does that which is good continually. So then all wrong/sinful/guilty people, who believe in Yesus, He decides to stamp/brand/categorise them as straight/righteous people. [EXEG/DISCOURSE: SSA, Uma; ellipsed propositions to connect 25 &amp; 26. UNS's not get it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Verse transition between 25 &amp; 26"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Verse transition between 25 &amp; 26 in Gk is unclear <span class="Italic">(25) </span>*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: God presented Jesus to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: God presented Jesus to be a [means of cancelling guilt/sacrifice for cancelling guilt/means of forgiveness/ propitiation/sacrifice for sins], through faith in his blood, to declare his [righteousness/justice] for the forgiveness/passing by/disregarding of past sins because of the [patience/forbearance] of God. LITERALLY: To show his righteousness at this time, that he might be just, and the justifier of the one who believes in Jesus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia kasi tumpa Dia pung dara,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dia kasi tumpa Dia pung dara, deng mati kasi sang kotong. Deng bagitu, Tuhan kasi tunju, bilang, apa yang Dia putus ame tu, batúl. Dia talalu sabar, ais Dia pili ko lupa buang sala-sala yang orang bekin dolu. Sakarang, Dia kasi tunju sang samua orang, bilang, Dia bekin yang bae tarús. Ais, samua orang sala, yang parcaya sang Yesus, Dia putus ko bekin dong jadi batúl.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Jadi karmana? Mangkali bosong pikir bosong bisa omong bésar, tagal Tuhan su tarima sang bosong, ko? Sonde bisa! Mau kasi tunju satu Atoran yang bekin bosong babae deng Tuhan, ko? Bosong kira Tuhan tarima sang bosong tagal bosong bekin hal bae, ko? Sonde bisa! Kotong cuma bisa kasi tunju Atoran yang bilang, Tuhan Allah tarima sang kotong tagal kotong parcaya sang Yesus. Bagitu sa!<bt>So (consequently) how is it? Perhaps you-pl are thinking you can talk-big=boast, because God2 has accepted you, [+tag question= huh]? [You] Can't! [Do you] Want to show one Regulation that can make you-pl in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, [+tag question = huh]? Do you think God2 will accept you because you do good things, [tag question = huh]? [You] Can't! We-inc can only show the Regulation that says, God1 receives/accepts us because we-inc believe in Yesus. That's it/all! [EXEG: CONTEXT: “law of faith” = “believing in Jesus” has already been made explicit in vs.22-26. Out of context Paul would be talking about the Mosaic law, so Jesus here would be an anachronism. But in context it is not.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong pikir bosong babae deng Tuhan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bosong pikir bosong babae deng Tuhan, tagal bosong bekin hal bae, ko? Sakarang, bosong pikir bosong bisa omong bésar, ko? Sonde bisa! Mau kasi tunju satu Atoran yang bekin bosong babae deng Tuhan, ko? Bosong kira Tuhan tarima sang bosong tagal bosong bekin hal bae, ko? Sonde bisa! Kotong cuma bisa kasi tunju Atoran yang bilang, kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah tagal kotong parcaya sang Dia.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Where is boasting then? It"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what rule/reason? By deeds? No, but by the rule of faith.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Andia ko sakarang kotong su tau bagini: orang bisa babae deng Tuhan tagal dong parcaya sang Dia, bukan tagal dong bekin iko Dia pung Atoran sa.<bt>That's why now we know/understand like this: people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because they believe in Him, not just because they do according to his Law. [EXEG: if object of ‘faith’ needs clarification, SSA says “believe in Christ”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore we conclude that a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore we conclude that a person is justified by faith without the deeds of the Law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Naa, beta mau tanya bagini: Tuhan Allah cuma tarima orang Yahudi sa, ko, Dia ju tarima orang laen dong? Batúl! Dia tarima samua!<bt>Naa, I want to ask like this: does God only receive/accept the Yahudi people, or, does He also accept other people? True! He accepts them all!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Is he the God of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Is he the God of the Jews only? Isn't he the God of the Gentiles too? Yes, also the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, beta mau tanya bagini: Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Naa, beta mau tanya bagini: Allah tu, cuma jadi Tuhan kasi orang Yahudi sa, ko, Dia ju jadi Tuhan kasi orang bukan Yahudi dong? Batúl! Dia jadi Tuhan kasi dong samua!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Te Tuhan Allah tu, cuma satu sa. Deng cuma ada satu jalan yang Dia tarima ko kotong manusia bisa babae deng Dia. Andia, tagal kotong parcaya sang Kristus. Itu jalan tu, kasi sang orang Yahudi deng orang bukan Yahudi ju.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) the.aforementioned God1, is only just one. And [there is] only just one path/way which He accepts so that we-inc humans can be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. That.is, because we believe in Kristus. That path, is for the Yahudi people and the non Yahudi people also. [EXEG: NLT. Note ‘Kristus’ as object of faith here--it's explicit in Gk. in vs.22. (sort of), so we don't have to maintain the Abraham model here. See SSA.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Kristus as object of belief"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** Kristus as object of belief (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because there is only one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because there is only one God, who will justify the circumcision from faith and the uncircumcision through faith.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:4, Galatia 3:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Jadi beta mau tanya bagini: kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan, itu hapus buang Dia pung Atoran, ko? Sonde! Yang batúl, itu bekin sah Dia pung Atoran.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: if we-inc believe in God2, does that wipe away His Law, or [not]? No! in actual fact, it makes His Law legal/officially.validated. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /bekin sah/ is too challenging to translate, try /kasi tunju, bilang, itu Atoran tu, batúl/. KM deliberately vague with /Tuhan/ as object of belief (can map to either God or Kristus). Higher-level context also allows, but does not require, /Yesus/ or /Kristus/. I (CEG) prefer this current rendering, because this section is building on the example of Abraham and the prophets believing in God.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do we then [make void/nullify/cancel]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do we then [make void/nullify/cancel] the Law by faith? Of course not! Instead, we [establish/uphold/confirm/validate/giving it its true value] the Law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Conto dari ba'i Abraham. Dia babae deng Tuhan tagal parcaya sang Tuhan [\s2]<bt>Example from forefather Abraham. He was in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because [he] believed in God2 [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi ame conto dari botong orang Yahudi pung nene-moyang, ba'i Abraham. Kotong bisa balajar apa dari dia, so'al orang jadi babae deng Tuhan tagal parcaya sang Kristus?<bt>So (consequently), take an example from our-exc Yahudi people's ancestor, Gf/Ff Abraham. What can we learn from him, about becoming/ obtaining a reciprocally good relationship with God2 because.of believing in Kristus? [EXEG: NLT] [NOTE to daughter translations: for most languages /balajar/mangajar/ is the same word and so ambiguous with Actor-Undergoer relationship unclear. Suggest alt. /tau/ (also in vs.2); ALSO your lgs should have a term for apical/first/founding ancestor.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** structure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** structure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what shall we say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what shall we say that Abraham, our physical ancestor, has found?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, kalo kotong lia conto dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, kalo kotong lia conto dari botong orang Yahudi pung nene-moyang, ba'i Abraham, kotong bisa balajar apa, so'al jadi babae deng Tuhan tagal parcaya sang Kristus tu?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Kotong bisa balajar bagini: kalo Abraham bisa babae deng Tuhan tagal dia bekin hal yang bae, dia ju ada pung dasar ko bisa omong bésar di manusia pung muka. Ma di Tuhan pung muka, dia sonde bisa omong apa-apa.<bt>We-inc can learn like this: if Abraham could be in reciprocally right relationship with God2 because he did things which were good, he also has a basis/foundation to talk big (=brag) in front of humans. But in God2's face (=eyes/view), he can't say anything.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if Abraham were justified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if Abraham were justified by deeds, he would have something to boast about, but not before God.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>But it is written in God2's Clean/Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tagal Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>&lt;&lt;Because Abraham believed in God1,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">andia ko Tuhan cap sang dia, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>that's why God2 stamped/marked/categorized him, as a straight liver (=righteous) person who is in a reciprocally right relationship with Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What does the Scripture say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What does the Scripture say? "Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:6, Galatia 3:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Naa, orang yang karjá, tarima dia pung gaji. Itu gaji bukan doi parsén, ma doi yang bos bayar ko ganti itu orang pung cape. Te itu orang karjá pung hak.<bt>Naa, [+shift] a person who works, receives his/her wages. That wage is not gift money, but money which the boss pays to replace/reciprocate that person tiredness/effort. Cuz/for (elaboration) that is that person's right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who works is paid."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who works is paid. His wages are not regarded as a gift, but as something he has earned.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Naa, Tuhan yang ada pung hak ko bilang, orang yang parcaya sang Yesus Kristus bisa babae kambali deng Dia, biar dolu itu orang su bekin sala deng sonde toe sang Tuhan. Sonde ada satu hal yang orang bisa bekin, ko dia babae deng Tuhan. Te orang musti parcaya sang Yesus Kristus, baru Tuhan cap sang dia ke orang hati lurus, deng tarima sang dia.<bt>Naa, [+shift] God2 is the one who has the right to say, a/the person/whoever believes in Him can be in a reciprocally good relationship again (=reconciled) with Him, even though previously that person did wrong and did not care at all about God2 There is not a single thing a person can do, so that s/he can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. Cuz/for (elaboration) a person must believe in Yesus Kristus, only then God2 stamps/marks/categorises him as a straight livered righteous person and accepts him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But to him who believes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But to him who believes in the one who justifies the ungodly, and does not work, his faith is credited to him as righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Raja Daud ju kasi tau bilang, orang pung hati babunga waktu Tuhan Allah cap sang dong bilang, dong tu, orang hati lurus, biar dong sonde bekin apa-apa ju. Te Daud tulis bilang:<bt>King Daud also told saying, person/people's livers flowered (=were joyful) when God1 stamped/marked them saying, they, were straight livered (=righteous) people, even though they didn't do a single thing. Cuz (elaboration) Daud wrote, saying:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: David also describes the happiness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: David also describes the happiness of the person to whom God [gives/credits] righteousness apart from works,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />&lt;&lt;Biar ini orang dong su langgar Tuhan pung Atoran,<bt>&lt;&lt;Even though these people had violated God2's Law,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Dia su hapus buang dong pung sala-sala.<bt>and He has erased away their wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Andia ko dong paling ontong!<bt>That's why they are most fortunate!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang yang bekin jahat dong,<bt>People/Person who did/do evil,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan su lupa buang dong pung sala-sala.<bt>God2 has completely forgotten their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarioi: fortunate, in a good state"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">makarioi: fortunate, in a good state of affairs/position/situation (carries through several verses); often badly translated as "happiness"--whereas the element of "happy" is not really part of the meaning of the word, but perhaps a result LITERALLY: How fortunate are those whose lawlessnesses are forgiven, and whose sins are covered up.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Te kalo Tuhan sonde ba'itong orang pung sala-sala,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if/when God2 does not count a person's wrongs, [EXEG: NLT uses “no longer” rather than “not” to be consistent with the higher level argument. OK for daughter translations to use either /sonde/ or /sonde...lai/.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, itu orang ontong batúl!&gt;&gt;<bt>na, that person is truly fortunate!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: How fortunate is the person"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: How fortunate is the person to whom God will not keep account of their sin.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 32:1-2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Naa, mangkali bosong ada pikir bilang, cuma orang Yahudi yang sunat, yang bisa ontong ko babae deng Tuhan, aa? Deng orang suku-bangsa laen yang sonde sunat, sonde bisa, aa? Sonde! Pikiran bagitu, sala! Andia ko botong su kasi inga sang bosong bilang, tagal Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan, andia ko Tuhan cap sang dia, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia.<bt>Naa [+shift] perhaps/probably you-pl are thinking that, only Yahudi people who are circumcised, are who can be fortunate/lucky enough to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, right? And people of other ethnic groups who are not circumcised, [they] can't, right? No! Thinking like that is wrong! That is why we-exc have reminded you-pl that, because Abraham believed in God2, that's why God2 stamped/marked him as a straight liver (=righteous) person who is in a reciprocally good relationship with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Does this happiness come only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Does this happiness come only to the circumcised, or to the uncircumcised also? For we say that faith was credited to Abraham as righteousness.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kapan Tuhan cap sang Abraham bagitu? Waktu dia su sunat ko, waktu dia balóm sunat? Yang batúl, bukan waktu dia su sunat abis, ma waktu dia masi balóm sunat.<bt>When did God2 stamp/mark Abraham like that? [Was it] when he was already circumcised or, when he was not yet circumcised? What is correct, is not when he had already been circumcised, but when he was still not yet circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then how was it credited?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then how was it credited? When he was circumcised, or uncircumcised? Not in circumcision, but in uncircumcision.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Batúl! Waktu Abraham balóm sunat, Tuhan Allah su cap sang dia, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Tuhan. Lama-lama, baru dia sunat ko jadi tanda bilang, dia jadi orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan. Deng bagitu, Abraham yang buka jalan kasi samua orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Te Tuhan tarima sang samua orang yang parcaya sang Dia, ko dong babae deng Tuhan, biar dong sunat, ko sonde.<bt>Really! When Abraham was not yet circumcised, God1 had already stamped/marked him, a straight liver (=righteous) person who was in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. Eventually, only then did he get circumcised as a sign that he was a person who believed in God2. In that way, Abraham was the person who opened the way for all people who believe in God. Cuz (elaboration) God2 accepts all people who believe in Him, so that they can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, regardless of whether they are circumcised, or not. [EXEG: Morris says, “We get light on the way Abraham was the father of uncircumcised believers by reflecting that Jabal was the father of tent-dwellers and breeders of livestock, while Jubal was the father of musicians (Gen. 4:20-21). In neither case was the paternity literal; it was concerned rather with the characteristics of the people in question.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Dia &gt; Tuhan at end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** Dia &gt; Tuhan at end ; (2009) Note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He received the sign of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He received the sign of circumcision [later], a proof of the righteousness by faith which he had before he was circumcised, that he might be the father of all who believe, even though uncircumcised, and are accepted as righteous.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:10</note><v n="12" />Abraham ju buka jalan kasi botong orang Yahudi yang kaná sunat. Bukan <span class="Italic">tagal</span> botong sunat, ma tagal botong parcaya sang Kristus, sama ke Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan waktu dia balóm sunat.<bt>Abraham also opened the way for us-exc Yahudi people who got circumcised. Not <span class="Italic">because</span> we are circumcised, but because we believe in Kristus, the same as Abraham believed in God2 when he was not yet circumcised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the father of circumcision"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the father of circumcision to them who are not of the circumcision only, but who walk in the steps of that faith of our father Abraham, which he had when he was still uncircumcised.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, na, kotong tarima apa yang Dia janji<bt>If we-inc believe in God1, na, we receive what He promises</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tuhan Allah ada ika janji deng Abraham deng dia pung turunan bilang, lama-lama dunya anteru jadi dong pung pusaka. Tuhan janji bagitu, tagal Abraham parcaya sang Dia, ais Tuhan cap sang dia bilang, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia. Ma Tuhan sonde janji bagitu, tagal Abraham bekin iko Dia pung Atoran dong.<bt>God had bound a promise with Abraham and his descendants saying, eventually the whole world would become their inheritance. God2 promised like that, because Abraham believed in Him, so/then God2 stamped/branded/categorised him, as a *righteous person who was in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. But God2 didn't promise like that, because Abraham was doing according to/obeying His Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan janji bagitu, tagal Abraham parcaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan janji bagitu, tagal Abraham parcaya sang Dia, ju babae kambali deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the promise that he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the promise that he would be the heir of the world was to Abraham, and his [offspring/children], not through the Law, but through the righteousness of faith.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:4-6, 22:17-18, Galatia 3:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Te kalo orang yang cuma bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran bisa tarima ame pusaka yang Tuhan janji tu, dia pung arti bilang, parcaya sang Tuhan tu, parcuma sa. Deng Tuhan pung janji tu, ju sonde ada pung guna.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if a person who only follows God2's Law can receive that inheritance which God promised, that means that, the aforementioned believing/belief in God2, is totally pointless/ineffectual. And that aforementioned promise of God2's, also doesn't have any use/worth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if they who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if they who are of the Law be heirs, faith is made [void/no good], and the promise made worthless.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 3:18</note><v n="15" />Di mana Tuhan pung Atoran ada, na, di situ ju orang langgar itu Atoran. Deng kalo orang langgar Dia pung Atoran, na, Tuhan mara, ais Dia hukum sang dong. Deng kalo Tuhan pung Atoran sonde ada, na, tantu sonde ada orang yang langgar itu Atoran.<bt>Wherever God2's Law exists, na, there also people violate that Law. And if people violate His Law, na, God2 gets angry, and then He punishes them. And if God2's Law doesn't exist, na, then there is certainly no person who can violate that Law. [EXEG: This is about a general state of affairs, so we don't want it read as “there are some who violate (and by implication: some who don't)” but as “(all) people (in general) violate”. SSA, CR]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** itu Atoran at end ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** itu Atoran at end ; (2009) revised to avoid ambiguity, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the Law produces wrath,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the Law produces wrath, for where there is no law, there is no [disobeying of the Law / transgression / sin].</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di mana Tuhan pung Atoran ada,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Di mana Tuhan pung Atoran ada, na, di situ kotong ju katumu orang yang langgar itu Atoran.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Andia ko kotong musti parcaya sang Dia. Itu lebe pantíng dari samua. Te Tuhan suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae deng pardeo sang orang yang parcaya sang Dia. Deng kalo kotong parcaya sang Dia sama ke Abraham, tantu kotong mau tarima apa yang Dia janji, biar kotong orang Yahudi yang bekin iko Dia pung Atoran, ko sonde. Jadi kotong samua yang parcaya tu, sama ke Abraham pung turunan.<bt>That's why you-pl must believe in Him. That is more important than everything. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 likes to show His good liver (=grace) freely/without.cost to people who believe in Him. And if we-inc believe in Him like Abraham [did], surely we will receive that which He promised, whether we are Yahudi people who follow His Law/Regulations, or not. So (consequently), all of us who believe, are like Abraham's descendants.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="monos: we assume talks of Jews"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">monos: we assume talks of Jews with two options: be of the Law only, or also believe. It does not contrast two groups, one who is of the Law and rejects faith, and one who accepts both. If it were the latter, if would contradict verse 14. LITERALLY: Therefore it is of faith, that it might be by grace, so that the promise might be certain to all the offspring, not the one who is of the Law only, but also of the faith of Abraham, who is the father of us all.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 3:7</note><v n="17" />Dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, Dia su janji sang Abraham bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta bekin ko lu jadi banya bangsa pung nene-moyang.&gt;&gt; Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan Allah. Ais lama-lama Tuhan Allah bekin jadi Dia pung janji. Dia ju yang kasi idop kambali orang mati. Dia cuma tenga omong sa, ko barang yang sonde ada, jadi memang.<bt>In God2's Clean/Holy Writings, He promised Abraham saying, &lt;&lt;I will do/arrange.things so that you-sg become the ancestor of many ethnic groups.&gt;&gt; Abraham believed God1. And so eventually God made His promise happen/fulfilled His promise. He also was the one who made dead people live again. He only needs to just speak, so that things which don't exist, happen/come into being straight away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "I have made you a father of many nations." Before him whom he believed, God, who makes the dead live, and calls those things which are not as though they were.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Abraham parcaya sang Tuhan, deng tunggu-tunggu sang Dia, biar dia sandiri balóm ada ana. Andia ko Tuhan bekin sang dia jadi &lt;&lt;banya bangsa pung nene-moyang.&gt;&gt; Itu sama ke yang ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Turunan bam-banya nanti datang dari lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Abraham believed (in) God, and waited expectantly for Him, even though he himself did not yet have a child. That's why God2 made him become &lt;&lt;many ethnic groups' ancestor.&gt;&gt; That is the same as what is written in the Holy/Clean Writings saying, &lt;&lt;Many descendants will later come from you-sg.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: / NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK to make sure the sense of “hoping beyond hope/against hope” comes through, or as Morris says, “he believed when there was nothing from this world's point of view to justify his faith or his hope.” It's implicit in this rendering and checks out in KM. If it needs to be explicit, consider ALT: Biar Abraham sandiri balóm ada ana, ma dia parcaya sang Tuhan, deng tunggu-tunggu sang Dia, Padahal dia pung parcaya tu, sonde maso akal. “Even though Abraham himself did not yet have offspring, nevertheless he believed God2, and kept waiting/hoping in Him. Whereas in fact, his belief didn't make sense.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added, ALT provided"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added, ALT provided</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who against hope believed in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who against hope believed in hope, that he might become the father of many nations, according to that which was spoken, "So shall your offspring be."</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 15:5</note><v n="19" />Abraham parcaya kuat sang Tuhan, biar dia tau dia pung badan su tua kakaluk, su umur saratus taon. Deng Sara pung tampa ana karíng, deng dia ju su tua ganggók.<bt>Abraham believed strongly in God2, even though he knew his body was old and wrinkled, already one hundred years. And Sara's child place was dry (=she was barren), and she also was already old and feeble. [NOTE for daughter translations: she was always barren, so avoid impression that she simply became barren due to old age. "deng amper mati" not retained, because figure of speech already carried by current rendering. In KM means he is within days or hours of dying (which he is not, in this verse), see NLT. CHECK collocations: e.g. Gk “womb is dead”; KM “womb is dry”; BI “womb is closed”; Dhao “womb is closed tight”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampa ana karíng = barren ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">tampa ana karíng = barren ; abraham su baboo tana = amper mati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was not weak in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was not weak in faith, he did not consider his own body, now [like] dead, because he was about a hundred years old, nor even the deadness of Sarah's womb.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 17:17</note><v n="20" />Ma Abraham pung parcaya sonde tagoyang, ko, pikir Tuhan sonde bisa bekin iko Dia pung janji. Dia pung parcaya sang Tuhan batamba kuat waktu dia angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama.<bt>But Abraham's faith was not shaken, or, think that God2 could not do according to His promise. His faith/belief in God2 continued to increase when/while he lifted up high (=*glorified) God2's name. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia parcaya kuat sang Tuhan tarús,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dia parcaya kuat sang Tuhan tarús, ju angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did not stagger at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did not stagger at God's promise through unbelief, but was strong in faith, giving glory to God.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Abraham yakin batúl-batúl bilang, apa yang Tuhan su janji, Dia mampu bekin iko.<bt>Abraham was really certain that, what God2 had promised, He was capable of doing it. [NOTE to daughter translations: /yakin/ - /parcaya/ or /tau/; /mampu/ - /bisa/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He was fully persuaded that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He was fully persuaded that what he had promised he was also able to do.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Andia ko Tuhan Allah cap sang Abraham, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia.<bt>That's why God1 stamped/marked Abraham, a straight livered (=righteous) person who was in a reciprocally good.relationship with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: if the antecedent of ‘therefore’ is not clear to UNS's, add at beginning /Tagal dia pung parcaya tu, andia ko .../]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And therefore it was credited"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And therefore it was credited to him as righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang, Tuhan sonde itong bagitu kasi Abraham sandiri sa,<bt>But God2's Holy/Clean Writings says, God2 doesn't/didn't count like just for Abraham, [NOTE to daughter translations: /itong/ works in KM for moral reckoning, but CHECK that it's equivalent in the vernacular also has that secondary use.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now it was not recorded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now it was not recorded for his sake alone that it was credited to him,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />ma kasi kotong ju! Te kalo kotong parcaya sang Dia, Dia ju cap kotong orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia. Tuhan tu, yang kasi idop kambali sang kotong pung Bos Yesus dari Dia pung mati.<bt>but for us-inc also! Cuz/for (elaboration) if we-inc believe in Him, He also stamps/marks us straight livered (=righteous) persons who are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. That God2, is the one who brought back to life our-inc Bos Yesus from His death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but for us also, to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but for us also, to whom it shall be credited, if we believe in the one who raised Jesus our Lord from the dead.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Yesus mati, tagal kotong pung bekin sala. Ais ju Dia idop kambali ko buka jalan ko biar kotong bisa babae kambali deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>Yesus died, because of our-inc doing wrong/sin. And then He lived again to open the way/path for us-inc to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who was delivered [to die]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who was delivered [to die] for our [offences/ wrongdoings/ sins], and was raised again for our justification.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah asal dong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus<bt>People can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God1 as long as they believe in Yesus Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi, tagal kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, andia ko Dia cap sang kotong orang hati lurus. Ais kotong pung hati su jadi barisi kasi sang Tuhan, tagal kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang, ada buka jalan ko kotong bisa badame.<bt>So (consequently), because we-inc believe in God1, that's why we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. Then our livers/hearts have become clean toward God2, because our Boss, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent, has opened the path/way so that we could be in a reciprocally peaceful/restored relationship like that. [NOTE to daughter translations: If needed, flesh out /badame/ to /badame deng Tuhan Allah/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireeneen ekhomen pros ton theon: the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">eireeneen ekhomen pros ton theon: the idea of a pono relationship, everything just as it should be. Like Hebrew shalom. LITERALLY: Therefore since we are justified by faith, we have peace [with/toward] God through our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, tagal kotong parcaya sang Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, tagal kotong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, andia ko kotong bisa babae deng Dia. Ais kotong pung hati su jadi barisi kasi sang Tuhan, tagal kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang, ada buka jalan ko kotong bisa babae bagitu.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong bagitu, tagal kotong parcaya sang Dia dolo. Andia ko kotong pung hati bisa jadi kuat. Deng kotong ju hati babunga, tagal botong tau bilang, nanti Tuhan mau angka kotong ko iko rasa Dia hebat.<bt>Kristus opened the way so that we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God1, so that He can show His good liver (=grace) to us, because we believed in Him first. That's why our-inc livers/hearts can be strong. And we also have flowering livers (=joy), because we know that, later God2 wants to lift us to participate in feeling/experiencing His greatness/incredibleness/glory. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: Gk genitive here famous for its complexity. See Fee &amp; Strauss 2007.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By whom [Christ] also we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By whom [Christ] also we have access by faith into this grace in which we stand, and rejoice in hope of the glory of God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus buka jalan ko kotong bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Kristus buka jalan ko kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah, ko Dia bisa kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Biar kotong dapa susa macam-macam, ma kotong hati babunga tarús. Te kotong tau bilang, kotong balajar dari susa, ko biar bisa batahan lebe kuat lai.<bt>Even though we-inc get all sorts of difficulties, nevertheless our-inc liver flowers (=has joy/rejoices) continually. Cuz/for (elaboration) we know that, we learn from difficulty, so that we can endure/persevere even more strongly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And not only that, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And not only that, but we glory in troubles also, knowing that troubles produce patience,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar kotong dapa susa macam-macam, ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Biar kotong dapa susa macam-macam, ma kotong hati babunga tarús. Te kotong tau, bilang, susa bekin kotong bisa batahan lebe kuat lai.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Kalo kotong batahan dalam susa, itu bekin kotong sonde jato, deng kotong pung idop bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Kalo kotong idop lebe kuat bagitu, itu bekin kotong parcaya lebe kuat bilang, nanti Tuhan mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong.<bt>If we-inc endure in difficulty, that makes us not fall (morally), and our lives please God2. If we live more strongly (=moral strength &amp; strength of character) like that, it makes us believe more strongly that, later God2 will show his good liver (=grace) to us. [EXEG: Is “makes us not fall (morally)” an addition? No. The Gk word has sense of “being proved/approved by successfully coming through testing (LN, BAGD). Morris describes it as “being approved on the basis of a trial”, NEB says “proof that we have stood the test”.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if /idop lebe kuat/ doesn't translate meaningfully, try /kotong sonde jato, deng kotong pung idop bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Kalo kotong idop bagitu.../]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and patience, experience, and experience,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and patience, experience, and experience, hope,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Kalo kotong parcaya lebe kuat bagitu, kotong sonde malu. Te Tuhan su kasi kotong Dia pung Roh yang Barisi, ko kotong bisa tau dalam kotong pung hati bilang, Dia ada sayang bam-banya sang kotong.<bt>If we believe more strongly like that, we are not embarrased/ashamed. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 has given us His Holy Spirit, so that we can know in our livers/hearts that, He has lots and lots of love for us. [EXEG: kataischunei: put to shame, but SSA "has more the sense of ‘be disappointed’ than ‘be put to shame’ (BAGD, p. 410.3a), but specifically it means to be humiliated because the source of one’s faith has been shown to be inadequate"] [NOTE to daughter translations: if “know in our hearts” is heavy as a Hebraism, just use “know well/understand deeply”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and hope does not disappoint"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and hope does not disappoint us, because God has poured out his love into our hearts by the Holy Spirit, who is given to us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dia kasi tunju Dia pung sayang bagini: waktu kotong masi tar mampu bekin diri babae deng Tuhan, tau-tau te Dia kirim Kristus ko mati kasi sang kotong yang idop sonde toe sang Tuhan. Tuhan pili waktu yang pas bagitu.<bt>When we-inc still were not capable of making ourselves in right.relationship with God [EXEG: SSA, high level], contrary-to-expectation He sent Kristus to die for us who lived without caring.about/ paying attention.to God2. God2 chose the appropriate time like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aseboon: ungodly LITERALLY: For when we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">aseboon: ungodly LITERALLY: For when we were still without strength, at the right time Christ died for the ungodly.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu kotong masi tar mampu bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Waktu kotong masi tar mampu bekin diri babae deng Tuhan, tau-tau te Kristus mati kasi sang kotong yang idop sonde toe sang Tuhan. Tuhan pili waktu yang pas bagitu.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Pikir bae-bae dolo! Te jarang ada orang yang sadia mati ganti dia pung tamán yang hati lurus. Mungkin ada orang saparu yang sadia mati ko tolong orang yang hati bae.<bt>Think carefully! Cuz/for (elaboration) there is rarely a person who is prepared to die in place of his straight livered (=righteous) friend/companion. Maybe there are some people who are prepared to die to help people/person who has a good liver/heart. [EXEG: Note the progression is downward to show the exceptional nature of God's love. 7a “righteous person”, 7b “good person”, 8 “still full-blown sinners”. Ex.Summ. #1; Morris.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jarang ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">jarang ***</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2013-09-25 00:50:57Z">Ex.Summ. #1; Morris.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because a person will hardly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because a person will hardly die for a righteous person. But maybe some would even dare to die for a good person.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te jarang ada orang yang sadia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te jarang ada orang yang sadia mati kasi sang orang hati lurus.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung sayang bam-banya kasi sang kotong. Tagal waktu kotong masi bekin sala, Kristus mati kasi sang kotong.<bt>But God1 has shown His abundant love for us. Because, when we-inc were still doing wrong/sin, Kristus died for us. [EXEG: phrased deliberately in this well-known verse to reflect ambiguities of Gk and leave open legitimate debates in theological circles re: substitutionary atonement. As with baptism, it is not the role of the translation to deliberately bias the debate--regardless of our personal views.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But God has shown how"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But God has shown how much he loves us, in that, while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tuhan Allah cap sang kotong orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia, tagal Kristus kasi tumpa Dia pung dara ko mati kasi sang kotong. Padahal kalo orang bekin sala, Tuhan mara. Ma tagal apa yang Kristus bekin tu, kotong yang bekin sala sonde kaná hukum lai.<bt>God1 stamped/marked us as straight livered (=righteous) people who are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, because Kristus spilled His blood to die for us. However/Whereas.in.actual.fact, if a person does wrong/sins, God gets angry. But because of that aforemention deed of Kristus', we who do wrong do not get punished anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since we are now justified"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since we are now justified by his blood, we will much more be saved from wrath through him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dolu kotong bamusu deng Tuhan. Ma Tuhan pung Ana sandiri mati ko bekin dingin Tuhan pung hati, ko biar kotong bisa badame deng Tuhan. Jadi sakarang kotong sonde bamusu lai, ma su babae kambali. Lebe-lebe lai, tagal Kristus su idop kambali, nanti di hari kiamat Dia ju kasi salamat sang kotong ko jang kaná Tuhan Allah pung hukuman lai.<bt>Previously we were in an enemy relationship with God2. But God's own Child died to cool God2's liver (idiom: remove reason for anger and damaged relationship) so that we can be restored/peaceful relationship with God2. So (consequently) now we-inc are not in an enemy relationship anymore, but restored to a right relationship. Even more so, because Kristus came back to life, later at the end of the world He will also save/deliver us to not get/experience God's punishment anymore. [EXEG: NLT, SSA, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if, when we were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if, when we were enemies, we were reconciled to God by the death of his Son, much more, being reconciled, we will be saved by his life.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, kotong bamusu deng Tuhan. Ma,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dolu, kotong bamusu deng Tuhan. Ma, Tuhan pung Ana sandiri mati ko bekin dame sang kotong deng Tuhan. Jadi, sakarang, kotong sonde bamusu lai, ma su babae kambali. Lebe-lebe lai, Kristus mau kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala, tagal Dia pung idop kambali.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Bukan bagitu sa! Kotong pung hati bisa babunga bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan tu, hebat talalu!&gt;&gt; tagal kotong ta'ika deng Dia. Kotong bisa jadi Dia pung orang, tagal kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus su mati kasi sang kotong, ko bekin kotong badame deng Tuhan.<bt>Not just that! Our-inc hearts can flower (=rejoice) saying, &lt;&lt;God2, is exceedingly amazing/incredible!&gt;&gt; because we-inc are bound with Him. We can become His people, because our Boss, Yesus Kristus, has died for us, to make us in a peace.relationship with God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katallagee: reconciliation, be one of his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">katallagee: reconciliation, be one of his guys LITERALLY: And not only that, but we also rejoice/boast in God through our Lord Jesus Christ, by whom we have now received the atonement.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong babanding Adam deng Kristus, ada dia pung sama, deng ada dia pung beda<bt>If/When we-inc compare Adam and Kristus, there are similarities, and there are differences</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi dari dolu-kala, manusia partama, andia ba'i Adam, yang mulai bekin sala. Andia ko Tuhan Allah sonde kasi biar dia idop tarús. Ais mulai itu waktu, samua orang di ini dunya ju iko bekin sala sama ke dia. Deng tagal dong bekin sala sama ke dia, dong samua ju musti mati sama ke dia.<bt>So (consequently), from long ago, the first human, that is forefather Adam, was the one who started to do wrong/sin. That's why God1 didn't allow him to keep on living. So then starting from that time, all people in this world also follow doing wrong, the same as him. And because they do wrong the same as him, they all also must die the same as him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babanding ***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">babanding ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because sin came into the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because sin came into the world by one man [Adam], and death by sin, and so death passed to all men, because all have sinned. dià tóuto: therefore. It's not clear if it refers to Verses 1-11, or just to Verse 11, or to everything from 1:17 up to 5:11<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>hoósper: Everybody since Adam has made the same kind of bad choice Adam made, back at the beginning. They all ended up sinning by just the same process as Adam ended up sinning hoútoos: in this way, as a result<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>diéelthen: spread throughout the human race -- not genetically, just because we are human and the first real human somehow screwed up our genes, or let loose some kind of moral virus, but because practically speaking, all the rest of us have fallen into the same trap as Adam, of not wanting to do things God's way</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:6</note><v n="13" />Dolu-dolu, waktu Tuhan Allah balóm kasi turun Dia pung Atoran dong, orang ada bekin sala di anteru dunya. Ma tagal balóm ada Atoran, sonde ada yang itong orang pung sala-sala dong.<bt>Long ago, when God1 had not yet handed down His Laws, people did wrongs throughout the entire world. But because there was not yet (the) Law, there was no one who counts/keeps track of people's wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For until the Law, sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For until the Law, sin was in the world. But sin is not kept account of when there is no Law. ellogéitai: it is not the practice to keep account; a bookkeeping term. God is the one who keeps track of such things, if we need to provide a subject<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Dari ba'i Adam sampe ba'i Musa tarima Tuhan pung Atoran, samua orang pasti mati. Biar dong sonde langgar Tuhan pung parenta yang Dia kasi sang Adam, ma dong masi bekin sala macam-macam yang laen. Andia ko dong musti mati, sama ke Adam.<bt>From Gf/Ff Adam until Gf/Ff Musa received God2's Law, all people surely died. Even if they didn't violate God2's commands which He gave to Adam, nevertheless they still did all sorts of other wrongs. That's why they must die, the same as Adam.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Kalo kotong banding ba'i Adam deng Tuhan Yesus, ada dia pung sama, deng ada dia pung beda. Te Adam ju sama ke satu gambar yang kasi tunju Yesus pung model, yang nanti muncul datang.<bt>So then! If we-inc compare Gf/Ff Adam with the Lord Yesus, there are similarities, and there are differences. Cuz/for (elaboration) Adam was also like a picture which showed Yesus's model/form/type, which would appear later on.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But death reigned from Adam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But death reigned from Adam to Moses, even over those who did not sin like Adam by disobeying God's command, who is a picture of the one who is to come. allà: in contrast what you might expect from a case where no records were kept of wrongdoing, everybody died anyway<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>ebasíleusen: death ruled; there was no way to escape it</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma Adam pung bekin sala, sonde sama ke Yesus pung bekin bae kasi kotong. Te orang yang satu, andia Adam, ada langgar Tuhan pung parenta. Andia ko samua orang musti mati. Ma Orang yang satu lai, andia Yesus Kristus, ada bekin bae macam-macam kasi kotong, deng sonde tunggu-tunggu orang balas Dia pung bae. Apa yang satu Orang bekin tu, cukup kasi samua orang, te Tuhan suka bekin yang bae kasi kotong.<bt>But Adam's wrong deed/s, were not the same as Yesus's good deeds for/toward us-inc. Cuz/for (elaboration) the one person, that is Adam, was violating God's command. That's why all people must die. But the other Person, that is Yesus Kristus, did all sorts of good deeds for us, and didn't keep waiting for people to reciprocate His goodness. That one Person's deeds, were sufficient for all people, cuz/for (elaboration) God2 likes to do deeds which are good toward/for us-inc. [NOTE to daughter translations: if 1st sentence “not the same as” doesn't fly in your RL, try “different from”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the offense is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the offense is not the same as the free gift. For if by the offense of one, many have died, much more the grace of God, and the gift by grace, which is by one man, Jesus Christ, has been more than enough for many. paráptooma: the result of getting out of line<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>chárisma: the result of God treating us graciously dooreà: for free, no charge, not asking for anything in return<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>eperisseusen: abound, have more than enough for, sufficient</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Yang Tuhan Allah ada kasi sang kotong tu, beda deng itu sala yang satu orang, Adam, ada bekin. Waktu dia bekin sala, Tuhan Allah putus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu sala. Jadi lu musti kaná hukum!&gt;&gt; Ma biar orang su bekin sala satu mal'unuk pung, Tuhan Allah, yang pareksa samua orang pung idop, masi mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae, deng putus bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta cap lu sonde sala. Jadi sakarang lu su bebas deng sonde kaná lu pung hukuman lai. Mari ko babae kambali deng Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Those aforementioned things which God1 gives to us, are different than that sin which the one person, Adam, did. When he did wrong, God2 decided/handed down (legal) decision saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg are wrong/guilty. So you must be punished!&gt;&gt; But even though people had already done a heap/pile of wrongs, God1, who examines all people's lives, still wants to show His good liver/heart, and decide saying, &lt;&lt;I stamp/mark/categorise you-sg as not wrong/guilty/you are innocent. So (consequently), now you are free and do not get/experience your punishment anymore. Come [+invite] be in a reciprocally good relationship again with Me!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And there is a difference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And there is a difference between God's gift and the sin of one person. After the one sin came the judgment of 'Guilty'. But after so many sins comes the undeserved judgment of 'Not Guilty'.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lu su bebas."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">lu su bebas.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Jadi satu orang, Adam, ada bekin sala, deng langgar Tuhan pung parenta. Andia ko, sakarang, samua musti mati. Ma satu Orang lai, andia Yesus Kristus, ada bekin yang bae. Tagal Dia pung bekin bae tu, andia ko kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan. Itu sama ke satu barang yang Dia parsén kasi kotong. Dia mau kasi kotong idop batúl, sama ke kotong jadi Raja pung tamán dong.<bt>So (consequently), one person, Adam, did wrong deed/s, and violated God's command. That's why, now, all must die. But one other Person, who was Yesus Kristus, did good. Because of those good deed/s of His, that's why we can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. That is the same a thing which he gives.freely to us. He wants to give us true life, as if we are the Raja's friends. [NOTE: don't force Gk. word play on “rule/reign”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV misses it on last clause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV misses it on last clause</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if by one man's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if by one man's offense, death ruled by one [Adam], much more they who receive abundance of grace and of the gift of righteousness, shall reign in life by one, Jesus Christ. paraptoómati: not the usual word for doing wrong, but for breaking the rules or getting out of line<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Jadi satu orang pung bekin sala, buka jalan ko samua orang musti kaná usir dari Tuhan pung muka. Deng satu Orang lai pung bekin batúl, yang buka jalan ko samua orang bisa babae kambali deng Tuhan, ko idop batúl deng Dia.<bt>So (consequently), one person wrong deed/s, opened the way/path so that all people had to be evicted from God2's face/presence. And yet another Person's /right.correct deed/s, are what opened the way/path so that all people could be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, in order to have true life with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, as the sin of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, as the sin of one condemned all people, in the same way, the one righteous act sets all people free and gives them life. ára óun: this wraps up the line of thought Paul started in Verse 12<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Beta pung maksud bagini: Adam tu, satu orang yang sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan, ais langgar Dia pung parenta. Deng banya orang ju iko bekin sala, sama ke dia. Ais Yesus tu, satu Orang yang dengar-dengar sang Tuhan, ais bekin iko Dia pung mau. Dia yang buka jalan ko banya orang bisa babae kambali deng Tuhan.<bt>My meaning is like this: That Adam, was a person who did not want to listen to/obey God, so [he] violated God's command. And many people have also followed doing wrong, the same as him. So/Then, that Yesus, was a Person who continually listened to/obeyed God2, and so did according to His will. He is the one who opened the path/way so that many people can be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2. [EXEG: 15-19 nutshell: The gist I get here is that the consequence of one man, Adam’s, sin brought death to us all. But the gift that Christ gave us is more than the neutralization of the death penalty. It is a free gift of an abundant life for all. CR.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as by one person's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as by one person's disobedience, many have been made sinners, so by the obedience of one, many will be made righteous. gàr: further explanation<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>hoósper ... hoútos: just as one thing happened ... in a similar way another thing happened. See note in vs.12 katestátheesan: were put in a position, were made to be something that they weren't before (Acts 7:27 "who made you the ruler and judge?")<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Tuhan Allah kasi turun Dia pung Atoran sang ba'i Musa, ko samua orang dapa tau parsís, mana yang sala. Ma di mana sa orang pung sala batamba banya, di situ ju Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae lebe banya.<bt>God1 handed down His Law to gf Musa, so that all people could know exactly, what [things] were wrong [implied by construction--and what was right]. But wherever people's wrongs increased, there also God showed His good liver even more. [EXEG: “sin increased” JB goes in the direction of volume “it was to multiply the opportunities for falling”, but NLT, Morris, CEV, LB, saying the law magnified sin, making it much more obvious for what it is. If a phrasing allows both readings, fine. Otherwise err on the latter interpretation. NOTE that both the Kupang and TB rendering are similarly vague on this point.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Try and keep the lexical parallel with where x increased, y increased. If the /di mana ... di situ/ construction is difficult for your RL, try ALT /Ma biar orang pung bekin sala tamba jalás, ju Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae lebe banya di situ./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded, ALT given"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note expanded, ALT given</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Law was introduced that the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Law was introduced that the wrongdoing might be emphasized. But where sin increased, grace increased more. pareiséelthen: entered in as a factor<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah kasi turun Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan Allah kasi turun Dia pung Atoran, ko samua orang dapa tau parsís, mana yang sala. Ma di mana sa orang ada bekin sala batamba-batamba, di situ ju Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae batamba lebe banya.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Dolu, jahat di orang pung hati ada pung kuasa ko ator sang dong, sampe dong bekin sala yang bawa hukuman mati. Ma sakarang, hal bae yang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus bekin tu, Tuhan Allah pake ko kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong. Deng itu hal bae ada pung kuasa ko ator sang kotong, ais kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan, ju idop batúl deng Dia tarús-tarús.<bt>Previously, evil that is/was in a person's liver had power/authority to arrange/control them, to the point that they did wrong/sin which carried/brought the penalty of death (indirect causality). But now, those good thing/s which our Boss, Yesus Kristus has done, God1 uses to show His good liver (grace) to us. And those good thing/s have power to arrange/ control us, so we can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, and have true life with Him forever. [NOTE: “evil in their livers” also sets the stage for ch.7]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** extensive</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That as sin rules by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That as sin rules by death, even so might grace rule by righteousness, [for/leading us to] eternal life by Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, sala-sala yang orang bekin tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dolu, sala-sala yang orang bekin tu, ada pung kuasa ko ator sang dong, deng bekin dong jadi mati. Ma sakarang, hal bae yang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus bekin tu, Tuhan Allah pake ko kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong. Deng itu hal bae ada pung kuasa ko ator sang kotong, ais kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan, ju idop batúl deng Dia tarús-tarús.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti kasi tenga kotong pung sala, ko idop iko Tuhan pung mau<bt>We-inc must leave behind our wrongs, to live according to God2's will</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi sakarang mau bilang apa? Bosong mangkali ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan su lupa buang botong pung sala, tagal Dia pung hati bae. Andia ko ada lebe bae botong bekin sala tarús, ko biar nanti Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae lebe-lebe sang kotong.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), now what should [we/you] say? You-pl are probably thinking saying, &lt;&lt;God2 has completely forgotten our wrongs, because of his goodness/grace/kindness/generosity. That's why is would be better for us-exc. to keep doing wrongs/sin, so that later God2 will show His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity even more to us.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Biar botong bekin sala tarús, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">&lt;&lt;Biar botong bekin sala tarús, ko nanti Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae lebe-lebe sang kotong.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What will we say then?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What will we say then? We will continue in sin, that [grace/favor] may increase?</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Sonde mungkin! Sonde pantas kalo kotong bekin sala tarús, te kotong su putus bilang, kotong su bale balakang kasi tenga kotong pung sala-sala dong. Tagal kotong su sonde ta'ika deng jahat lai, itu sama ke kotong su mati na! Te orang yang su mati sonde bisa bekin sala lai, to? Kalo kotong su mati bagitu, na, karmana ko kotong bisa idop bekin sala lai? Sonde bisa, to?<bt>Impossible/no way! It is not appropriate for us to keep doing wrong, cuz/for (elaboration) we-inc have decided that, we already have turned our backs leaving behind our wrongs. Because we are no longer bound/linked with/by evil, that's the same as if we've died [+emphatic]! Cuz/for (elaboration) people who already dead can't do wrongs anymore, right? If we have already died like that, na, how is it that we-inc can live doing wrong again? Can't be done, right? [NOTE: explicating ‘death’ required from UNS responses (in Belu).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Certainly not! How shall we,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Certainly not! How shall we, who are dead to sin, live any longer in it?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde mungkin! Te kotong su putus,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Sonde mungkin! Te kotong su putus, bilang, kotong su bale balakang kasi tenga kotong pung sala-sala dong. Itu sama ke kotong su mati na! Te orang yang su mati sonde bisa bekin sala lai, to? Kalo kotong su mati, na, karmana ko kotong bisa idop bekin jahat lai? Sonde bisa, to?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Mangkali bosong sonde mangarti bilang, waktu kotong dapa sarani, itu jadi tanda bilang, kotong su kasi tenga idop yang lama ko jadi orang baru, andia, yang ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus. Itu sama ke kotong su mati sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>Perhaps you don't understand that, when we-inc were *baptised, it was a sign that we have left behind/abandoned our old/former life to become a new person, that is, one who is bound/linked to Yesus Kristus. That is like/as if we have died together with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that “new person” doesn't actually mean “guest who has just arrived”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do you not know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do you not know that as many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mangkali bosong sonde mangarti, bilang, waktu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Mangkali bosong sonde mangarti, bilang, waktu kotong dapa sarani ko jadi tanda, bilang, kotong jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang, itu sama ke kotong mati sama-sama deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu Kristus mati, dong kubur sang Dia. Ais waktu kotong dapa sarani, itu sama ke kotong ju mati kasi tenga idop yang lama, ais dong kubur sang kotong. Naa, Allah Bapa pake Dia pung kuasa yang hebat, ko kasi idop kambali sang Kristus dari Dia pung mati. Allah Bapa ju suka kotong tarima Dia pung kuasa tu, ko idop kambali jadi orang baru.<bt>When Kristus died, they buried Him. And when we were baptized, that was like we also died leaving behind the old life, and then they (non-referential) buried us. Naa [+shift] Father God used His incredible power to bring Kristus back to life from His death. Father God also wants us to receive that power of His, to come back to life as a new person. [EXEG: Gk glory = power here, see NLT, Harrison, Calvin, etc.] [NOTE: This is a "safe" compromise approach to vs. 3-4 that focuses on the symbolism and result of baptism, avoiding the method quagmire that has no consensus among commentators and is bound to generate unhelpful disputes among readers.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore we are buried with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore we are buried with him by baptism into death. That just as Christ was raised up from the dead by the glory of the Father, even so we also should walk in newness of life.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kristus mati, ais dong (kasi) kubur"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Kristus mati, ais dong (kasi) kubur sang Dia. Ju waktu kotong dapa sarani, itu sama ke kotong ju mati, ais dong kasi kubur sang kotong. Naa, Allah Bapa pake Dia pung kuasa yang hebat, ko kasi idop kambali sang Kristus dari Dia pung mati. Allah Bapa ju suka kotong pake Dia pung kuasa tu, ko idop baru.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 2:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te itu sama ke kotong mati sama-sama deng Yesus. Jadi kotong yang ta'ika deng Dia, tantu kotong ju nanti idop kambali dari kotong pung mati, sama ke Dia su idop kambali.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) that is like we-inc died together with Yesus. So (consequently), we who are bound to Him, surely we-inc also later will live again from our deaths, just like He also came back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei: could be translated &quot;if&quot;, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">ei: could be translated "if", but here it's more like "since this is the way it is" sýmphytoi: grown together, come into a close relationship<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: For if we have been united with him in his death, we will certainly also be united with him in his resurrection.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dolu kotong jadi orang yang bekin sala macam-macam. Ma kotong pung idop lama tu, su ancor abis, sama ke dong su paku mati sang kotong di kayu palang sama-sama deng Kristus. Sakarang jahat di kotong pung hati sonde ada pung kuasa ko ator sang kotong lai. Sakarang kotong sonde ta'ika ko bekin sala lai. Te kotong su sonde sama ke budak yang sonde ada pung hak pili mau bekin apa.<bt>Formerly we were people who did all sorts of wrongs. But our former lives, has already been completely destroyed, the same as if they (non-referential) had nailed killing us on the cross together with Kristus. Now evil in our livers doesn't have any power/authority to mangage/control us anymore. Now we-inc aren't bound to do wrong anymore. Cuz/for (elaboration) we are no longer like a slave who doesn't have the right to choose what [s/he] wants to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that our old"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that our old self was crucified with him, so that the [body of sin/power of the sinful self] might be made powerless, that we should no longer be slaves to sin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, kotong jadi orang yang bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dolu, kotong jadi orang yang bekin sala macam-macam. Ma itu orang dolu tu, su ancor abis, sama ke dong su paku mati sang dia di kayu palang sama-sama deng Kristus. Sakarang, kotong pung sala sonde ada pung kuasa lai. Sakarang, kotong sonde ta'ika ko bekin sala lai. Te kotong su sonde sama ke budak yang sonde ada pung hak pili mau bekin apa.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Kalo orang su mati, dia su bebas, to? Sonde ada satu ju yang bisa paksa sang dia ko bekin sala lai.<bt>If a person is already dead, he/she is already free, right? There is nothing that can force him/her to do wrong again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he that is dead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he that is dead is freed from sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Jadi, tagal itu sama ke kotong su mati sama-sama deng Kristus, na, kotong parcaya bilang, kotong ju nanti idop tarús deng Dia.<bt>So (consequently), because that is like we already died together with Kristus, na, we believe that we will also live continually with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now if we are dead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now if we are dead with Christ, we believe that we will also live with him.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, kotong parcaya, bilang, kalo itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, kotong parcaya, bilang, kalo itu sama ke kotong su mati sama-sama deng Kristus, na, kotong ju nanti idop tarús deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Kotong tau bilang, tagal Kristus su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, Dia sonde mati ulang lai. Te sonde ada satu apa lai yang ada pung kuasa ko bekin Dia mati.<bt>We know that, because Kristus has lived again from His death, He will not die again. Cuz/for (elaboration) there is nothing else/more which has the power to make Him die.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that since Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that since Christ was raised from the dead, he cannot die again. Death has no [control/power] over him.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dolu Dia mati satu kali, ko cabu buang sala pung kuasa. Ma sakarang Dia idop ko kasi tunju hormat sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Formerly He died one time, to strip away the power/authority of wrong/sin. But now He lives to show honor to God1. [EXEG: NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cabu buang = example of stripping"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">cabu buang = example of stripping away an official's rank/authority ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The death he died, he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The death he died, he died to sin once for all. But the life he lives, he lives to God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dolu, Dia mati satu kali, ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dolu, Dia mati satu kali, ko kasi kala sala pung kuasa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Bosong ju musti anggap diri bagitu. Tingka ke bosong su mati, andia ko sala sonde ada pung kuasa sang bosong lai. Jadi sakarang bosong musti idop ko kasi tunju hormat sang Tuhan, tagal bosong ada ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus.<bt>You-pl also must consider yourselves like that. It's as if you-pl are already dead, that's why wrong doesn't have power over you anymore. So (consequently) now you must live to show honor to God2, because you are bound together with Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the same way, count"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the same way, count yourselves dead to sin but alive to God in Christ Jesus. hoútoos: in the same way as happened with Christ<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong ju musti anggap diri sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bosong ju musti anggap diri sama ke apa yang su jadi deng Yesus Kristus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jang kasi biar ko jahat di lu pung hati ada kuasa ko bisa ator sang lu, ko lu cuma iko lu pung badan pung mau-mau ko bekin jahat dong. Te lu pung badan nanti mati.<bt>Don't allow evil in your liver to have power/authority to be able to manage/control you-sg, so that you-sg only follow your-sg body's desires to do evil things. Cuz/for (elaboration) your body will later die. [EXEG: “mortal body” Ex.Summ., CEV] [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: Jahat di lu pung hati ada pung kuasa. Jang kasi biar itu jahat bisa ator sang lu,...]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Do not let sin take"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Do not let sin take control of your [earthly/mortal] bodies, that you should obey it and its evil desires. thneetóoi: subject to death<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>soómati: body, but from the Jewish framework Paul writes in he's including the mind, not just biological urges -- "your natural self", "da way you stay", "how you feel"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang kasi biar ko sala bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jang kasi biar ko sala bisa kuasa sang lu, ko lu cuma iko lu pung badan pung mau-mau ko bekin jahat dong. Te lu nanti mati.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Deng jang sarakan lu pung diri ko bekin hal yang sonde batúl dong, te itu ju sala. Ma sarakan lu pung diri kasi pi Tuhan Allah sa, ko Dia yang ator sang lu. Tingka ke lu su mati, ais idop kambali. Jadi pake lu pung diri anteru-anteru ko bekin hal yang batúl dong, kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>And don't hand.over your-sg self to do things which are not right/correct, cuz/for (elaboration) that also is wrong. But just hand.over your self to God1, so that He manages/controls you-sg. It's as if you had already died, then come back to life. So use your entire-entire self to do things which are right/correct, for (the benefit of) God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nor surrender any part of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nor surrender any part of your bodies as instruments of unrighteousness for sin; but surrender yourselves to God, as those that are alive from the dead, and the parts of your bodies as instruments of righteousness for God. mélee: individual parts of the body. He's focusing on the different parts because he's really talking about our entire personality, body included<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Jang kasi biar ko sala bisa ator sang bosong, sama ke sala jadi bosong pung bos. Sakarang bosong sonde usa idop bekin iko Musa pung atoran lai ko jadi babae kambali deng Tuhan. Te bosong ada idop lurus, tagal Tuhan su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong. Jadi sakarang Dia pung hati bae tu, yang ator sang bosong.<bt>Don't allow for wrong/sin to manage/controls you-pl, as if wrong/sin had became your-pl boss. Now you-pl don't need to live following/obeying Musa's law anymore to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2. Cuz/for (elaboration) you-pl are living straightly (=righteously), because God2 has shown His good liver/heart to you-pl. So (consequently) now that good liver of His, is what controls/manages you. [EXEG: SSA, TB. Specify Moses' law, so we're not saying you don't have to follow God's law anymore.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Law to Moses law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Law to Moses law (plus note), and throughout ch.6 (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For sin shall not have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For sin shall not have [control/power] over you; for you are not under the law, but under grace. ou kyrieúsei: in the context the future tense has the force of an imperative<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>hypò: dominated by. "because you do not live by what the law tells you you must do, but by the goodness which God has shown you"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong jadi sama ke budak yang karjá iko Tuhan pung mau<bt>We are like a slave who works according to God2's will</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Jadi karmana? Bosong mangkali pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal kotong sonde usa idop bekin iko Musa pung atoran lai, ko jadi babae deng Dia, biar ko kotong bekin sala tarús sa. Te Tuhan masi mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae kasi kotong na!&gt;&gt; Bosong ada pikir bagitu, to? Beta kasi tau, é! Itu tu, sala!<bt>So (consequently) how is it? You-pl are probably thinking saying, &lt;&lt;Because we-inc we don't need to live following/ obeying Moses' law anymore, in order to be in a reciprocally good.relationship with Him, let's just continue to do wrong/sin. Cuz/for (elaboration) of course God1 still wants to show His good liver/heart to us!&gt;&gt; You are thinking like that, right? I'm telling [you], e! That [+emphatic] is wrong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Moses law, not God's Law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** Moses law, not God's Law (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then? Shall we sin,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then? Shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? Certainly not!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, karmana? Bosong pikir, bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, karmana? Bosong pikir, bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar kotong bekin sala tarús, tagal kotong sonde usa bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran dong, ko jadi babae kambali deng Tuhan. Deng Tuhan masi mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae kasi kotong.&gt;&gt; Bagitu, to? Beta kasi tau, é! Itu sala tu!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta ame conto dari bos deng budak. Kalo bosong sarakan bosong pung diri ko karjá kasi satu orang, na, bosong musti dengar sang dia, deng karjá iko dia pung mau. Te dia tu, bosong pung bos yang hak parenta sang bosong. Deng bosong tu, dia pung budak. Bagitu ju, bosong bisa pili mau iko yang mana. Te bosong bisa pili ko bekin sala, ais bosong jadi sala pung budak. Ma kalo bosong pili bagitu, bosong bekin diri tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah. Ko, bosong bisa pili ko bekin yang batúl, deng jadi budak yang bekin iko apa yang Tuhan suru sang bosong. Kalo bosong pili bagitu, na, bosong bisa jadi babae deng Dia!<bt>I'll take the example of a bos and a slave. If you hand.over your-pl selves to work for a person, na, you must listen to/obey him, and work according to his desires. Cuz/for (elaboration) he, is your-pl bos who has say-so/ordering rights over you. And you-pl, are his slave. In the same way also, you must choose which (among choices) you want to follow/obey. Cuz/for (elaboration) you can choose to do wrong, and.then you become wrong's/sin's slave. But if you choose like that, you make yourselves separated apart from God1. Or, you can choose to do that which is right/true/correct, and become a slave to do what God2 orders you. If you choose like that, na, you can be/become in a reciprocally good relationship with Him!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Don't you know that whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Don't you know that whoever you surrender yourself to, as servants to obey, you are his servants to obey, whether of sin that leads to death, or obedience that leads to righteousness? eétoi: a pick one or the other choice<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong musti mangarti ini hal: kalo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bosong musti mangarti ini hal: kalo bosong sarakan bosong pung diri pi satu orang, ko dia jadi bosong pung bos, bosong musti dengar sang dia, deng karjá iko dia pung mau. Te dia tu, bosong pung bos. Deng bosong tu, dia pung budak.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dolu bosong kasi biar ko sala yang ator sang bosong, ma sakarang bosong ada dengar bosong pung dalam hati, ko bekin iko apa yang orang sarani dong ajar sang bosong. Andia ko beta minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Formerly you allowed wrongs to be what controlled/managed you, but now, you are hearing/listening.to your inner hearts (=conscience), to do according to what the <span class="Italic">(sarani)</span> Christian people have taught you. That's why I give thanks to God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thank God that you were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thank God that you were servants of sin, but you have obeyed from the heart that form of teaching which was given to you. eis hòn paredótheete: you started to obey the kind of teaching that was passed on to you<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Te Tuhan su kasi lapás sang bosong dari sala pung kuasa, sampe sala sonde ator sang bosong lai. Jadi sakarang, hal yang batúl yang ator sang bosong.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 has freed you-pl from the power of wrong/sin, to.the point that wrong/sin does not manage/control you-pl anymore. So (consequently) now, right/correct things are what controls/manages you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You have been set free"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You have been set free from sin and have become servants to righteousness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Beta omong ni, pake conto hari-hari dari bos deng budak, ko bosong gampang mangarti beta pung maksud. Dolu bosong sarakan bosong pung diri jadi budak ko bekin sala, yang bawa bosong ko jadi kamomos, iko Musa pung Atoran. Ma sakarang bosong musti sarakan bosong pung diri jadi budak ko cuma idop bekin yang batúl sa, yang bawa bosong ko jadi barisi di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>I am speaking here, using an everyday example from a boss and slave, so that you can easily understand my meaning/intent. Formerly you-pl handed.over your selves to become slaves to do wrong, which brought you to become dirty/defiled according to Moses' Law. But now you must hand.over your selves to become slaves in order to only live doing just what is right/correct/true, which brings/leads you to be clean in God2's face (=view). [EXEG: NLT + HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarkos: &quot;make yoaself be da kine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">sarkos: "make yoaself be da kine peopo dat ..." may be another solution for the "body" metonymy. LITERALLY: I speak in human terms because of the weakness of your natural selves. Because just as you surrendered the parts of your bodies as servants for uncleanness that leads to sin after sin, so now surrender the parts of your bodies as servants to righteousness that leads to holiness.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>sarkòs: your human nature, your natural selves eis: the expected goal<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dolu waktu bosong cuma dengar deng bekin iko sala pung mau, bosong sonde usa dengar deng bekin iko yang batúl.<bt>Previously when you only heard/obeyed and did according to the ways/desires of sin/wrong, you didn't have to/not obligated to hear/obey and do what was right/correct/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when you were servants"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when you were servants of sin, you were free from righteousness.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Naa, beta mau tanya bagini: bosong dapa hasil apa yang bae dari bosong pung bekin-bekin tu? Sonde ada, to? Padahal hasil yang bosong dapa tu, bekin malu sang bosong sa. Tagal bosong pung bekin sala bagitu, dia pung ujung-ujung, Tuhan Allah bale balakang sang bosong, ais bosong tapisa buang dari Dia.<bt>Naa [+shift], I want to ask like this: what good results have you gotten from those (negatively valued) deeds of yours? There's nothing, right? In.actual.fact, those results which you got, just make you embarrased/ ashamed. Because of your doing wrong like that, the end result, [is that] God1 turns his back on you, with the result that you are separated off from God. [EXEG: Gk ‘death’ explicated from OV to better match KT.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Make sure it is clear that /bosong pung bekin-bekin/ in KM is strongly s.t. that is socially or morally wrong. MTT's only partly proficient in KM may not pick this up.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dia pung ujung-ujung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">dia pung ujung-ujung</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What [fruit/good] did you have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What [fruit/good] did you have then from the things you are ashamed of now? Because the end of those things is death.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma sakarang Tuhan su kasi lapás sang bosong dari bos yang lama, jadi bosong sonde usa bekin sala lai. Sakarang bosong musti jadi Tuhan pung orang karjá. Dia pung ujung-ujung, nanti bosong jadi barisi kasi sang Dia, deng dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>But now God2 has freed you from your old boss, so you don't need to do wrong anymore. Now you must become God2's working people (=workers). The end result, [is that] later you will be clean for (the benefit of) Him, and be able to have true life which doesn't ever end.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now you have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now you have been made free from sin, and have become servants of God, you have your fruit that leads to holiness, and the end eternal life.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Te waktu kotong bekin sala, dia pung upa, andia Tuhan bale balakang sang kotong ko kotong tapisa buang dari Dia sonde putus-putus. Kotong mati su! Ma Tuhan su sadia satu jalan kaluar kasi kotong. Te Dia mau kasi parsén sang kotong idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Deng kotong dapa itu idop, kalo kotong maso jadi kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung orang.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) when we do/did wrong, the reward/wages, was that God2 turns his back on us so that we are eternally cseparated off from Him. We're dead [+idiomatic, emphatic]! But God2 has prepared a way out for us. Cuz/for (elaboration) He wants to give.a. free.gift to us of true life which doesn't ever end. And we receive that life, if/when we enter and become our Bos Yesus Kristus' person. [EXEG: Gk ‘death’ explicated from OV to better match KT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi parsén sang = parsén kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">kasi parsén sang = parsén kasi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the wages of sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the wages of sin is death. But the gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te waktu bosong bekin sala, dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te waktu bosong bekin sala, dia pung upa, andia Tuhan bale balakang sang bosong. Ma Tuhan su sadia satu jalan kaluar kasi bosong. Te Dia mau kasi parsén sang bosong idop yang batúl yang sonde putus-putus. Deng bosong dapa itu idop, kalo bosong maso jadi kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung orang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">kalo orang su mati, atoran hukum sonde ada pung hak lai sang dia<bt>If a person has died, legal regulations don't have rights over him anymore [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: /Atoran hukum sonde kaná deng orang yang su mati/]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara dong! Sakarang beta omong kasi bosong yang mangarti atoran hukum dong. Bagini: kalo bosong masi idop, atoran hukum ada hak ko ator sang bosong. Ma kalo bosong su mati, atoran hukum sonde ada pung hak ko ator sang bosong lai.<bt>Siblings! Now I am speaking to you-pl who understand Moses' legal regulations. It's like this: if you-pl are still alive, legal regulations have the right to control/manage you. But if you are already dead, legal regulations don't have the right to control you anymore. [NOTE to daughter translations: Personification “regs controlling us” works in KM, and should be adjusted in Daughter Translations only if personification doesn't work. Not simply because they are personification.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, I am speaking to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, I am speaking to those who know (the) law. Don't you know that the law has authority over a person as long as he lives? èe agnoéite ... ginoóskousin: I am assuming you know how laws in general work -- they apply to living people, not dead people<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nómon: law in general, not specifically Jewish or Roman</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Beta ame conto dari atoran laki-bini. Kalo satu parampuan su kawin deng dia pung laki, iko atoran hukum, dong dua jadi laki-bini sampe mati. Ma kalo dia pung laki su mati, na, itu janda sonde ta'ika lai deng itu atoran. Dia bole kawin baru.<bt>I'll take an example from husband-wife regulations. If a female/woman has married with her husband, according to legal regulations, the two of them are husband-wife until death. But if her husband is dead, na, that widow is not bound/tied anymore to that regulation/law. She may marry anew.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the woman who has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the woman who has a husband is bound to the living husband by law. But if the husband dies, she is released from the law concerning the husband.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma kalo dia kawin deng orang laen waktu dia pung laki masi idop, na, iko atoran, dia su barsina. Ma kalo dia pung laki su mati, atoran laki-bini sonde kaná sang dia lai. Dia su bebas. Ais kalo dia kawin deng orang laen, na, iko atoran dia sonde barsina.<bt>But if she marries with another/different person when her husband is still living well, according to the regulation she is committing adultery there. But if her husband is already dead, the husband-wife regulations don't affect her anymore. She is free. Then if she marries another person, na, according to regulation/law she is not committing adultery. [EXEG: Gk /géneetai andrì hetérooi/: can be applied to marriage, as it is later in this verse, but in the first part it implies the woman leaving her husband and shacking up with somebody else. So NRSV “if she lives with another man”; CEV “goes off with another man”; SSA “means ‘marries’, ‘is joined to’, or more probably ‘lives with, cohabits with’”; NEB “if…she consorts with another man” TB missed the shift. Most of our lgs have a term that can mirror the ambiguity in the Gk between a formal marriage and a de facto relationship that hasn't gone through recognised cultural processes. Try to mirror this. Otherwise err on the side of the non-formal relationship.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then, if she marries"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then, if she marries another man while her husband is living, she will be called an adulteress. But if her husband is dead, she is free from the law, and if she marries another man, she is not an adulteress. géneetai andrì hetérooi: can be applied to marriage, as it is later in this verse, but in the first part it implies the woman leaving her husband and shacking up with somebody else<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>chreemaatísei: she is acting like an adulteress, is recognized as one</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Bagitu ju deng bosong yang parcaya! Bagini: Kristus su mati. Itu sama ke bosong ju su mati sama-sama deng Dia, deng kasi tenga bosong pung idop yang lama. Ais atoran hukum sonde kaná sang bosong lai. Sakarang bosong su bebas dari itu atoran, deng su ta'ika deng Kristus, yang su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati. Itu sama ke janda yang kawin baru. Sonde ada masala. Jadi sakarang, samua yang bosong bekin tu, bekin kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>It's like that also with you who believe! Like this: Kristus has died. That is like you also have died together with Him, and have left behind your old lives. So (consequently) the legal regulations don't affect/apply.to you anymore. Now you are free from that Law, and already tied/bound together with Kristus, who has already come back to life again from His death. That is the same as a widow who marries anew. There's no problem. So (consequently) now, everything which you do, do for God2. [EXEG: some commentators see this as applying broader than just to Jewish law so don't restrict vs.4-6.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** add Begini: to make the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** add Begini: to make the discourse transition better (2009) <span class="Italic">(4) </span>(al) It like this: At one time you were under the authority of Moses law. But when Chirst died, he rescued you from the Law’s authority. Now you have a different Authority over you. That is the One who was waken from the dead in order to work in you/ make you profitable to God. (Suriname)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So, my brothers, you also"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So, my brothers, you also have become dead to the law by the body of Christ, that you should belong to another, to the one who is raised from the dead, that we should produce fruit for God. tóoi nómooi: as far as the law is concerned -- again, not just the Jewish law, but whatever cultural rules you live under<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Te dolu, kotong cuma bekin iko kotong pung mau-mau sandiri sa. Tagal kotong tau atoran, itu bekin kotong suka langgar itu atoran dong, ko bekin hal-hal yang sonde batúl. Naa! Kotong pung sala tu, yang bekin Tuhan Allah bale balakang sang kotong.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) formerly, we-inc only just did according to our-inc own desires/passions. Because we know the regulation/s, that makes us like to violate those regulations, to do things which are not correct. So! Those wrongs of ours, are what makes God turn his back on us. [EXEG: SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV confused here;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV confused here;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For when we were [in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For when we were [in the flesh/controlled by our sinful nature], the sinful passions, which were by the law, worked in our [members/bodies] to produce fruit for death. dià tóu nómou: the law made us want to do bad things, and this determined what we did with our bodies<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Dolu kotong musti bekin iko atoran. Ma sakarang atoran sonde kaná lai sang kotong, te kotong su lapás buang kotong pung idop lama. Iko jalan lama pung mau, na, Musa pung atoran yang ada tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi ada ika sang kotong. Ma iko jalan baru pung mau, na, kotong su bebas dari itu atoran. Te Tuhan pung Roh yang ator sang kotong na! Andia ko, sakarang kotong karjá kasi sang Tuhan sa.<bt>Formerly we had to do according to the regulation/s. But now the regulation/s doesn't apply to us anymore, cuz/for (elaboration) we have thrown off our old lives. Following the desires of the old way, na, Moses' Law/Regulation/s which are written in the Clean/Holy Writings are tying/binding us. But following the desires/requirements of the new way, na, we are free from those regulation/s. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2's Spirit is what controls us [+emphatic]! That's why, now we just work for God2. [EXEG: SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Regs to Moses' regs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Regs to Moses' regs following SSA, TB (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now, by dying to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now, by dying to what once bound us, we have been released from the law, so that we serve in the new way of the Spirit, and not in the old way of the written law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Musa pung atoran buka kasi tunju jahat yang ada di kotong pung hati<bt>Moses' Law reveals the evil that is in our-inc livers [Section: SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Regs to Moses regs,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Regs to Moses regs, SSA (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi kotong mau bilang apa? Mangkali bosong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Atoran yang Tuhan kasi sang Musa tu, sala!&gt;&gt; Sonde! Te kalo beta sonde mangarti itu atoran, sonde mungkin beta mangarti hal-hal yang sonde batúl dalam beta pung hati. Conto ke, ada atoran yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang kapingin mau ame orang pung milik.&gt;&gt; Ma karmana beta bisa tau kapingin macam bagitu tu, sala, kalo beta sonde tau ada dia pung atoran? Sonde bisa!<bt>So (consequently), what do we-inc want to say? Perhaps/probably you-pl are thinking, &lt;&lt;God2's Law, is wrong!&gt;&gt; No! Cuz/for (elaboration) if I don't understand His Law, it's not likely that I will understand the things which are not right/correct in my liver/heart. For example, there is a regulation which says, &lt;&lt;Don't desire to take/get people's possessions.&gt;&gt; But how can I know that a desire like that is wrong, if I don't know its regulation? (I) can't! [EXEG: SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Regs to Moses regs,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Regs to Moses regs, SSA (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tí óun eróumen: starts a new"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Tí óun eróumen: starts a new section, with a different philosophical argument LITERALLY: What shall we say then? That the law itself is sinful? Certainly not! But I would not have known sin except through the law. I would not have known what it is to covet if the law had not said, "You shall not covet."<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="7:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:17, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:21</note><v n="8" />Ma tagal ada atoran yang bilang bagitu, itu tingka ke hal-hal jahat dalam beta pung hati ada bekin beta kapingin mau ame orang pung milik macam-macam. Kalo sonde ada atoran yang larang, na, sala ju sonde ada pung kuasa ko ator orang.<bt>But because there is a regulation which says like that, it is as if the evil things in my liver/heart are making me disire to take/get all.sorts of possessions of people. If there aren't regulation/s/law that forbid, na, wrong/sin also doesn't have power to control people. [EXEG: NLT, MC]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But sin, taking the opportunity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But sin, taking the opportunity given by the commandment, produced in me every kind of covetous desire. For apart from law, sin is dead.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Di beta pung idop dolu, beta sonde mangarti batúl sarat dari Tuhan pung Atoran. Lama-lama, baru beta dapa mangarti deng batúl. Andia ko baru beta sadar bilang, beta su langgar itu Atoran deng bekin sala. Deng sala pung upa tu, andia beta musti mati.<bt>In my former life, I didn't truly understand the requirements of God2's Law. Eventually, only then did I truly understand. That's why I became aware that I had violated/transgressed that Law and done wrong. And the reward/consequence of wrong, is I had to die. [EXEG: NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***extensive reworking to fix exegesis in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***extensive reworking to fix exegesis in context (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Once I was alive apart"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Once I was alive apart from the law. But when the commandment came, sin sprang to life,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di beta pung idop dolu, beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Di beta pung idop dolu, beta sonde kanál Tuhan pung Atoran. Lama-lama, baru beta dapa tau Dia pung Atoran yang larang hal-hal yang sonde batúl. Tarús, hal-hal jahat dalam beta pung hati maspurak kaluar, sampe beta langgar itu Atoran deng bekin sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais beta pung hati ancor, te beta tau bilang, beta sandiri sonde bisa babae deng Tuhan, cuma tagal bekin iko Dia pung Atoran. Beta pantas kaná Tuhan pung mara, andia hukuman mati, tagal beta su langgar Dia pung Atoran. Padahal Atoran ada, ko bekin orang bisa idop batúl. Ma buat beta, itu Atoran yang bekin rusak sang beta, ais bekin Tuhan bale balakang sang beta.<bt>So then my liver was destroyed (discouraged, disappointed) cuz I knew/came to realise that I myself couldn't be recip.good with God2, only because of obeying His Law. It is appropriate that I get (adversely) God2's anger, that is the punishment of death, because I have violated His Law. Where.in.actual.fact, the Law exists, in order to make/cause people able to live right/correctly. But for me, it was that Law which ruined me, and so made God2 turn his back on me. [EXEG: See SSA, Moo. Something along the lines of “I came to realize that my assumption that I could obtain eternal life by actually keeping the law, was wrong. In fact, obeying the law made me come to realize I was separated from God.” In the context, he's talking about keeping the law, not about his inadequate attempts of “trying” to keep it. It is a massively profound theological watershed for Paul.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, itu sama ke beta mati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ais, itu sama ke beta mati dalam beta pung hati.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and I died. And the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and I died. And the commandment, which was meant to bring life, in my case brought death.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Atoran tu, memang kasi tunju jalan idop yang batúl. Ma tagal ada jahat yang idop dalam beta pung hati, beta su tipu ame beta pung diri, ko pikir bilang, beta bisa babae deng Tuhan asal beta bekin iko Dia pung Atoran. Ais, itu tingka ke Atoran sandiri yang bekin sampe Tuhan noju sang beta, deng sonde mau bagabung deng beta.<bt>That Law, really does show the path of life which is right/correct. But because there is wrong/sin which lives in my liver/heart, I have deceived myself to think that I can be in a right.relationship with God2 as long as I do according to His Law. Then, it's as if it's the Law itself which makes God2 to the point that He is disgusted/revolted with me, and not want to relate to me. [NOTE to daughter translations: some mesolectal speakers don't know /noju/, so explicated in last clause. Not necessary if everyone knows the word in your language.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Because this wrong is in my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Because this wrong is in my liver, I deceived myself that I could be right with God by keeping God's law.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For sin, taking the opportunity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For sin, taking the opportunity given by the commandment, deceived me, and by it killed me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu sala tu, pake Tuhan pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Itu sala tu, pake Tuhan pung Atoran ko tipu ame sang beta. [depersonifired].</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi, kalo tadi orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Atoran yang Tuhan kasi sang Musa tu, sala,&gt;&gt; na, beta manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Tuhan pung Atoran tu, barisi!&gt;&gt; Deng samua parenta dalam itu Atoran tu, barisi, batúl, deng bae.<bt>So (consequently), if those recent people (=earlier in the text) say, &lt;&lt;The Law that God gave Moses, is wrong,&gt;&gt; I respond saying, &lt;&lt;No! God2's Law, [is/are] clean/holy/pure!&gt;&gt; And all the commands in that Law are also clean/holy, right/correct, and good. [NOTE: responding to v.7, SSA, TB]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Law to law God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Law to law God gave Moses, as in v.7 fr SSA, TB (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then, the law is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then, the law is holy, and the commandment holy, and just, and good. nómos: by now it's more specifically the revealed law, as well as cultural rules<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Mangkali bosong ju pikir bilang, itu Atoran yang bekin Tuhan bale balakang sang beta, to? Sonde! Te biar beta tau itu Atoran, ma beta masi dengar-dengar sang itu jahat yang ada dalam beta pung hati, sampe beta bekin sala. Naa, beta pung bekin sala tu yang bekin Tuhan bale balakang sang beta. Atoran sandiri memang bae, te itu kasi tunju hal-hal yang jahat, yang bekin kotong tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah. Jadi waktu Tuhan kasi tunju jalan idop yang batúl, itu Atoran yang kasi jalás bilang, hal jahat dalam kotong pung hati tu, sonde bae.<bt>Perhaps/probably you are also thinking saying, it's the Law which made God2 turn his back against me, right? No! Cuz/for (elaboration) even though I know that Law/Regulation, nevertheless I still keep listening to/obeying/following that evil which is in my liver/heart, to the point that I do wrong/sin. Naa [+shift] it is my doing wrong that makes God2 turn his back/reject on me. The Law itself is certainly good, cuz/for (elaboration) it shows/reveals thing which are evil, which cause us-inc to be cut off/separated away from God1. So (consequently), when God2 shows the path of life which is right/correct, that Law is what makes clear/explains that, those evil things in our liver/hearts, are not good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Did that which is good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Did that which is good become death to me? Certainly not! But so that sin might be seen as sin, it produced death in me through what was good, so that through the commandment sin might become completely sinful.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te sala yang ada dalam beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te sala yang ada dalam beta pung hati tu, yang pake itu Atoran, deng bekin Tuhan bale balakang sang beta. Atoran sandiri memang masi bae, te itu kasi tunju hal-hal yang jahat batúl, yang bekin Tuhan Allah bale balakang sang kotong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hal bae deng hal jahat batola-bahela dalam kotong pung hati<bt>Good things and evil things push and pull (struggle with each other) in our-inc livers/hearts.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kotong tau bilang, Atoran yang Tuhan kasi sang ba'i Musa turun datang dari Tuhan pung Roh. Ma beta cuma manusia biasa yang pung hati sonde kuat. Ais beta dengar-dengar hal jahat yang ada dalam beta pung hati yang busuk, sampe beta bekin sala. Itu sama ke sala jadi beta pung bos, deng beta jadi sala pung budak.<bt>We-inc know that, the Law which God2 gave to Gf/Ff Musa, came down from God2's Spirit. But I am only an ordinary human whose liver (character) is not strong. So I listen.to/obey the evil things which are in my rotten liver/heart, to the point that I do wrong. That is as if wrong/sin was my boss, and I became sin's slave.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batola balakang = berlawanan ; batola-bahela"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">batola balakang = berlawanan ; batola-bahela = tug of war, baku lawan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that the law is spiritual. But I am [unspiritual/carnal/worldly], sold as a slave to sin.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta jadi bingung. Beta sonde mangarti apa yang beta bekin. Te beta sonde bekin iko apa yang beta mau bekin. Ma beta bekin iko apa yang beta sonde mau bekin.<bt>I'm confused. I don't understand what I do. Cuz/for (elaboration) I don't do according to what I want to do. But I do according to what I don't want to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I do not know what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I do not know what I am doing. Because what I want to do, I do not do. But what I hate, I do.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 5:17</note><v n="16" />Kalo beta bekin iko apa yang beta sonde mau bekin, beta mangaku bilang, Tuhan pung Atoran tu, batúl.<bt>If I do according to what I don't want to do, I acknowledge/confess that, that Law of God2's, is right/true. [NOTE to daughter translations: in a number of lgs, one can only “confess wrong” but can't confess /mangaku/ s.t. in the sense of “affirm” as in confess this is true, confess JC as Lord, etc. Try /tarima/ or /satuju/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If I do what I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If I do what I do not want to do, I agree that the law is good.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Jadi bukan beta yang ator beta pung diri. Ko jahat yang idop di beta pung hati yang ator sang beta na!<bt>So (consequently), it's not me who controls/manages myself. Obviously it's the evil which lives in my liver/hearts that controls me [+speaker emphasis]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then it is not me"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then it is not me that does it, but sin that lives in me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Beta su tau bilang, sonde ada hal bae yang idop di beta pung hati. Te beta ni, manusia yang pung hati busuk. Mau tar mau, beta sonde bisa paksa diri ko bekin yang batúl. Beta mau, ma sonde jadi-jadi!<bt>I know that, there is no good thing which lives in my liver/heart. Cuz/for (elaboration) I here, am a human who has a rotten liver/heart. Want to or not, I cannot force myself to do what is right/correct. I want to, but it doesn't happen/eventuate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I know that nothing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I know that nothing good lives in me, that is in my sinful nature. Because the good desire is with me, but I do not find how to do that which is good.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Te beta kapingin bekin yang bae, ma beta sonde bekin. Deng beta sonde mau bekin yang jahat, ma beta bekin sa!<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) I desire to do what is good, but I don't do it. And I don't want to do what is evil, but I just do it!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the good that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the good that I would like to do, I do not do. But the evil that I do not want to do, that I do.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Naa! Kalo beta bekin iko apa yang beta sonde mau bekin, itu bukan tagal beta sandiri, ma tagal jahat yang ada idop di beta pung hati.<bt>So! If I do according to what I don't want to do, that is not because of me myself, but because of the evil which is living in my liver/heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now, if I do what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now, if I do what I would not like to do, it is not me that is doing it, but sin that lives in me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu bukan beta, yang karjá, ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">itu bukan beta, yang karjá, ma sala yang ada idop di beta pung hati yang karjá.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Itu kasi tunju satu parinsip, bagini: biar beta mau bekin yang bae, ma ada jahat dalam beta pung hati yang malawan.<bt>That shows/reveals a principle (assimilated loan), like this: even if/though I want to do what is good, nevertheless there is evil my liver/heart which opposes/rebels/fights against it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parinsip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">parinsip</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So I find a principle,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So I find a principle, that when I want to do good, evil is present with me.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Padahal beta pung dalam hati paling sanáng, kalo beta ada pikir so'al Tuhan pung Atoran.<bt>However, my inner liver/heart (=conscience) is very happy, if I am thinking about God2's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I delight in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I delight in the law of God in my inner being.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ma tingka ke ada kuasa dalam beta pung hati yang bekin rusak sang beta. Te beta kapingin mau bekin yang bae, ma sonde jadi-jadi. Itu tingka ke kuasa jahat yang ada dalam beta pung hati ada tangkap ame sang beta, ko mau paksa beta iko sang dia sa.<bt>But it.is.as.if there is a power/authority in my liver/heart which ruins/destroys me. [NOTE: kuasa 'power' here intended as sense #2 authority/law/principle, not sense #1, power. Kuasa's can be in opposition, but atoran and prinsip can't.] Cuz/for (elaboration) I desire to do what is good, but it just doesn't happen/eventuate. It.is.as.if the evil force/power which is in my liver/heart has captured/arrested me, trying to force me to only follow him (personification).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I see another principle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I see another principle in my body, fighting against the principle of my mind, and bringing me into captivity to the principle of sin, which is in my body.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Aduu, kasian, é! Beta orang sangsara! Sapa yang bisa kasi salamat sang beta dari ini kuasa jahat yang idop di beta pung hati, yang bekin Tuhan noju sang beta sampe Dia bale balakang sang beta?<bt>Aduu, kasian [+grief, remorse] Oh dear! I am a person in a difficult fix! Who can save me from this evil power which lives in my liver/heart, which makes God2 detest/abhor me to the point that He turns His back on me? [NOTE to daughter translations: last clause explication of /noju/ which soem mesolectal Kupang speakers don't know; so if local word clear, don't put in the explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What a miserable person I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What a miserable person I am! Who will rescue me from this body of death?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma, awii! Tuhan Allah sandiri su buka jalan ko kasi lapás sang beta! Tarima kasi bam-banya sang Dia, tagal kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus bisa kasi salamat sang beta! Jadi, kalo beta idop basandar di beta pung diri, beta sangsara. Biar beta kapingin mau bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran samua, ma ada kuasa jahat di beta pung hati yang buju sang beta ko bekin sala tarús.<bt>But awii [+amazement]! God1 himself has opened the way to set me free! Many thanks to Him, because our Bos Yesus Kristus can save me! So (consequently), if I live leaning/depending on my own self, I am miserable/in torment. Even if I want to do according to all God2's Law, nevertheless there is an evil power in my liver/heart which coaxes/persuades, cajoles/tempts me to keep doing wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thanks to God through Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thanks to God through Jesus Christ our Lord! So then, with the mind I myself serve God's law, but with the body the [law/principle] of sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong bisa idop batúl, kalo kotong ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh<bt>We-inc can truly live, if we are bound/linked with God2's Spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi Tuhan Allah sonde kasi hukum sang orang yang ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus!<bt>So (consequently), God1 doesn't punish people who are bound/linked/tied.together with Yesus Kristus!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, there is now no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus, ára: this wraps up what Paul has said before. It's like getting back to the main point<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>nýn: in contrast to the impasse he was talking about in the last chapter. It's talking about logic, not time -- "the way things really are" sárka: probably copied from Verse 4 to make clear what "stay tight" is referring to. It's in a few important manuscripts but not in all<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te ada dua parinsip yang batúl: partama, kalo kotong ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus, Tuhan pung Roh kasi kuasa sang kotong ko bisa idop batúl. Yang kadua, ada jahat di kotong pung hati yang buju kotong ko bekin sala. Deng kalo kotong bekin sala, Tuhan Allah noju sang kotong, ju bale balakang sang kotong. Naa. Kalo kotong dapa Tuhan pung Roh, Dia kasi lapás sang kotong dari sala pung kuasa.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) there are two principles which are right/true: first, if we are bound/linked with Yesus Kristus, God2's Spirit gives us power/authority to be able to live right/correctly. The second is, there is evil in our livers that cajoles/coaxes/tempts/persuades us to do wrong/sin. And if we-inc do wrong, God1 is disgusted/abhorred with us, and turns his back on us. Naa [+shift]. If we have God2's Spirit, He frees us from the power of wrong/sin. [EXEG: “/nomos/ of the Spirit” is widely argued that it has to be taken in the sense of “principle” and not “law” in this context. See Morris, Moo, SSA, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Because the principle of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Because the principle of the Spirit bringing life in Christ Jesus has set me free from the principle of sin and death.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te ada dua parinsip yang batúl:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te ada dua parinsip yang batúl: partama, kalo kotong ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh, Dia mau bekin kotong ko idop batúl, deng ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus. Yang kadua, kalo kotong bekin sala, Tuhan Allah noju sang kotong, ju bale balakang sang kotong. Naa. Kalo kotong dapa Tuhan pung Roh, Dia kasi lapás sang kotong dari sala pung kuasa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Biar kotong bekin iko Musa pung Atoran, itu sonde bisa kasi salamat sang kotong dari sala pung kuasa, te kotong cuma manusia biasa sa yang bekin sala tarús. Ma Tuhan yang buka jalan kaluar. Te Dia kirim Dia pung Ana sandiri ko jadi manusia biasa sama ke kotong. Biar kotong manusia biasa laen bekin sala macam-macam, ma Yesus sandiri sonde parná bekin sala apa-apa. Tamba lai, Dia jadi korban ko hapus buang orang pung sala-sala. Deng dia bekin bagitu, Dia kasi ancor buang sala pung kuasa yang parná ator sang kotong.<bt>Even if we do according to Moses' Law, that cannot save us from the pwer of wrong/sin, cuz/for (elaboration) we-inc are only just ordinary humans who keep sinning. But God2 is the one who opened/made a way out. Cuz/for (elaboration) He sent His own Child to become an ordinary human like us. Even though we-inc other normal humans do all sorts of wrong, nevertheless Yesus himself never did any wrong. Furthermore, His life shows that, what it is that people do, is wrong/sin. In addition, He became a *sacrifice to erase/wipe away people's wrongs/sins. In that way, He destroyed the power of sin that once controlled us. [EXEG: SSA, NLT, CEV, TB, Morris, Moo. It is not about the effort in trying to do it (whether it succeeds or not), but that even if we could do it successfully, Paul has come to realise that still wouldn't make the grade. Clarified “sinful nature” in 1st sentence in 2013. NLT He “destroyed sin's control over us”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Law to Moses' law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Law to Moses' law (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For what the law could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For what the law could not do, in that it was weakened by our sinful nature, God did by sending his own Son in the likeness of sinful man [and for sin/ to be a sin offering]. And so he condemned sin in sinful man,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal, Yesus sonde parná bekin sala."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Padahal, Yesus sonde parná bekin sala. Ais, Dia pung idop kasi tunju, bilang, apa yang orang dong bekin tu, sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Tuhan Allah su kirim sang Kristus ko Dia mati, ko biar kotong bisa bekin iko samua hal yang batúl, iko Tuhan pung Atoran dong. Ais sakarang kotong ada bekin hal-hal yang batúl, iko Tuhan pung Roh pung mau, deng sonde bekin iko lai kotong pung mau-mau sandiri.<bt>God1 sent Kristus in order that He die, so that we-inc can do according to all the things that are right/correct/true, according to God2's Law. So then now we are doing right/correct/true things, according to God2's Spirit's desire/will, and not following anymore our own desires/passions. [EXEG: Not Moses law here (Moo, SSA). Don't follow TB.] [NOTE: BT “desire/will” and “desires/passions” are lexically related, but morphologically distinct.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: in order that the righteous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: in order that the righteous requirements of the law might be fully met in us, who do not live according to the sinful nature, but according to the Spirit. katà sárka: same idea as in 3 -- human nature is driven by how we feel, and it motivates the way our bodies behave<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Orang yang idop iko dong pung mau-mau sandiri tu, idop bagitu tagal dong cuma tau pikir hal-hal jahat tarús sa. Ma orang yang idop iko Tuhan pung Roh pung mau, dong cuma tau pikir hal-hal yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung Roh sa.<bt>Those people who live according to their own desires/passions, live like that because they only able to think continually about evil things. But people who live according to God2's Spirit's desires/will, they are only able to think about things which make God2's Spirit happy. [NOTE to daughter translations: Wording resonates with Gen. 6:5--compare phrasing.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gen 6:5 ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Gen 6:5 ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those who live according to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those who live according to their sinful nature have their minds set on what the sinful nature wants; but those who live according to the Spirit have their minds set on what the Spirit wants.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Orang yang kasi biar hal-hal jahat ko ator dia pung pikiran, sama ke orang yang sonde tau dengar Tuhan pung Roh, andia dia pung dalam hati su mati kasi sang Tuhan. Ma orang yang kasi biar Tuhan pung Roh ko ator dia pung pikiran tu, dia idop batúl, deng dia pung hati tanáng.<bt>A person who allows evil things to control/arrange his thinking, is the same as a person who doesn't know how/isn't able to listen to God's Spirit, that is his/her conscience/ inner being is already dead toward God2. But a person who allows God2's Spirit to control/ arrange that thinking of his, he has true life, and his liver/heart is calm. [HCE: EXEG: SSA seems to be incorrect here in pushing death &amp; life = eternal damnation &amp; eternal life; mind, controlled by, life &amp; peace all seem to indicate he is talking about here on earth; “death” is structurally juxtaposed to “life &amp; peace”, hence rendering here as “death in his liver” Morris rejects the idea of “consequences, results in, brings”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thanatos: mahke inside, as in 1"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">thanatos: mahke inside, as in 1 Timothy 5:6 LITERALLY: The mind of the sinful nature is death, but the mind controlled by the Spirit is life and peace,<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang cuma pikir hal-hal jahat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Orang yang cuma pikir hal-hal jahat yang dia mau bekin tu, sama ke orang yang su mati dalam dia pung hati. Ma orang yang kasi biar Tuhan pung Roh ko ator dia pung pikiran tu, dia idop yang batúl, deng dia pung hati tanáng.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Kotong manusia pung mau-mau sandiri bamalawan karás deng Tuhan pung mau. Ais kotong sandiri sonde tondo ko mau dengar sang Tuhan, tagal kotong sandiri sonde bisa.<bt>Us-inc human's own desires/passions strongly oppose God2's will. So then we (by) ourselves don't bow (=symbol of respect) or want to listen to God2, because we (by) ourselves can't.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: because the mind of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: because the mind of the sinful nature is hostile to God. It does not submit to God's law, nor can it do so.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te orang yang kasi biar dong pung mau-mau sandiri ko ator sang dong, mau tar mau, sonde bisa bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) people who allow their own desires/passions to control/manage them, want-to-or-not, [they] cannot make.happy(=please) God2's liver/heart.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those controlled by their sinful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those controlled by their sinful nature cannot please God. arésai: do something that God will be happy about. It's like everything they do is polluted and they don't know it, but God knows<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma bosong tu, orang yang sonde idop jahat iko bosong pung mau-mau sandiri lai. Te kalo Tuhan pung Roh ada idop dalam bosong pung hati, bosong bekin hal-hal yang bekin sanáng sang Dia. (Ma kalo ada orang yang Kristus pung Roh sonde idop dalam dia pung hati, dia ju sonde jadi Tuhan pung milik.)<bt>But as for you-pl, [you are] people who do not live in an evil manner according to your own desires/ passions any more. Cuz/for (elaboration) if God2's Spirit is living in your livers, you do things that make.happy(=please) Him. (But if there is a person who Kristus' Spirit doesn't live in his liver, he also has not become God2's possession.) [NOTE to daughter translations: if /milik/ is troublesome, just use /orang/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you are not controlled"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you are not controlled by your sinful nature, but by the Spirit, if the Spirit of God lives in you. But if any person does not have the Spirit of Christ, he is not his.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Bosong pung badan nanti mati, tagal bosong pung bekin sala dolu. Ma tagal sakarang Kristus ada idop di bosong pung hati, bosong pung roh nanti idop tarús, tagal Tuhan su cap sang bosong, orang hati lurus, ais bosong su babae kambali deng Dia.<bt>Your-pl bodies later will die, because you previously did wrong/sin. But because now Kristus lives in your livers, your spirits later will live continually, because God2 has stamped/categorised you as striaght livered/ righteous people, so you are already in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. [NOTE to daughter translations: if bodies don't die, but people die, don't feel you have to retain the image. “You will die...” But discuss it in the full framework of vs.10-11, where there is death:life and body:spirit. So don't force the language, but make sure the contrasts come through.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if Christ is in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if Christ is in you, your body is dead because of sin, but your spirit is alive because of [righteousness / justification].</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal bosong su babae kambali deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">tagal bosong su babae kambali deng Tuhan.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Te Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati. Jadi biar kotong mati, kalo Tuhan pung Roh ada idop dalam kotong pung hati, Dia ju nanti bekin kotong idop kambali. Dia pung arti bilang, Dia kasi idop sang kotong, sama ke Dia su kasi idop kambali sang Kristus.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) God1 is the one who caused Yesus to live again from His death. So (consequently), even if/though we die, if God2's Spirit is living in us, He also later will make us live again/come back to life. That means, He will make us live/give us life, the same as He caused Kristus to live again. [DISCOURSE: shift to /kotong/ from Gk 2p for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And if the Spirit of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And if the Spirit of the one who raised Jesus from the dead is living in you, he who raised Christ from the dead will also give life to your [mortal / dying] bodies through his Spirit who lives in you.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop kambali sang Yesus dari Dia pung mati. Deng kalo Tuhan pung Roh ada idop dalam bosong, Dia ju nanti bekin bosong idop kambali. Andia, Dia kasi idop bosong pung badan, sama ke Dia kasi idop kambali sang Kristus, biar bosong pung badan dolu mati.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 3:16</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Roh kasi tau bilang, kotong jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana<bt>God2's Spirit tells/makes known that, we-inc have become God2's children</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi bagini, sodara dong! Kotong ada pung utang. Itu bukan utang ko idop iko kotong manusia pung mau-mau, ma utang ko idop iko Tuhan Allah pung mau.<bt>So it's like this, siblings! We-inc have a debt. It is not a debt to live following our human desires/passions, but a debt to live according to the will of God1. [EXEG: last clause implicit to explicit--from Helong check.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then brothers, we have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then brothers, we have an obligation, but it is not to our sinful nature, to live according to that.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te kalo kotong idop iko jahat yang ada di kotong pung hati sa, tantu Tuhan mau bale balakang sang kotong, deng hukum mati sang kotong! Ma kalo kotong kasi biar Tuhan pung Roh kasi ancor kuasa dari sala yang ada dalam kotong pung hati, nanti baru kotong bisa idop batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if we just live following/obeying the evil that is in our livers/hearts, surely God2 will turn His back on us, and punish us with death! But if we allow God2's Spirit to destroy the power from the wrong/sin that is in our liver, only then will we be able to live in a right/true/correct manner // have true life forever/eternally.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For if you live according"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For if you live according to the sinful nature, you will surely die! But if, by the Spirit, you [put to death / kill] the deeds of the body, you will live.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Orang yang dengar-dengar sang Tuhan pung Roh ko Dia ator sang dong, na, dong tu, Tuhan pung ana-ana.<bt>People who habitually.listen to/obey God2's Spirit so that He controls/manages them, na, they are God2's children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Those who are led by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Those who are led by the Spirit of God are the sons of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Kalo kotong kasi biar Tuhan pung Roh ator sang kotong, Dia sonde bekin kotong jadi ke budak yang idop taku-taku. Dolu, kotong bagitu. Ma tagal kotong su tarima Tuhan pung Roh ko ator sang kotong, kotong tau kotong su jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana. Andia ko nanti Dia mau dengar, kalo kotong pange sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa Bo'i, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>If we-inc allow God2's Spirit to control us, He doesn't make us become like a slave that lives in fear. Formerly we were like that. But because we have already received God's Spirit to control/manage us, we know we have already become God2's children. That's why later He will listen, if/when we call Him saying, &lt;&lt;Dear Papa, é!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: shift to /kotong/ from Gk 2p for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For you did not receive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For you did not receive a spirit [of slavery to fear / that makes you slaves to fear] again, but you received a Spirit [of sonship / who makes you sons]. And by him we cry out, "Abba [Papa/ Daddy], Father".</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 14:36, Galatia 4:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kotong pung hati sandiri yang kasi tau bilang, kotong jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana. Deng Tuhan pung Roh ju kasi tau bagitu.<bt>Our very own livers are what tells/lets us know that, we have become God2's children. And God2's Spirit also tells/makes known like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The Spirit himself gives testimony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The Spirit himself gives testimony with our spirit that we are God's children.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Kalo kotong jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana, dia pung arti bilang, nanti kotong tarima ame Dia pung pusaka, tagal Dia jadi kotong pung Bapa. Ais nanti, kalo Bapa kasi pusaka sang Dia pung Ana Kristus, kotong ju tarima sama-sama Dia pung pusaka. Ma ada satu hal lai: kotong musti dapa sangsara, sama ke Kristus ju dapa sangsara, ko biar nanti Tuhan bisa angka tinggi-tinggi sang kotong, sama ke Dia su angka tinggi-tinggi sang Kristus.<bt>If we become/are God's children, it means that, later we will receive His inheritance, because He is/has become our Father. So later, if Father gives an inheritance to His Child, Kristus, we also receive together [with Him] His inheritance. But there is one more thing: we must encounter/experience suffering, just as Kristus also encounter/experienced suffering, so that later God2 can lift us up high (=exalt/praise/glorify), the same as He has lifted Kristus up high.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Now since we are children,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Now since we are children, then we are heirs--heirs indeed of God and co-heirs with Christ, if we [suffer with him / share in his suffering], in order that we may also [be glorified with him / share in his glory]. ei: no doubt about it -- more like "since we are ..."<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>hína: suffering is the prerequisite, and it leads to the payoff, which is glory</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15-17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 4:5-7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nanti Tuhan angka tinggi-tinggi sang kotong<bt>Later God will lift us-inc up high (=praise/exalt/glorify)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma iko beta, sangsara yang kotong dapa sakarang sonde ada pung arti, kalo banding deng hal-hal hebat yang Tuhan nanti kasi tunju sang kotong.<bt>But according to me, the suffering which we get now doesn't have any meaning, if/when compared with the amazing/incredible things which God2 will later show us. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokalyftheenai: be revealed (by God) LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">apokalyftheenai: be revealed (by God) LITERALLY: For I consider that the present sufferings are not worth comparing with the glory that will be revealed for us.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Padahal samua yang Tuhan Allah su bekin di langit deng di bumi, ada tunggu-tunggu deng rindu ko mau lia Dia kasi tunju Dia pung ana-ana yang batúl tu, sapa. Te Dia ada mau kasi tunju sang dong deng hati babunga.<bt>In.actual.fact everything which God1 has made/created in the sky and the earth, is waiting expectantly and yearning to see Him show/reveal who His true children are. Cuz/for (elaboration) He wants to show/reveal them with a flowering(=joyful) liver. [EXEG: SSA + HCE (larger context)] [NOTE to daughter translations: if the /sapa/ construction makes things difficult, try a statement /ada tunggu-tunggu deng rindu ko mau lia Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung ana-ana deng hati babunga./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokaradokía: eager longing, deep desire, can't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">apokaradokía: eager longing, deep desire, can't wait to find out, itching LITERALLY: The creation waits in eager expectation for the sons of God to be revealed.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te Tuhan bekin langit deng bumi deng dong pung isi samua, ko bekin iko Dia pung maksud. Ma sonde jadi-jadi, bukan tagal dong sonde mau, ma tagal iko Tuhan pung mau, te Dia kasi hukum sang dong deng biar ko dong jadi rusak. Biar bagitu ju, ma masi ada harapan.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 made the sky and the earth and all their contents, in order to carry.out His intent/purpose/s. But it didn't happen/eventuate, not because they didn't want to, but because of following God2's will, cuz (elaboration) He punished them, and allowed them to become rotten/decayed. Even though that's the case, nevertheless there is still hope. [EXEG: SSA; theologically hairy verse; Morris points out arguments in several directions make equal (non)sense.] [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure /sonde jadi-jadi/ tracks to /bekin iko Dia pung mau/ not to creation (!) If problem, try /Ma dong sonde mau iko/. Also, if needed, see Helong for alternate organization combining vs.20-21.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the creation was subjected"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the creation was subjected to [worthlessness / futility / purposelessness], not by its own choice, but by the will of the one [God] who subjected it. Yet there was this hope,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bukan tagal dong pung mau sandiri,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">bukan tagal dong pung mau sandiri, ma tagal iko Tuhan pung mau.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:17-19</note><v n="21" />Te sakarang, samua yang Tuhan su bekin tu, rusak, deng sonde ada jalan kaluar. Ma nanti, Tuhan mau kasi lapás sang dong, ko dong sonde rusak lai, ma dong bisa jadi hebat iko Dia pung maksud. Dia ju mau angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung ana-ana dong, ko dong ju talapás dari yang rusak dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now, all those aforementioned [things] which God2 made, are ruined, and there is no way out. But later, God2 is going to free them, so that they aren't in a (morally/socially) ruined state anymore, but they can become amazing/incredible following/in.accord with His intent/purpose. He also is going to lift up high (exalt, glorify) His children, so that they also are freed from those things that are ruined. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: that the creation itself will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: that the creation itself will be freed from its bondage to decay, and brought into the glorious freedom of the children of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Te kotong su tau bilang, ada banya susa deng sangsara dalam ini dunya. Dari dolu sampe sakarang, samua yang Tuhan bekin tu, mahahoo dari rasa saki, waktu tunggu-tunggu ko Tuhan bekin samua jadi baru. Itu sama ke parampuan yang mahahoo dari rasa saki waktu tunggu-tunggu mau barana ame ana.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) we already know there is much trouble and strife in this world. From long ago until now, all those aforementioned things which God2 did/made/created, moan from pain, while eagerly waiting for/anticipating God2 making everything new. That is like a female who is groaning in pain anticipatin the birth of (her) child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that the whole"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that the whole creation has been groaning in the pains of childbirth right up to the present time.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kotong su tau, dari dolu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te kotong su tau, dari dolu sampe sakarang, samua yang Tuhan bekin tu, mahahoo dari rasa saki, sama ke parampuan yang rasa saki mau barana.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Bukan dunya sandiri sa yang ada tunggu-tunggu, ma kotong ju ada tunggu-tunggu bagitu. Biar Tuhan su kasi Dia pung Roh lebe dolo sang kotong, kotong ju ada mahahoo dalam hati. Te kotong ada jaga-jaga ko tunggu Tuhan Allah angka sang kotong jadi Dia pung ana-ana yang batúl, deng kasi lapás sang kotong pung badan dari samua yang rusak.<bt>Not just the world/creation itself which keeps waiting/anticipating, but we-inc also keep waiting/anticipating like that. Even though God2 has given His Spirit to us first, we also are moaning in our livers. Cuz/for (elaboration) we keep watching to wait for God1 to lift us up/appoint/adopt to become His true children, and to free our bodies from everything that is ruined. [NOTE to daughter translations: a possible way to better reflect the concept of “first fruits” is “God2 has given us His Spirit first, to show that later we will get more than that, we still moan...” But be careful it is not such heavy information load that it skews the focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparkheen: the first installment of what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">aparkheen: the first installment of what he plans to give us eventually. LITERALLY: And not only [them], but we also, who have the Spirit as the [firstfruits /first gift], groan inwardly as we wait eagerly for our adoption as children, the redemption of our bodies.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bukan dong sandiri sa, ma kotong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bukan dong sandiri sa, ma kotong ju bagitu. Biar kotong ada Roh yang Tuhan su kasi partama sang kotong, kotong ju ada mahahoo dalam hati. Te kotong ada jaga-jaga ko tunggu Tuhan Allah angka sang kotong jadi Dia pung ana-ana yang batúl, deng kasi lapás sang kotong pung badan dari samua yang rusak.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 5:2-4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Waktu Tuhan kasi salamat sang kotong, Dia ju kasi tau, nanti Dia mau bekin karmana. Ma sakarang kotong masi tunggu-tunggu, tagal balóm jadi. Kalo kotong lia satu hal su jadi, kotong sonde parlú tunggu-tunggu lai ko mau lia itu hal. Te orang sonde tunggu-tunggu lai ko mau lia satu hal yang su jadi, to?<bt>When God saved us, He also told/made known, what/how he would want to do later. But now we still waiting expectantly (in eager anticipation--carried by the reduplication), because it's not happened/ eventuated yet. If we see a thing has happened, we don't need to wait anymore to want to see that thing. Cuz/for (elaboration) people don't keep waiting (in anticipation) anymore to see a thing that has already happened, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we were saved by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we were saved by hope. But hope that is seen is not hope. For who hopes for what he sees?</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ma kalo kotong ada tunggu-tunggu ko mau lia satu hal yang balóm jadi, kotong masi bisa batahan deng sabar.<bt>But if we are eagerly waiting to see something that has not yet happened, we can still endure with patience.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But if we hope for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But if we hope for what we do not see, we wait for it with patience.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Bagitu ju, waktu kotong ada tunggu-tunggu, Tuhan pung Roh ju ada tolong sang kotong, tagal kotong sonde kuat, deng sonde tau sambayang deng batúl. Ma Tuhan pung Roh sandiri ada sambayang ganti sang kotong, biar kotong cuma tau mahahoo sa, deng sonde tau mau sambayang pake kata apa.<bt>In the same way also, while we keep waiting/anticipating/hoping2, God2's Spirit is also helping us. because we are not strong, and don't know how to pray right/true/correctly. But God2's Spirit himself is praying replacing us, even though we only just know how to moan, and don't know how to pray using which words. [EXEG: Morris, SSA, Phillips. TB misses it badly with “unuttered complaints”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: In the same way, the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: In the same way, the Spirit helps us in our weakness. We do not know how we should pray, but the Spirit himself [intercedes / pleads] for us with groans that words cannot express.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Tuhan Allah sandiri tau samua-samua yang kotong mau omong dalam kotong pung hati. Dia ju tau Dia pung Roh pung pikir. Andia ko Dia tau samua hal yang Dia pung Roh mau omong ko tolong sang kotong. Te Tuhan pung Roh pung pikir, sama ke Tuhan sandiri pung pikir. Deng Dia pung Roh ada sambayang sang Tuhan, minta ko Tuhan tolong sang orang parcaya dong. Te itu Roh sambayang iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>God himself knows everything that we want to say in our livers. He also knows His Spirit's thinking. That's why He knows/understands everything which His Spirit wants to say to help us. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2's Spirit's thinking, is the same as God2's own thinking. And His Spirit is praying to God2, requesting that God2 help the believers. Cuz/for (elaboration) that Spirit prays following/according to God2's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entynkhanei hyper hagioon: CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">entynkhanei hyper hagioon: CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY: And he who searches hearts knows the mind of the Spirit, because the Spirit intercedes for the saints in accordance with God's will.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Sakarang kotong su tau bagini: Tuhan Allah bekin samua jadi bae kasi orang yang sayang sang Dia. Te dari dolu-kala, Tuhan su ator memang so'al Dia mau bekin karmana kasi sang dong. Ju Dia su pange sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari, su! Mari jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Now we already know like this: God1 will make everything become good on.behalf.of/for the people who love Him. Cuz/for (elaboration) from long ago, God2 has arranged beforehand what it is that He wants to/is going to do for them. And He has already called them saying, &lt;&lt;Come on! Come become My people!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if /su ator memang so'al Dia mau bekin karmana kasi sang dong/ is hard to translate, try /su putus memang, iko Dia pung mau./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For those who love God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For those who love God and are called according to his purpose, he works out everything for good.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sakarang kotong su tau bagini: Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Sakarang kotong su tau bagini: Tuhan Allah bekin samua jadi bae kasi orang yang sayang sang Dia. Te dari dolu kala, Tuhan su ator memang so'al Dia mau bekin karmana kasi sang dong. Deng Dia su pange sang dong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari, su! Mari jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Te dolu-dolu, Dia su kanál memang sang dong, deng pili ame sang dong ko bekin jadi model sama ke Dia pung Ana, andia Kristus. Te Kristus yang sulung, deng yang laen dong jadi Dia pung adi.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) long ago, He already knew/recognised them beforehand, and chose them to become a model/image like His Child, which is Kristus. Cuz/for (elaboration) Kristus is the eldest [child], and the others are His younger siblings. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk “firstborn (of all creation)” is also used in Colossians, where that context makes it clear that sequential order is not in focus, but rather status above all creation. Just keep in mind that you also want status more in focus here, and if possible, minimise temporal order.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For those whom he knew"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For those whom he knew beforehand, he also planned beforehand to [become / be made] like his Son, so that he [Christ] might be the first born among many brothers.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Itu orang yang Tuhan su kanál dari dolu-dolu dong, Dia ju pange ame sang dong ko jadi Dia pung orang. Deng itu orang yang sama dong, yang dolu orang sala, Dia bekin jadi orang hati lurus ko dong babae kambali deng Dia. Deng Dia ju angka tinggi-tinggi sang dong.<bt>Those people whom God2 already knew from long ago, He also called them to become His people. And those very same people, who formerly were sinful/wrong /guilty people, He has made to become straight livered/righteous people so that they are in a reciprocally good relationship again with Him. And He also lifts them up high (=exalt, glorify; different grammar from lift up = appoint, adopt).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And those he knew beforehand,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And those he knew beforehand, he also called. Those he called, he also justified. Those he justified, he also glorified.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah sayang mati sang kotong<bt>God1 loves us to the max</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Jadi kotong mau bilang apa lai so'al itu hal dong? Tuhan Allah ada deken mati sang kotong. Deng kalo bagitu, na, sapa bisa lawan sang kotong lai? Sonde ada, to?<bt>So (consequently), what else can we say about these things? God1 is supporting/backing us to the max. If that the case, na, who can oppose us anymore? There's nothing/no.one, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what will we say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what will we say about these things? If God is for us, who is against us?</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Tuhan sonde tahan ame Dia pung Ana sandiri. Ma Dia sarakan Dia pung Ana ko mati jadi korban, ko tolong sang kotong samua. Tagal Tuhan sonde tahan ame Dia pung Ana sadiki ju, kotong bisa tau bilang, nanti Dia ju parsén kasi kotong, samua hal yang bae. Batúl, to?<bt>God2 didn't hold back His own Child. But He handed.over His Child to die as a sacrifice, in order to help us all. Because God2 didn't hold back His Child even just a little bit, we are able to know that, later He will also free.gift(verb) to us, all things which are good. That's true, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He who did not spare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He who did not spare his own Son, but gave him up for us all, how will he not also, with him, freely give us all things?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Mangkali bosong pikir bilang, masi ada orang yang bisa lempar sala kasi orang yang Tuhan su pili ame dong? Ma sonde ada, to? Te Tuhan sandiri yang su cap sang kotong bilang, orang hati lurus yang sonde ada pung sala lai, ko kotong babae deng Dia.<bt>Perhaps/probably you-pl think that there still are people who can accuse/cast blame on the people whom God2 has chosen? But there is no one, right? Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 himself is the one who stamped/branded/categorised us-inc as straight livered/righteous people who no longer have any wrong/sin/guilt, so that we could be in a reciprocally right relationship with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who will bring any accusation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who will bring any accusation against the ones that God has chosen? It is God who justifies [them].</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sapa mau lempar sala kasi orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Sapa mau lempar sala kasi orang yang Tuhan su pili ame dong? Sonde ada, to? Te Tuhan sandiri yang bekin dong jadi orang batúl ko dong babae deng Dia.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Mangkali bosong pikir bilang, masi ada orang yang bisa bilang Tuhan musti kasi hukum orang yang Dia su pili ame dong. Ma sonde mungkin! Te Yesus Kristus su mati. Lebe-lebe lai, Tuhan su kasi idop kambali sang Dia dari Dia pung mati. Ais Tuhan angka sang Dia ko dudu di tampa yang paling hormat di Dia pung sablá kanan. Di situ Dia ju yang sambayang tarús kasi sang kotong.<bt>Perhaps/probably you think that there still are people who can say that God2 must punish the people whom He has chosen (collective). But that is not possible/not going to happen! Cuz/for (elaboration) Yesus Kristus, has died. And even more, God2 caused Him to live again from His death. So/Then, God lifted Him up to sit in the place which has the most honor at His right side. There, He also is the one who prays continually on.behalf.of/for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who is the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who is the one who condemns? Christ Jesus is the one who died, or rather, who was raised to life, who is at the right side of God, who is also [interceding / pleading] for us.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, sonde ada orang lai yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, sonde ada orang lai yang bisa bilang Tuhan musti kasi hukum orang yang Dia su pili ame dong. Te Yesus Kristus tu, yang su mati. Lebe-lebe lai, Dia yang Tuhan su kasi idop kambali dari Dia pung mati. Ais, Tuhan angka sang Dia ko dudu di tampa yang paling hormat di Dia pung sablá kanan. Deng Dia ju yang sambayang tarús kasi sang kotong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Mangkali bosong pikir bilang, ada orang ko, ada hal ko, yang bisa paksa Kristus sampe Dia sonde sayang lai sang kotong, ko? Sonde mungkin! Te biar kotong dapa parkara ko, susa ko, sangsara ko, lapar ko, sonde ada pakean ko, ada calaka ko, orang mau bunu ko, ma Kristus tatáp sayang tarús sang kotong. Sonde ada satu ju yang bisa bekin Dia barenti sayang sang kotong!<bt>Probably/perhaps you think that there is person or, a thing or [whatever], that can force Kristus to the point that He does not love us anymore, [+tag question]? Impossible/no way! Cuz (elaboration) even if/though we get/experience/encounter a issue/dispute/ litigation or, difficulty or, suffering or, hunger or, not having clothes or, having misfortune or, people wanting to murder [us] or [whatever], nevertheless Kristus keeps on [+double continuative] loving us. There is not one thing that can make Him stop loving us!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Who shall separate us from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Who shall separate us from the love of Christ? Shall trouble, or hardship, or persecution, or famine, or nakedness, or danger, or sword?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong pikir, bilang, mangkali ada parkara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Bosong pikir, bilang, mangkali ada parkara ko, susa ko, sangsara ko, lapar ko, sonde ada pakean ko, ada calaka ko, orang mau bunu ko, yang bisa bekin Kristus sonde sayang lai sang kotong, wuang?</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang,<bt>In God2's Clean/Holy Writings it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Orang cari-cari jalan ko mau bunu sang kotong,<bt>&lt;&lt;People are looking for a way (to try) to murder us-inc,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal kotong jadi Tuhan pung orang.<bt>because we have.become/are God2's people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong bekin sang kotong,<bt>They do to us,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke domba yang dong mau horo.&gt;&gt;<bt>like a sheep which they want to/are going to slice.it's.throat (the act of the first phase of slaughter [ritual or for meat]).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As it is written, &quot;For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As it is written, "For your sake we are in danger of death all the day long. We are treated like sheep that are going to be slaughtered."</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 44:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Jadi biar kotong dapa susa karmana ju, ma kotong su manáng, tagal Kristus sayang mati sang kotong!<bt>So (consequently), even though we get/experience whatever kind of difficulty, nevertheless we have already won, because Kristus loves us to the max!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal Kristus sayang mati sang kotong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tagal Kristus sayang mati sang kotong, jadi, sonde ada yang bisa ganggu sang kotong lai, biar kotong dapa susa karmana ju. Ko kotong su manáng na!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: No, in all these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: No, in all these things we are more than conquerors through him who loved us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Beta su tau parsís bagini: sonde ada satu hal ju yang bisa bekin Tuhan kasi barenti Dia pung sayang sang kotong. Biar kotong idop ko, kotong mati ko, ada ana bua dari sorga ko, yang pegang parenta ko, ada kuasa ko, parkara sakarang ko, parkara nanti ko,<bt>I know precisely like this: there is not one thing that can make God2 stop His love for us. Regardless of whether we live or, we die or, there are underlings from heaven (=angels) or, those who hold rule/government or, there is a power or, disputes/issues now or, disputes later or,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I am convinced that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I am convinced that neither death nor life, neither angels nor other rulers or powers, neither the present nor [things to come / the future],</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />kuasa di langit ko, kuasa di bumi ko, barang laen yang Tuhan su bekin dong -- sonde ada satu ju yang bisa kasi pisa sang kotong dari Tuhan Allah, yang bekin Dia sonde sayang lai sang kotong! Tagal kotong ada ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang.<bt>powers in the sky or, powers on the earth or, other things which God2 has made, --- there is not a single thing which can separate us from God1, which can make Him not love us anymore! Because we are bound/linked with our Boss, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: neither height nor depth, nor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: neither height nor depth, nor anything else in all creation, will be able to separate us from the love of God that is in Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pili ame orang Isra'el dong<bt>God1 chose the Israel people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Kotong yang ada ta'ika deng Kristus, omong yang batúl. Jadi beta sonde omong kosong sang bosong. Beta pung dalam hati ju kasi tau sang beta bilang, Tuhan pung Roh ada ator beta pung hati.<bt>We-inc who are bound/linked/tied.together with Kristus, speak what is true/correct. So (consequently), I am not speaking emptily (=lying) to you-pl. My inner liver (=conscience) also tells me that, God2's Spirit is controlling my liver. [EXEG: on the switch from “I” to “we” in the 1st sentence, note Morris;' discussion about “as a Christian” being background for Paul's assertion; Moo's “as one united with Christ” being “the Christian reality from which he speaks”. The Gk. goes Positive-specific (I), Negative-specific (I). The Kupang deliberately goes Positive-generic principle (we-inc), Negative-specific (I), which is more natural for rephrasing in KM.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if “my conscience tells me” is too heavy, just say /Beta pung dalam hati ju kasi tau, bilang/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I speak the truth in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I speak the truth in Christ--I am not lying, my conscience [confirms/ testifies/ assures me] it to me in the Holy Spirit,</Message></Annotation><v n="2-3" />Beta kasi tau bagini: beta pung hati susa. Beta rasa barát bagitu, tagal beta inga beta pung orang sandiri. Te beta mau ko beta pung bangsa Yahudi dong<bt>I'm telling like this: my liver is distressed. I feel heaviness/sadness like that, because I remember my own people. Cuz/for (elaboration) I want that my own Yahudi ethnic group</bt><note reference="9:2-3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bangsa <span class="Italic">Yahudi</span> tu, sama deng bangsa Isra'el, andia orang Yahudi yang tenga di tana Isra'el, deng di tampa-tampa laen ju. Ma suku <span class="Italic">Yahuda</span> sonde sama deng bangsa Yahudi. Te suku Yahuda tu, andia, satu dari dua blas suku Isra'el.<bt>The <span class="Italic">Yahudi</span> race/people group, is the same as the Isra'el race/people group, that is the Yahudi people who live in the land of Isra'el, and also in other places. But the tribe of <span class="Italic">Yahuda</span> is not the same as the Yahudi race/people group. Cuz (elaboration) the tribe of Yahuda, is one of the twelve tribes of Isra'el.</bt></note>ju jadi ta'ika deng Kristus, ma banya yang sonde parcaya sang Dia. Andekata beta bisa buka jalan kasi sang dong, beta sadia minta ko Tuhan kasi hukum sang beta, ko ganti sang dong. Deng beta ju sadia minta ko Tuhan kasi pisa sang beta dari Kristus, ko biar beta pung orang bisa ta'ika deng Dia.<bt>also becomes bound/linked with Kristus, but many don't believe in Him. If perchance [=hypothetical] I could open the path for them, I am prepared to request that God2 punish me, to replace them. And I am also/would also be prepared to request God to separate me from Kristus, so that my people can become bound/linked with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: becauseI have great [sorrow /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: becauseI have great [sorrow / sadness / grief] and continual [anguish / sorrow / pain] in my heart. LITERALLY: For I could wish that I myself were cursed and cut off from Christ for the sake of my brothers, my own kinsmen in the flesh,<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>eeuchómeen: hypothetical, not saying that that's how it actually is, but what Paul would be willing to accept if that would help the others katà sárka: natural born relatives<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Padahal dong tu, orang Isra'el, andia satu bangsa yang paling ontong. Tuhan su angka sang dong jadi Dia pung ana-ana dari dolu-kala. Dia kasi tunju Dia pung kuasa yang hebat kasi sang dong. Dia ika janji macam-macam deng dong. Dia kasi Dia pung Atoran sang dong. Dong yang tau sémba sang Dia, deng layani sang Dia. Dia su janji mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang dong.<bt>Whereas in fact, they are the Isra'el people, that is a most fortunate race/people group. God2 has already raised/appointed/adopted them to be His children from long ago. He showed his amazing power to them. He bound/tied/made all.kinds.of promises with them. He gave His Law to them. They are the ones who know/knew how to worship Him, and serve Him. He already promised that He wants to show His good liver (grace/goodness/kindness) to them. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: who are the Israelites, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: who are the Israelites, who have been made children, and [received] the glory, and the [covenants / agreements], and the Law, and the [worship / spiritual service /religious service], and the promises, dóxa: glory, probably referring to God's awesome appearance in Exodus 14:22<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>diathéekai: not a contract they bargained over, but a mutually acceptable agreement on a take-it-or-leave it basis. The plural reflects the fact that the Israel people agreed to God's proposal three different times, at Sinai, just before they crossed the Jordan River, and again at Gerizim and Ebal, or else it reflects the series of covenants with Adam, Hoah, Abraham, and Moses latreía: the correct forms for public worship of God in the Tent and the Temple<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 4:21, 14:22</note><v n="5" />Dong turun datang dari botong pung nene-moyang, andia: ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob (orang ame nama &lt;Isra'el&gt; dari dia). Deng Kristus, yang Tuhan su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang tu, ju turun datang dari botong bangsa Yahudi pung nene-moyang dong. Kristus tu, andia Tuhan Allah yang parenta samua-samua ju. Jadi pantas kalo orang angka puji-puji sang Dia sampe salamanya. Batúl!<bt>They descended from our-exc ancestors, who were: Gf/Ff Abraham, Gf/Ff Isak, and Gf/Ff Yakob (people take/got the name &lt;Israel&gt; from him). And Kristus, that one whom God had promised beforehand long ago to send, also descended from our Yahudi ethnic group's ancestors. That Kristus, is also God1 who commands/orders/governs everything. So (consequently), it is appropriate if people lift up praises to Him forever. Really! [NOTE: names plus Jacob = Isra'el for high-level cohesion setting up following verses &lt; HCE; EXEG: Christ--who is God (theos, not kurios) over all] [NOTE to daughter translations: check if you can streamline /ju turun datang dari botong bangsa Yahudi pung nene-moyang dong./ = /ju turun datang dari dong./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***check UNS suggestion"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***check UNS suggestion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: From them are the [fathers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: From them are the [fathers / patriarchs], and from whom [came / was born] the Christ [according to the flesh / physically]; who is God over all--may he be [spoken well of / praised] forever, Amen! theòs: grammatically this is linked back to Christ, "the God who is in charge of everything, whom we praise from now to eternity". Most translations try to unlink them as "who is in charge of everything -- God be praised for ever", but then we would expect the article "ho" in front of theòs<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 32:22-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Biar orang Isra'el banya balóm tarima sang Kristus, ma orang sonde bisa omong bilang, Tuhan pung janji tu sonde jadi. Te jang kira kata, samua orang yang turun datang dari nene-moyang Isra'el tu, jadi bangsa Isra'el yang Tuhan pili ko jadi Dia pung orang.<bt>Even though many Isra'el people have not yet accepted Kristus, nevertheless people cannot say that, that promise of God2's didn't happen/eventuate. So don't think that all people who descend from ancestor Isra'el, are the Isra'el ethnic group that God2 chose to be/become His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is not as though"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is not as though God's Word had failed. For not all who are descended from Israel are Israel.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Conto ke, banya orang turun datang dari botong pung nene-moyang, ba'i Abraham. Ma dong samua bukan Abraham pung turunan yang Tuhan pili. Te Tuhan su kasi tau sang Abraham bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung turunan yang beta kanál, cuma dong yang turun datang dari lu pung ana Isak sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>For example, many people descended from our ancestor, Gf/Ff Abraham. But they are not all Abraham's descendants who God2 chose. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 told Abraham saying, &lt;&lt;Your-sg descendant/s whom I know/recognize, are only just those who descend from your child Isak.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Nor are Abraham's descendants all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Nor are Abraham's descendants all his children. On the contrary, "Through Isaac your offspring will be called." tékna: children without an article or a possessive (not "his children") in a section like this are more likely God's than Abraham's<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>all': on the contrary, rendered by "ony" inside the quotation</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 21:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Dia pung arti bilang, dari dolu sampe sakarang, sonde samua turunan yang datang dari botong orang Yahudi pung ba'i Abraham, yang jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana. Cuma turunan yang dari Tuhan pung janji kasi sang Abraham sa, yang Tuhan itong jadi Dia pung ana-ana yang batúl.<bt>It means that, from previous.times until now, not all descendants who come from we-exc Yahudi people's Gf/Ff Abraham, are the ones who are/become God1's children. Only just the descendants who are from God2's promise to Abraham, are the ones who God2 counts as His true children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That is, it is not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That is, it is not the physical children that are God's children, but the children of the promise are [considered / counted] to be the offspring.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung arti, bilang, dari samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dia pung arti, bilang, dari samua turunan yang turun datang dari kotong pung ba'i Abraham dari dolu sampe sakarang, bukan samua yang jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana. Cuma yang barana iko Tuhan pung janji kasi sang Abraham sa, yang Tuhan itong jadi Dia pung ana-ana yang batúl.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te Tuhan ika janji deng Abraham bilang, &lt;&lt;Kira-kira taon datang, Beta kambali. Itu waktu, lu pung bini Sara su barana satu ana laki-laki.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 bound/tied/made a promise with Abraham saying, &lt;&lt;Around next year, I will return. At that time, your wife Sara will already have given birth to a male child.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: compare with wording in Gen. 18:10]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For this was how the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For this was how the promise was stated: "At this time I will come back, and Sarah will have a son."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Bukan bagitu sa. Te botong pung ba'i Isak deng dia pung bini Ribka barana ame sang dua ana bagambar.<bt>Not just that. Cuz/for (elaboration) our-exc Gf/Ff Isak and his wife Ribka gave birth to twin children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Not only that, but Rebecca's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Not only that, but Rebecca's children had one and the same father, our ancestor Isaac.</Message></Annotation><v n="11-12" />Waktu Ribka balóm barana ame sang dong, dong balóm bekin hal bae ko hal jahat. Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan su kasi tau memang sang Ribka so'al ana bagambar yang kaluar lebe dolo bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti yang kaka karjá kasi dia pung adi.&gt;&gt; Tuhan kasi tau bagitu, ko kasi tunju bilang, kalo Dia su pili ame satu orang, Dia su tau Dia mau pake itu orang ko bekin karmana. Ais Tuhan ada pili sang itu adi ko jadi Dia pung orang. Dia sonde usa tunggu mau lia itu adi mau bekin karmana, tagal Tuhan su tau memang.<bt>When Ribka had not yet given birth to them, they had not yet done good things or evil things. Even though that was the case, nevertheless God had already told ahead of time to Ribka about the twin child which came out first saying, &lt;&lt;Later the one that is the elder.sibling will work for his younger sibling.&gt;&gt; God2 told like that, to show that, if He had already chosen a person, He already knew how/what He wanted to use that person to do. So then God chose that younger sibling to become His person. He didn't need to wait to see what that younger sibling was going to do, because God2 already knew beforehand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Yet, before the twins were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Yet, before the twins were born or had done anything good or bad, in order that God's purpose in choosing might stand, not by works but by him who calls. She was told, "The older one will serve the younger one." the order of the parts in 11 and 12 in Pidgin makes it better to put them together, because there isn't a logical break at the same place there is in Greek<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 25:23</note><v n="13" />Te Tuhan omong dalam Dia pung Tulisan Barisi so'al itu ana bagambar bilang,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 wrote in His Clean/Holy Writings about those twins saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta pili ame sang Yakob,<bt>&lt;&lt;I chose Yakob,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma beta tola buang sang Esau.&gt;&gt;<bt>but I rejected Esau.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Just as it is written,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Just as it is written, "Jacob I loved, but Esau I hated."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 1:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Jadi kotong mau bilang apa? Mangkali ada yang mau bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan putus parkara deng sonde adil?&gt;&gt; Sonde mungkin!<bt>So (consequently), what can we say? Perhaps there is someone who wants to say, &lt;&lt;God2 unfairly/unjustly decides/judges cases?&gt;&gt; Impossible/no way!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: What then shall we say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: What then shall we say? Is God unjust? Not at all!</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Te dolu-dolu Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang ba'i Musa bilang,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) long ago God told Gf/Ff Musa saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta kasi tunju rasa kasian sang orang yang Beta pili sandiri.<bt>&lt;&lt;I show pity/mercy toward people/person whom I myself choose. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure merciful actions are coming through, not just feelings of pity/compassion.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Beta kasi hati sang orang yang Beta tunju sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I give my liver (=show compassion) toward people/person whom I myself designate.&gt;&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV understranslates the meaning, and misses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CEV understranslates the meaning, and misses the literary parallel.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For he says to Moses,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For he says to Moses, "I will have mercy on whom I have mercy, and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 33:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Jadi itu orang sonde rasa Tuhan pung kasian tagal itu orang pung mau sandiri, ko, tagal dia pung bekin sandiri. Ma tagal Tuhan sandiri yang mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang itu orang.<bt>So (consequently), that person doesn't feel/experience God's pity/mercy because of that person's own will, or because of his own deeds. But because its God2 himself who wants to show His mercy/pity to that person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, it does not depend"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, it does not depend on a person's desire or effort, but on God's mercy.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te di Tulisan Barisi, Tuhan omong deng raja Masir bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta angka ame sang lu jadi raja, tagal Beta mau pake sang lu ko kasi tunju Beta pung kuasa sang banya orang. Deng bagitu, orang di anteru dunya bisa angka-angka Beta pung nama.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) in the Clean/Holy Writings, God2 spoke to the Masir (Egypt) raja saying, &lt;&lt;I lift you-sg up/appointed to be raja, because I want to use you to show My power to many people. In that way, people in the entire world will repeatedly lift up (=praise) My name.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Scripture says to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Scripture says to Pharoah, "I raised you up for this very purpose, that I might show my power in you, and that my name might be proclaimed in all the earth."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 9:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Jadi, kalo Tuhan mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang satu orang, na, Dia bekin sa. Deng kalo mau bekin satu orang pung hati karás, na, Dia bekin sa.<bt>So (consequently), if God2 wants to show His mercy/pity to a person, na, He just does so. And if he wants to make a person's liver/heart hard (unbending, unyielding--negatively valued), na, He just does so.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK hati karás here (cold-hearted vs."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">CHECK hati karás here (cold-hearted vs. hard-hearted);</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, God has mercy on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, God has mercy on those whom he wants to have mercy, and he hardens those whom he wants to harden.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:16-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 7:7-9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan bisa kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian, ma Dia ju sonde tarima jahat<bt>God2 can show His mercy/pity, but He also doesn't accept/put up with evil</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Naa! Andekata ada orang yang protes sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, kalo Tuhan mau bekin satu hal, sapa yang bisa malawan sang Dia? Sonde ada, to? Jadi, akurang ko Dia mau lempar sala sang kotong? Itu sonde adil!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then! If perchance [+hypothetical] there is a person who protests to me saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, if God2 wants to do something, who can oppose Him? No one, right? So (consequently), why does He want to accuse/blame us of wrong/sin? That's not just/fair!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then will you say to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then will you say to me, "Why does God still blame us? For who can resist his will?" mémphetai: find fault, complain, blame<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Kalo ada yang pikir bagitu, beta manyao bagini: &lt;&lt;Lu pikir lu ni, sapa?! Lu mau omong malawan sang Tuhan, ko?&gt;&gt; Jang bagitu! Te dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang bekin satu barang, mana bisa itu barang nanti tanya bale sang itu orang yang bekin sang dia bilang, &lt;Akurang ko lu bekin sang beta bagini!?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>If there is someone thinking like that, I respond like this: &lt;&lt;Who do you-sg think you are?! You want to speak opposing God, [+tag]?&gt;&gt; Don't (be/do/think) like that! Cuz/for (elaboration) in God2's Clean/Holy Writings it is written saying, &lt;&lt;If a person makes a thing, how can that thing later ask in return to that person who made it saying, &lt;&lt;Why did you-sg make me like this [+challenge]!?&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But who are you, O"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But who are you, O man, to talk back to God? "Shall what is [formed/ made] say to the one who formed it, 'Why have you made me like this?'" menóunge: used to answer a question when you have to correct the person asking the question -- he doesn't understand the situation<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:16, 45:9</note><v n="21" />Conto ke tukang bekin pareu. Dari tana liat satu kabuak, dia ada pung hak ko mau bekin satu kumbang mangkilat ko orang puji. Dia ju ada pung hak pake itu tana kabuak ko bekin satu tampa sampa, iko dia pung mau sa.<bt>For example, a pot maker. From one glump of clay, he has the right to make a shiny/fancy basin/jug for people to praise. He also has the right to use that glump of clay [short form for referent tracking] to just make a place for rubbish (=rubbish bin), according to his will/desire. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /hak/ doesn't collocate here, try /dia pili ko .../ (x2)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tong = drum ; guci ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">tong = drum ; guci = porclain jug</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phyrámatos: a mixed quantity of something."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">phyrámatos: a mixed quantity of something. Here, it's clay and water mixed together until it is just gooey enough to work with smoothly. Also used of mixing ingredients for medicine, the mix beer is brewed from, and mixed wine. If they had made poi, they would have used this word timeén: to be honored, usually in public. In this case, a vessel that is honored by the use to which it is put<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>atimían: shame, disgrace, humiliation, dishonorable use. UBS suggests that it means 'everyday use', but that comes in only as one possibility with the adjective átimos 'dishonored, insignificant'. In the papyri all uses of the words in this family are pretty strong, including association with 'being reviled', 'confiscation and public shame', 'shame of prostitution' 'accursed', 'denied the right to vote' LITERALLY: Doesn't the potter have the right to make out of the same lump of clay one pot for special purposes and another for common use?<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Bagitu ju deng Tuhan Allah. Dia ada pung hak ko bekin iko Dia pung mau. Dia mau kasi tunju sang samua orang bilang, Dia mara, deng sonde tarima orang pung bekin jahat apa-apa. Dia ju mau ko orang tau bilang, Dia ada kuasa bam-banya. Ko orang dapa tau bagitu, Dia tahan diri deng orang pung bekin jahat macam-macam. Ma orang yang bekin jahat, dong cuma tunggu dia pung waktu ko dong ancor buang.<bt>It's like that also with God1. He has the right to do according to what He wants. He wants to show all people that, He is/gets angry, and doesn't accept/put up with any of the evil that people do. He also wants people to know that, He has alot of power. So.that people can know like that, He restrains himself with/over all sorts of evil people do. But people who do evil, they are only waiting for the right time for them to be completely destroyed. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tahan diri = a lexical unit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">tahan diri = a lexical unit</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since God, wanting to show"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since God, wanting to show his wrath, and to make his power known, endured with much patience the objects of his wrath, which are prepared for destruction? skeúee: pots, same word as in the preceding verse. It shifts to a wider meaning here, "objects of wrath", but keeps the connection clear<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dia bekin bagitu, ko mau kasi tunju sang banya orang bilang, Dia mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang orang saparu. Dong tu, yang Dia su pili memang ko mau angka tinggi-tinggi. Deng Dia mau orang tau bilang, Dia sandiri hebat talalu.<bt>He did like that, in order to show many people that, He wants to show His mercy/pity to some people. They are the ones whom He chose ahead of time to lift up high (exalt, glorify). And He wants people to know that, He himself is extremely amazing/incredible. [EXEG: Gk: glory here 2x]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: He did this to make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: He did this to make the riches of his glory known on the objects of his mercy, whom he prepared in advance for glory. skeúee: just as in Verse 22, he continues the "pot" figure of speech to refer to people who were made with a certain purpose in mind. This time it's a good purpose<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>proeetoímasen: parallel to Verse 22, "ready", but with a twist -- God is the one who made them ready ahead of time eis dóxan: parallel to Verse 22's "ready fo get wipe out", but these other people are ready to be made glorious<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te kotong ni, yang Dia su pili memang ko jadi Dia pung orang dong. Kotong ni, saparu dari orang Yahudi, deng saparu dari suku-bangsa laen dong.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) we-inc here, are the ones whom He chose beforehand to become/be His people. We here, some are from the Yahudi people, and some from other ethnic groups.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For we are the ones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For we are the ones whom he called, not only from the Jews, but also from the Gentiles. ex ethnóon: from various ethnic groups (not Jewish)<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Dolu Tuhan pake Dia pung jubir Hosea, ko tulis so'al orang bukan Yahudi dong bilang,<bt>Long ago, God2 used his spokesperson Hosea, to write about non-Jews saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada orang yang dolu bukan Beta pung orang,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who were previously not My people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Beta mau pange sang dong bilang,<bt>but I am going to call them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Bosong tu, Beta pung orang.&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are My people&gt;.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng ada suku-bangsa yang dolu Beta sonde sayang,<bt>And there are ethnic groups which previously I didn't love,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Beta mau pange sang dong bilang,<bt>but I am going to call them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Bosong tu, suku-bangsa yang Beta sayang.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are ethnic groups whom I love.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="laos: nation, people, crowd, commoners LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">laos: nation, people, crowd, commoners LITERALLY: As he says in Hosea, "I will call them 'my people' who are not my people, and 'my loved one' who is not my loved one"<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 2:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dia ju tulis bilang,<bt>He also wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Di situ,<bt>&lt;&lt;There,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di tampa yang Tuhan su kasi tau sang dong bilang,<bt>in the place that God2 has told them about saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">&lt;Bosong tu, sonde jadi Beta pung orang!&gt;<bt>&lt;You-pl there, are not My people!&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Tuhan yang Idop mau kasi tau sang dong bilang,<bt>Later God2 who Lives will tell them saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Sakarang bosong su jadi Beta pung ana-ana!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;Now you have become My children!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 1:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia omong bagitu, tagal Dia kasian sang orang bukan Yahudi dong.<bt>He spoke like that, because He pitied/had compassion on the non-Yahudi people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And, &quot;It will happen that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And, "It will happen that in the place where it was said to them, 'You are not my people' they will be called 'children of the living God.'" erréthee autóis: it was said to them = God said to them, said in a respectful form that did not actually name God because that was kapu if you didn't have to name him<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Tuhan pung jubir laen, andia Yesaya, parná ba'eki so'al bangsa Isra'el bilang,<bt>Another spokesperson of God2's, that is Yesaya, once called out about the Israel ethnic group saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Biar orang Isra'el jadi satu mal'unuk pung,<bt>&lt;&lt;Even though the Israel people have become one heap/pile of alot [of people],</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke pasir di pante laut,<bt>like the sand on the sea shore,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">ma nanti Tuhan cuma kasi salamat sang dong sadiki orang sa,<bt>nevertheless later God2 will save only just a few of them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari dong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>from their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Isaiah crys out about Israel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Isaiah crys out about Israel, "Though the number of the Israelites is like the sand by the sea, only a small number will be saved. hypóleimma: a small number of survivors<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="28" />Te nanti dia pung waktu datang,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) the time is coming,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan putus parkara kasi samua orang di anteru dunya,<bt>for God2 to decide the cases for every person in the whole world,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te apa yang Tuhan su kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te apa yang Tuhan su kasi tau Dia mau bekin di anteru dunya,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke Dia su kasi tau memang.<bt>just as He has made known beforehand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma Dia sonde tunggu-tunggu,<bt>But He doesn't wait around/drag His heels,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te Dia bekin kalár deng capát!&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) He brings it to completion quickly!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: NRSV, NLT, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For the Lord will quickly"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For the Lord will quickly carry out and finish his word in the world."</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:27-28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 10:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dolu-dolu, Yesaya ju kasi tau so'al orang Yahudi dong bilang,<bt>Long ago, Yesaya also told about the Yahudi people saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kotong ontong,<bt>&lt;&lt;We-inc are fortunate,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan yang Paling Kuasa,<bt>because God2 who is Most Powerful,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi biar ko kotong pung turunan saparu dapa idop.<bt>allowed/permitted some of our descendants to live.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te kalo sonde bagitu, na,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if it wasn't like that, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kotong su abis buang,<bt>we would be completely annihilated,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke orang kota Sodom deng kota Gomora dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>just like the people of Sodom city and Gomora city.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: It is just as Isaiah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: It is just as Isaiah said before, "If the Almighty Lord had not left us descendants, we would have become like Sodom, and we would have been like Gomorrah." sabaoòth: a Hebrew word for large numbers of people, used in the Old Testament for the heavenly armies of angels or the armies formed on earth when God's people had to fight, and carried over into Greek in this quotation<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>spérma: seed, used here of descendants who can carry on the family line</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 1:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kabar Bae kasi bangsa Isra'el yang sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan<bt>Good News for the Israel ethnic group that doesn't want to listen to/obey God1</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Jadi kotong mau bilang apa? Bilang kata, orang bukan Yahudi dong dari mana-mana, yang dolu sonde cari-cari ko mau babae deng Tuhan, sakarang su babae deng Dia, tagal dong parcaya sang Yesus Kristus.<bt>So (consequently), what can we-inc say? [Do we] say that, the non Yahudi people from all over the place, who previously didn't seek to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, now they are in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, because they believe in Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then what shall we say?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then what shall we say? That the Gentiles, who did not go after righteousness, have obtained it, a righteousness which is by faith,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Padahal orang Isra'el dong, su coba bekin iko Musa pung atoran ko dong bisa babae deng Tuhan, ma sonde jadi-jadi ju.<bt>Whereas the Israel people, already tried to do according to Moses' law so that they could be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, but it just couldn't happen/eventuate/become reality. [EXEG: SSA, Moo, Morris]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** God's Law &gt; Moses' law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** God's Law &gt; Moses' law (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But Israel, who followed a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But Israel, who followed a law of righteousness, has not obtained it.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32-33" />Akurang ko dong sonde bisa babae deng Tuhan? Tagal dong cuma mau bekin iko atoran ko biar Dia tarima sang dong ke orang hati lurus, ma dong sonde parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Ais tingka ke dong ta'antok kaná di satu &lt;&lt;batu antok&gt;&gt;. Ini yang Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi pung maksud bilang,<bt>Why couldn't they be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2? Because they only wanted to follow the law so that He would accept them as a straight livered/righteous person, but they didn't believe in Yesus Kristus. So then it's as if they stumbled on a &lt;&lt;stumbling stone&gt;&gt;. This is what is meant in God2's Clean/Holy Writings saying, [EXEG: SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'antok ; antok = stumble &lt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">ta'antok ; antok = stumble &lt; BI antuk ; *** Law &gt; law (2009)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lia sini doo!<bt>&lt;&lt;Look over here!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Beta su taro satu Orang<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) I have put a Person</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">di gunung Sion, di kota Yerusalem.<bt>in mount Sion, in Yerusalem city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu Orang sama ke satu batu,<bt>That Person is like a stone,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bekin orang ta'antok.<bt>which makes people stumble.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma sapa yang parcaya sang Dia, na,<bt>But whoever believes in Him, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sonde usa malu.&gt;&gt;<bt>[they] don't need to be ashamed.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa. Itu batu tu, andia Yesus. Ma orang Isra'el dong tola buang sang Dia. Itu sama ke dong ta'antok, ais dong jato tagal itu batu.<bt>Naa. That aforementioned stone, is Yesus. But the Isra'el people rejected Him. That is like they stumbled, and then they fell (can be physical, moral, or social) because of that stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Why not? Because they did"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Why not? Because they did not go after it by faith, but by works. They stumbled over "the stumbling stone". LITERALLY: As it is written, "Look! I lay in Zion a stumblingstone and a rock to make them fall. And the one who trusts in him will never be [ashamed / disappointed]."<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung ahir, orang Isra'el dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Dia pung ahir, orang Isra'el dong su ta'antok, ais dong jato di itu batu. Itu batu tu, andia Yesus. Ma dong sonde mau parcaya sang Dia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara dong! Beta mau ko orang Isra'el dong, jadi karmana? Beta sambayang ko dong kasi biar Tuhan kasi salamat sang dong dari dong pung sala-sala. Kalo jadi bagitu, baru beta pung hati sanáng!<bt>Siblings! What do I desire to happen/become the Israel people? I pray that they will allow God2 to save them from their wrongs. If that would happen, only then my liver would be happy!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Brothers, my heart's desire and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Brothers, my heart's desire and prayer to God for them [the Israelites] is that they might be saved. eudokía: wish<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Beta bisa kasi tau so'al ini orang dong pung sifat: dong rajin ko mau iko sang Tuhan. Biar dong rajin bagitu, ma dong sonde mangarti jalan yang batúl.<bt>I can tell about these people's characteristics: they are diligent in wanting to follow God2. But even though they are diligent like that, they nevertheless don't understand the true/right/correct way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I can testify about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I can testify about them that they are zealous for God, but their zeal is not based on knowledge. epígnoosin: not based on true knowledge, their understanding of how to serve God is not right<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tagal dong sonde mangarti jalan idop yang batúl, yang bekin orang bisa babae deng Tuhan, andia ko dong buka dong pung jalan sandiri ko mau coba-coba babae deng Dia. Deng bagitu, dong sonde mau dengar sang Dia.<bt>Because they don't understand the life path that is right/correct/true, which enables people to be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2, that is why they forge their own path attempting (in vain--carried by reduplication) to be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. In that way, they don't want to listen to/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since thy were ignorant of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since thy were ignorant of the righteousness that comes from God, and going around to establish their own, they did not submit to God's righteousness. ouch hypetágeesan: they refused to submit<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kalo orang cuma bekin iko atoran sa, ko biar Tuhan Allah tarima sang dong, na, itu sonde cukup. Andia ko Kristus su bekin ganáp samua, ko biar kotong bisa babae deng Tuhan. Ais sakarang samua orang yang parcaya sang Kristus bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>If a person/someone only just follows/obeys the Law, so that God2 will accept them, na, that's not enough. That's why Kristus has made everything complete, so that we-inc can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2. So now all people who believe in Kristus can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God1. [EXEG: lots of debate in commentaries about scope of “law” in this verse. We go with “law of Moses” following SSA, Moo, Morris, TB, and context of vs.5, but leave it vague in same ways as Gk.] [DISCOURSE: 1. Problem, 2. Solution. 3. General principle or state of affairs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Atora &gt; atora (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** Atora &gt; atora (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Christ has brought the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Christ has brought the law to an end, so that there may be righteousness for everyone who believes. télos: the Law has no more value. Could also be that the goal that the Law was supposed to accomplish, Christ achieved for us; but in this chapter the emphasis is that just keeping the rules doesn't hack it<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan mau kasi salamat sang samua orang dari dong pung sala-sala<bt>God2 wants to save all people from their wrongs</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Naa, dolu ba'i Musa su kasi tunju jalan di Tulisan Barisi, ko orang bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah, asal dong bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran samua-samua. Dia tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang bekin iko ini Atoran samua-samua, nanti dong dapa idop yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [+shift] long ago Gf/Ff Musa already showed the way in the Clean/Holy Writings, so that people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God1, as.long as they do according to all-all (=every single one // or entire/totality) of God2's Regulations. He wrote saying, &lt;&lt;The person/whoever does according to every single one of these Regulations, later will obtain true life.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: here retain “God's Regs” because of how it's set up in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For Moses describes the righteousness"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For Moses describes the righteousness which is from the law, that "the person who does these things will live by them."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 18:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ju ada kasi tunju jalan laen bilang, orang bisa babae deng Tuhan Allah asal dong parcaya sang Kristus. Ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa tanya bilang, &lt;Sapa yang bisa nae pi sorga?&gt;&gt;&gt; (Itu tingka ke orang mau nae pi kasi tau sang Kristus bilang, botong manusia ada kapingin ko Dia turun datang ko kasi salamat sang botong.)<bt>But God's Clean/Holy Writings also shows another way saying, people can be in a reciprocally good relationship with God2 as.long as they believe in Kristus. It is written saying, &lt;&lt;It's not necessary to ask saying, &lt;So who will be able to go up to heaven?&gt;&gt;&gt; (That is as if people/person/someone wants to go up to tell Kristus saying, we-exc humans are desiring that He comes down to save/rescue us.) [EXEG: clarify from high level context. NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the righteousness that is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the righteousness that is from faith says, "Do not say in your heart, 'Who will ascend into heaven?'" (that is, to bring Christ down),</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Tulisan Barisi ju ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa tanya bilang, &lt;Sapa yang mau turun pi Lobang Naraka, di tampa orang mati dong?&gt;&gt;&gt; (Itu tingka ke orang mau turun pi ko bawa nae sang Kristus kambali dari Dia pung mati ko Dia kasi salamat sang kotong.)<bt>The Holy Writings also writes saying, &lt;&lt;It's not necessary to ask saying, &lt;So who wants to/is going to go down to Hell Hole, to the place of dead people?&gt;&gt;&gt; (That is as if someone wants to go down to bring Kristus back up from His death to save us.) [EXEG: SSA; Problem: this is a misquote of Deut 30:13 (vs. 6 is from 30:12). Rather than say this is not quoting scripture (remove Barisi from the KM), which would skew the focus and raise unhelpful questions, note the following: In the grammar of the Gk, Paul is clearly including/subsuming the contents of vs.7 under his quote margin in vs.5, so the idea of a misquote of Deut 30:13 is both misrepresenting Paul and covering up or correcting his apparent ‘mistake’. What Paul has done here is a very common rabbinic thing to do. Moo points out that it is not as sloppy a misquote as it first appears in English, and that there are Aramaic paraphrases and other sources that do about the same thing, equating and substituting ‘abyss’ with ‘sea’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abysson: the Abyss of Hell LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">abysson: the Abyss of Hell LITERALLY: Or, "'Who will descend into the deep?'" (That is to bring Christ up from the dead).<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Sonde usa bagitu! Te di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ju ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan pung pasán su ada di lu pung muka-idong! Te itu pasán ada di lu pung mulu deng lu pung hati.&gt;&gt; Itu pasán yang kotong kasi tau orang tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu mau cari salamat, na, lu musti parcaya sang Kristus!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's not necessary! Cuz (elaboration: grounds) in God2's Holy Writings it also is written saying, &lt;&lt;God's message is right in front of our nose! Cuz/for (elaboration) that message is already in your-sg mouth and in your liver.&gt;&gt; That is the message which we have told people says, “If you want to be saved, na, you-sg must believe in Kristus!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rheema: (specific) word, message, instructions LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">rheema: (specific) word, message, instructions LITERALLY: But what does it say? "The [word / message] is near you; it is in your mouth and in your heart", that is, the [word / message] of faith which we are proclaiming.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 30:12-14</note><v n="9" />Kalo lu mangaku pake lu pung mulu sandiri bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus tu, beta pung Bos yang hak parenta sang beta,&gt;&gt; deng lu parcaya dalam lu pung hati bilang, Tuhan Allah su kasi idop kambali sang Yesus Kristus dari Dia pung mati, na, Tuhan kasi salamat sang lu dari lu pung sala dong pung kuasa.<bt>If you-sg acknowledge/confess using your own mouth saying, &lt;&lt;That [known info] Yesus, is my Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over me,&gt;&gt; and you believe in your liver saying, God1 has caused Yesus Kristus to live again from His death, na, God2 will save you from your wrongs/sins. [NOTE to daughter translations: Collocation: Some languages can only confess wrong [negative], not use this word to affirm s.t. positive (e.g. not confess that Jesus is Lord, but profess/declare...)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homologeesees: show yourself in agreement with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">homologeesees: show yourself in agreement with an idea. CHECK PARALLELS. LITERALLY: That if you [confess / profess] with your mouth "Jesus is Lord", and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te kalo lu pake lu pung hati ko parcaya sang Kristus, Tuhan cap ame sang lu bilang, orang hati lurus yang babae deng Dia. Deng kalo lu pake lu pung mulu ko mangaku bilang, Yesus jadi lu pung Bos yang hak parenta sang lu, Tuhan mau kasi salamat sang lu dari lu pung sala dong pung kuasa.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if you-sg use your liver to believe in Kristus, God2 stamps/brands/categorises you as a *righteous person who is in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. And if you use your mouth to acknowledge that, Yesus is your Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over you, God2 will save you from the power of your wrongs. [NOTE to daughter translations: vs.9-10 retain chiasmus structure from Gk A B B A, Check if your lg needs to make it A B A B, or A A B B, but not lose the force of it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo lu pake lu pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Te kalo lu pake lu pung hati ko parcaya sang Tuhan, Dia bekin lu babae deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For it is with your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For it is with your heart that you believe and are justified, and it is with your mouth that you confess and are saved.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, nanti sonde dapa malu, te Tuhan mau bekin jadi, samua hal yang Dia su omong.&gt;&gt;<bt>In God2's Holy Writings it is written saying, &lt;&lt;A/the person/whoever believes in God1, later will not be ashamed, cuz/for (elaboration) God2 wants to do everything which He has said.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: Last clause necessary for making sense in context, higher level; also HCE; SSA notes “In some languages a statement of the reason for or reference of the disappointment may be needed.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: As the Scripture says, &quot;Whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: As the Scripture says, "Whoever believes in him [God] will not be [put to shame / disappointed]." ou kataischyntheésetai: will not be put to shame<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:16</note><v n="12" />Orang Yahudi, deng orang bukan Yahudi dong, sama. Sonde ada beda. Te cuma ada satu Bos, deng Dia jadi Bos kasi samua suku-bangsa. Dia mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae bam-banya kasi samua orang yang minta Dia tolong sang dong.<bt>The Yahudi people, and the non Yahudi people, are the same. There is no difference. Cuz/for (elaboration) there is only one Boss, and He is Boss for all ethnic groups. He wants to abundantly show His good liver (=grace) to all people who request Him to help them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For there is no difference"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For there is no difference between Jew and Gentile. The same Lord is Lord of all, and richly blesses all who call on him.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te di Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua orang yang minta tolong sang Tuhan, nanti Dia kasi salamat sang dong dari dong pung sala dong pung kuasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) in the Holy Writings it is written saying, &lt;&lt;All people who request help from God2, later He will save them from the power of their wrongs.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For &quot;Everyone who calls on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For "Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved." ónoma: name, the Lord himself, in Jewish usage it focusses on his essential character -- the name means something, and a well-applied name tells you what a person is like<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma karmana orang bisa minta tolong sang satu orang, kalo dong balóm parcaya sang dia? Deng karmana dong bisa parcaya sang dia, kalo dong sonde parná dengar so'al dia? Karmana dong bisa dengar so'al dia, kalo sonde ada orang yang kasi tau sang dong?<bt>But how can people request help from a person, if they don't believe in him? And how can they believe in him, if they have never heard about him? How can they hear about him, if there is no one who tells them?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then how will they call"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then how will they call on the one they have not believed in? And how can they believe in the one they have not heard of. And how can they hear without someone preaching to them?</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Karmana dong bisa kasi tau orang, kalo sonde ada yang utus sang dong? Di Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang bawa datang kabar bae, dong pung datang tu, talalu bagus!&gt;&gt;<bt>How can they tell people, if there is no one who commissions them/sends them out on a task like that? In the Holy Writings it is written [CHECK for UNS: should this be tatulis?] saying, &lt;&lt;If people bring the good news, their arrival/coming, is exceeding good!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: feet &gt; arrival, see Morris, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And how can they preach"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And how can they preach unless they are sent? As it is written, "How beautiful are the feet of those who bring good news!"</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma bosong su tau bilang, ada orang Isra'el saparu yang sonde mau dengar-dengar Tuhan pung Kabar Bae. Te Tuhan pung jubir Yesaya ada tulis bilang,<bt>But you-pl already know that, there are some Israel people who don't want to listen to/obey God2's Good News. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2's spokesperson Yesaya writes saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bos, é!<bt>&lt;&lt;Boss, e!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Orang dong sonde mau parcaya pasán<bt>People don't want to believe the message</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang dong su dengar dari botong!&gt;&gt;<bt>which they have heard from us-exc!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But not all the Israelites"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But not all the Israelites responded to the good news. For Isaiah says, "Lord, who has believed our message?" hypeékousan: obeyed<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Jadi, kalo mau parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, na, musti dengar Dia pung Kata-kata dolo. Deng kalo dong mau dengar Tuhan pung pasán, na, musti dengar so'al Kristus dolo.<bt>So (consequently), if [a person/you] want to believe in God1, na, [he/she/you] must hear His Words first. And if they want to hear/obey God2's message, na, [they] must hear about Kristus first. [NOTE to daughter translations: experiment to see which sequencing works best for your RL/UNS's. /Orang musti dengar so'al Kristus dolo, baru dong bisa parcaya sang Dia. Ma musti ada yang kasi tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata dolu, baru dong bisa dengar./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So then faith comes by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So then faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of Christ. ára: back to the main point<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>Christóu: UBS takes it as "the message about Christ" or "preaching about Christ", not "checking out what Christ actually said"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Beta tanya coba bagini: mangkali bosong ada pikir bilang, orang Isra'el dong sonde parná dengar so'al Kristus, ko? Tantu dong su dengar! Sama ke ada tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi dari dolu bilang,<bt>I want to ask like this: perhaps/probably you-pl are thinking that, the Israel people have never heard about Kristus, right? Of course they've heard! Just like what is written in God2's Holy Writings from long ago saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan pung jubir dong pung pasán so'al Tuhan<bt>&lt;&lt;God2's spokespeople's message about God2 [EXEG: Gk “their voice” Is this to be taken in the context of Ps. 19 where it is the message of creation, or in the context of vs.14-17 above, where it is the msg of salvation brought by those who bring God's msg? Grammatically in the context of Romans, “their voice” goes back to the bringers of God's message of salvation in vs.14-17, irrespective of how it's used in Psalms. Moo points out “The implied object of the verb “heard” in Paul’s question must be “the word of Christ”; “their voice” and “their words” in the Psalm verse must then refer to the voices and words of Christian preachers (see vv. 14-16). Paul is not, then, simply using the text according to its original meaning. Note also TB “the voices of the bringers of the message…” The context in the Psalms doesn't trump the context in Romans in this instance. I (CEG) think the NLT solution disrupts and misses the flow of the argument in chapters 7-8.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su tasiar pi anteru dunya;<bt>has spread around the entire world;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong pung kata-kata<bt>Their words</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su sampe di dunya pung huk-huk.&gt;&gt;<bt>have arrived at the world's corners (=farthest reaches).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But I ask, &quot;Didn't they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But I ask, "Didn't they hear?" Yes, of course! "Their voice has gone out into all the earth; their words to the ends of the world." oikouménees: inhabited world, not just the physical world<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 19:5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Beta mau tanya lai satu hal bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang Isra'el dong sonde mangarti Tuhan pung jalan, ko?&gt;&gt; Ba'i Musa tu, orang partama yang tulis so'al itu hal bilang, Tuhan kasi tau orang Isra'el bagini:<bt>I want to ask more thing saying, &lt;&lt;The Israel people don't understand God's path/way, right?&gt;&gt; That aforementioned Gf/Ff Musa, was the first person who wrote about that matter saying, God2 told the people of Isra'el like this: [EXEG: SSA, Morris, Moo]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta mau bekin satu hal<bt>&lt;&lt;I want to do one thing</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi orang suku-bangsa laen dong.<bt>for people of other ethnic groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Itu hal nanti bekin bosong iri hati.<bt>That thing will make your-pl livers jealous.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Beta mau bekin satu hal ju,<bt>And I want to do one thing,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi orang yang bosong anggap ke otak kea.<bt>for people whom you consider turtle-brained (dumb as an turtle/ox).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu hal nanti bekin bosong makan gigi.&gt;&gt;<bt>That thing will make you grind your teeth (=furious).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Again I ask, &quot;Didn't Israel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Again I ask, "Didn't Israel [know / understand]?" First, Moses says, "I will make you jealous [by / of] those that are not a people, and I will anger you by a foolish nation." asynétooi: who don't understand anything, stupid<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:21</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dari balakang, ba'i Yesaya tulis taráng-taráng so'al orang bukan Yahudi bilang,<bt>Later on, Gf/Ff Yesaya wrote in a clear manner about non-Jews saying, [EXEG: SSA, Morris, Moo]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada orang yang dolu sonde cari-cari sang Beta,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who previously didn't (make any effort to--implied by reduplication) seek Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma dong su dapa katumu sang Beta.<bt>but (contrary to expectation) they have been able to meet Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ada orang yang dolu sonde minta ko lia sang Beta,<bt>There are people who previously didn't request to see Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma Beta su kasi tunju diri sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>but I will nevertheless reveal Myself to them.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Then Isaiah boldly says, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Then Isaiah boldly says, "I was found by those who did not seek me; I revealed myself to those who did not ask for me."</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 65:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ma so'al orang Isra'el, Tuhan su kasi tau bagini:<bt>But about the Israel people, God2 has already told like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Siang-malam, Beta buka Beta pung tangan lebar-lebar,<bt>&lt;&lt;Night-and-day, I open My arms/hands widely,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko tunggu-tunggu orang Isra'el dong datang di Beta.<bt>waiting eagerly for the Israel people to come to Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma dong sonde mau dengar sang Beta,<bt>But they don't want to listen to/obey Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dong ju suka bamalawan sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>and they also like to oppose Me.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But about Israel, he says,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But about Israel, he says, "All day long I have held out my hands to a disobedient and obstinate people." antilégonta: more like direct rebellion, not just complaining.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 65:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah kasian sang orang Isra'el dong<bt>God1 has compassion/pity on the Israel people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi beta mau tanya bagini: mangkali bosong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal orang Isra'el sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan Allah, andia ko Dia su tola buang sang dong.&gt;&gt; Bagitu, ko? Sonde! Te beta ju dari dong! Beta ni, dari suku Benyamin. Benyamin pung bapa, Yakob. Dia pung ba'i, Isak. Isak pung bapa, Abraham yang jadi samua orang Isra'el dong pung nene-moyang.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: perhaps/probably you are thinking, “Because the people of Isra'el do not want to listen to/obey God1, that is why He has rejected them.” Like that, right? No! Cuz/for (elaboration) I am also one of them! I here, am from the Benyamin tribe. Benyamin's father, was Yakob. His grandfather, was Isak. Isak's father, was Abraham, who is ancestor of all the Israel people. [EXEG: Gk is Israelite, Abraham, Benjamin. If Israelite is to be taken as a reference to Jacob, target language norms require they be reordered. NLT has attractive solution in taking Israelite = Jew. But just mentioning Abraham and Benjamin in KM doesn't work, because the people know just enough to be dangerous. Local cultures around eastern Indonesia revere the ultimate founding father most (and rarely even mention others outside genealogies, unless with reference to some legendary exploit). and Paul clearly ascribes the founding identity of the Jews with Abraham, and sets up numerous arguments in Romans built on that, without mentioning Jacob. So shifting to elevate Jacob as the founding ancestor, rather than Abraham, I think is actually problematic in the context of Romans.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[DISCUSS: use of /orang Yahudi/ vs."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">[DISCUSS: use of /orang Yahudi/ vs. /orang Isra'el/ vs. mixed.] *** note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meè apoósato: he didn't push them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">meè apoósato: he didn't push them away, did he? reject, refuse to listen Benjamin was Abraham's great grandson: Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, Benjamin. The blood lines took their traditional names from Benjamin and his brothers<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: I ask, then, has God rejected his people? By no means! I myself am an Israelite, a descendant of Abraham, a member of the tribe of Benjamin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, beta mau tanya bagini: Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, beta mau tanya bagini: Tuhan Allah su tola buang Dia pung orang Isra'el, ko? Sonde! Te beta ju dari dong! Beta ni, dari suku Benyamin. Benyamin pung bapa, Yakob. Dia pung ba'i, Isak. Isak pung bapa, Abraham, yang jadi samua orang Isra'el dong pung nene-moyang.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Filipi 3:5</note><v n="2" />Tuhan Allah sonde parná tola buang Dia pung orang dong. Dong tu, yang Dia kanál memang dari dolu-dolu. Bosong masi inga, ko sonde, apa yang tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi so'al ba'i Elia? Dia mangomel sang Tuhan so'al orang Isra'el, ju dia minta ko Tuhan kasi hukum sang dong,<bt>God2 has never completely rejected his people. They are the ones He knew/recognized beforehand from long ago. You-pl still remember, right?, what was written in God2's Holy Writings about Gf/Ff Elia? He complained/grumbled to God2 about the Israel people, and he requested that God punish them, [EXEG: HCE, Morris: take action against]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: God has not rejected his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: God has not rejected his people whom he foreknew. Do you not know what the scripture says of Elijah, how he pleads with God against Israel?</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />bilang,<bt>saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bos! Ini orang dong bunu bekin mati jubir-jubir,<bt>&lt;&lt;Boss! These people murder killing spokespersons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang Bos kirim datang.<bt>whom Boss  (=you) have sent.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong ju bongkar kasi ancor meja korban,<bt>They also take.apart destroy the sacrifice table (=altar),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di tampa orang sémba sang Bos.<bt>in the place/s where people worship Boss (=you).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dari Tuhan pung jubir dong samua,<bt>From among all of God2's spokespersons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">cuma beta sandiri sa yang masi idop.<bt>only just I alone who still lives.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Ma dong ju cari jalan lai,<bt>But they are also looking for ways again,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko mau bunu bekin mati sang beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>to try and murder killing me!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “Lord, they have killed your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: “Lord, they have killed your prophets, they have demolished your altars; I alone am left, and they are seeking my life.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 19:10, 14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma Tuhan manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung omong tu, sala! Te Beta pung orang yang sémba sang Beta, masi ada tuju ribu orang. Dong batahan karás deng sonde songgo sang Ba'al!&gt;&gt;<bt>But God1 responded/replied saying like this: &lt;&lt;What you are saying, is wrong! Cuz/for (elaboration) My people who worship Me, there are still seven thousand people. They endure strongly and don't [traditional]worship Ba'al!&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: if no /songgo/ word, try /sémba sang Ba'al pung patong/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng sonde songgo sang Beta pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">deng sonde songgo sang Beta pung musu, Ba'al!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But what is the divine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: But what is the divine reply to him? “I have kept for myself seven thousand who have not bowed the knee to Baal.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Bagitu ju, sakarang. Te sonde samua orang Yahudi yang bale balakang sang Tuhan Allah. Masi sisa sadiki orang dari botong yang Tuhan su pili mau kasi salamat, tagal Dia mau kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang botong, bukan tagal botong ada bekin hal bae! Te kalo Dia <span class="Italic">musti</span> pili sang botong tagal botong pung bekin bae, dia pung arti bilang, Dia sonde bisa putus ko mau kasi tunju, ko, sonde kasi tunju, Dia pung hati bae sang botong. Kalo bagitu, dia pung nama su bukan &lt;kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae&gt; lai.<bt>It's like that also, now. Cuz/for (elaboration) not all Yahudi people have turned their backs on God1. There still remains a few people from amongst us-exc (includes Paul) whom God2 has chosen to save, because He wants to show His good liver=grace to us, not because we have done good things! Cuz/for (elaboration) if He <span class="Italic">must</span> choose us because of our good deeds, that means, He can't decide to show, or not show, His good liver to us, or not. If that's the case, its name is no longer &lt;show His good liver (= grace)&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="léimma: a few people left cháritos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">léimma: a few people left cháritos: just because he wants to, because he feels kindly toward them, acts graciously. Refers to his character, that he is basically for us and wants us to succeed<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: So too at the present time there is a remnant, chosen by grace. khariti: usually "like do good tings fo dem", but here the "give um chance" (mercy) component needs to be foregrounded to fit in with the rest of the context.<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>NRSV: But if it is by grace, it is no longer on the basis of works, otherwise grace would no longer be grace.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 7:7-8</note><v n="7" />Jadi dia pung ujung-ujung bagini: banya orang Yahudi cari-cari ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang dong, ko dong ju bisa babae deng Dia. Ma sonde tau dapa-dapa, tagal dong pung hati bakarás deng sonde mau dengar sang Dia. Ma ada saparu yang dapa. Dong tu, andia yang Tuhan su pili memang.<bt>So (consequently), in the end, it's like this: many Yahudi people are seeking/trying to find ways for God to show His good liver = grace to them, so that they can be in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. But they don't know how to obtain it/unable to obtain it, because their livers are hardened and the don't want to listen to/obey Him. But there are some who obtain it. They are the ones whom God already chose beforehand [EXEG: NLT].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What then? Israel failed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: What then? Israel failed to obtain what it was seeking. The elect obtained it, but the rest were hardened,</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis so'al itu orang kapala batu dong bilang,<bt>In God2's Holy Writings is written about those rock heads (=stubborn) saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan kasi sang dong,<bt>&lt;&lt;God2 gave them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mata yang sonde bisa dapa lia,<bt>eyes which cannot see,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">talinga yang sonde bisa dapa dengar,<bt>ears which cannot hear,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng otak kea yang sonde bisa pikir.<bt>and turtle brains which cannot think.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi dong sonde mangarti yang batúl,<bt>So (consequently), they don't understand what is true/right/correct,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe ini hari ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>even until this day.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katanýxeoos: numbness, insensibility, insensitivity NRSV: as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">katanýxeoos: numbness, insensibility, insensitivity NRSV: as it is written, “God gave them a sluggish spirit, eyes that would not see and ears that would not hear, down to this very day.”<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 29:4, Yesaya 29:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Raja Daud ju tulis so'al bangsa Yahudi dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>King Daud also wrote about the Yahudi people in the Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Biar ko dong bapesta di dong pung meja sandiri.<bt>&lt;&lt;Just let them [dismissive] feast at their own table.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te dong pung pesta sandiri yang hiki bale sang dong,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) it will be their own feast that ensnares them in return,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko dong pikir samua su bae.<bt>so that they think everything is good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng dong pung harta sandiri yang bekin dong ta'antok.<bt>And their own belongings which make them stumble. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And David says, “Let their"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: And David says, “Let their table become a snare and a trap, a stumbling block and a retribution for them;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Biar dong pung mata jadi galáp,<bt>Just let their [dismissive] eyes become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong sonde usa lia apa-apa!<bt>so they don't need to see anything!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko dong pikol babán barát tarús,<bt>Just let them carry heavy burdens all the time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong pung balakang tulang tamba bongko!&gt;&gt;<bt>so their back bones become even more bent over!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babongko &lt; bongko ; balakang tulang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">babongko &lt; bongko ; balakang tulang = backbone</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: let their eyes be darkened"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: let their eyes be darkened so that they cannot see, and keep their backs forever bent.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:23-24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan mau kasi salamat orang bukan Yahudi ju<bt>God2 wants to save non Yahudi people also,</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Jadi beta mau tanya bagini: akurang ko orang Yahudi dong ta'antok? Dong su jato, ko? Sonde! Ma tagal dong sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan Allah, deng sonde mau parcaya sang Kristus, itu buka jalan kasi orang bukan Yahudi dong ko bisa dapa salamat dari dong pung sala-sala. Deng Dia bekin bagitu, Tuhan mau ko orang Yahudi dong camburu, ais kambali ko iko sang Dia lai.<bt>So (consequently), I want to ask like this: why did the Yahudi people stumble? They've fallen, right? No! But because they don't want to listen to/obey God, and don't want to believe in Kristus, that opens the path for non Yahudi people to be able to be saved from their wrongs. By doing like that, God2 wants for the Yahudi people to be jealous/envious, and so return to follow/obey2 Him again. [EXEG: NLT, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaka'e ; kana batu = ta'antok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">kaka'e ; kana batu = ta'antok</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So I ask, have they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: So I ask, have they stumbled so as to fall? By no means! But through their stumbling salvation has come to the Gentiles, so as to make Israel jealous.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, beta mau tanya, bagini: akurang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jadi, beta mau tanya, bagini: akurang ko orang Yahudi dong ta'antok? Dong su jato, ko? Sonde! Ma tagal dong langgar Tuhan pung Atoran, deng sonde parcaya sang Dia, itu buka jalan kasi orang bukan Yahudi dong ko bisa dapa salamat dari dong pung sala-sala. Itu yang bekin orang Yahudi dong camburu.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Su jalás bilang, orang Yahudi dong langgar apa yang batúl. Andia ko orang laen dari anteru dunya bisa rasa Tuhan pung hati bae. Jadi orang Yahudi dong, rugi bésar. Ma itu bekin orang bukan Yahudi dong ontong bésar. Naa, lama-lama, kalo samua orang Yahudi ju babae kambali deng Tuhan, itu lebe bae lai!<bt>It's clear that, the Yahudi people violated what was right/true. That's why other people from the entire world can taste/sense/experience God2's good liver (=grace). So (consequently), the Yahudi people, lose out in a big way. But that makes the non Yahudi people gain an advantage/benefit in a big way. Now [+shift], eventually, if all the Yahudi people were also to be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2, that would be even better!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now if their stumbling means"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now if their stumbling means riches for the world, and if their defeat means riches for Gentiles, how much more will their full inclusion mean!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Naa! Beta mau kasi tau sang bosong yang bukan orang Yahudi, bagini: Tuhan su utus sang beta ko jalan pi kasi tau sang bosong so'al Dia pung Kabar Bae. Andia ko beta pasang kaki ko kasi jalan ini karjá yang talalu bae ni.<bt>So! I want to tell you-pl who are non Yahudi people, like this: God2 has commissioned me to go tell you about His Good News. That's why I plant my feet (=strive very hard) to carry out this work which is extremely good. [EXEG: SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now I am speaking to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now I am speaking to you Gentiles. Inasmuch then as I am an apostle to the Gentiles, I glorify my ministry</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te kalo beta kasi jalan ini karjá deng bae, jang sampe beta bekin beta pung orang Yahudi sandiri camburu, sampe dong saparu dapa salamat dari dong pung sala-sala.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if I carry out this work well, possibly I will make my own Yahudi people jealous, to the point that some of them get saved from their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Can jang-jang be positive?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Can jang-jang be positive?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parazeeloósoo: get them so worked up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">parazeeloósoo: get them so worked up they'll start thinking about it NRSV: in order to make my own people jealous, and thus save some of them.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Waktu Tuhan tola buang Dia pung orang Yahudi sandiri, itu buka jalan ko orang laen dong dapa sampat ko dong bisa maso jadi Tuhan pung orang. Ma nanti, andekata dong badame kambali deng Tuhan, itu talalu bagus. Te itu sama ke dong su idop kambali dari dong pung mati!<bt>When God2 rejected His own Yahudi people, that opened the path so that other people could get the opportunity so that they could enter becoming God2's people. But later, if.perchance [+hypothetical] they reconcile with God, that is sooo good. Cuz (elaboration) that will be as if they have come back to life again from their deaths!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if their rejection is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if their rejection is the reconciliation of the world, what will their acceptance be but life from the dead!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ame conto dari orang mau bekin roti. Kalo dia ame tarigu sadiki ko sarakan pi sang Tuhan, nanti itu roti dong samua ju jadi Dia pung milik yang barisi. Deng kalo orang sarakan pohon pung akar satu ko jadi ulu hasil kasi Tuhan, nanti itu pohon anteru ju jadi Dia pung milik yang barisi.<bt>Take the example of a person wanting to make bread. If s/he takes a bit of flour and hands.it.over to God2, later that all the bread [rolls/loaves-implicit: from that dough/flour] will be His possession that is clean/holy. And if a person hands.over a tree's root/s to become the first product (presented in thanksgiving) for God, later that entire tree will aso be His possession that is clean/holy. [EXEG: SSA; Note: Morris notes that Num. 15:20-21 is talking about ground meal &gt; tarigu, but in the OT it is the bread that is consecrated, not the dough. The NLT seems to be jumping the gun on Paul a bit here. He's working towards that later, but here he's only giving a picture for comparison for starting in that direction.] [NOTE to daughter translations (to help picture context): Gk uses “part of dough” and “whole batch”. Picture a Jewish priest in NYC blessing one ball of uncooked dough, with the result that the whole batch of 600 bagels is blessed (that's what they actually do).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="order of anteru = seluruh ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">order of anteru = seluruh ; ulu hasil ; bua sulung (KM) ; *** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparkhee: first fruits NRSV: If the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">aparkhee: first fruits NRSV: If the part of the dough offered as first fruits is holy, then the whole batch is holy; and if the root is holy, then the branches also are holy.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Beta mau banding bangsa Yahudi deng satu pohon saitun yang ada idop di kabón. Tuhan Allah su potong buang itu pohon pung tangke saparu. Ma bosong yang bukan Yahudi dong, sama ke saitun utan. Ais Tuhan su potong ame bosong pung tangke saparu ko tempel pasang di itu pohon dalam kabón. Deng bagitu, tangke dari pohon di luar, tarima ame dia pung idop dari pohon di dalam. Itu sama ke bosong yang bukan Yahudi dong, ju tarima ame Tuhan pung hati bae, yang Dia mau kasi sang Dia pung orang Yahudi dong.<bt>I want to compare the Yahudi ethnic group with an olive tree that lives/grows in a garden. God1 already cut and threw away some of that tree's branches. But you who are not Yahudi, are like a wild/jungle olive. So then God already cut keeping some of your-pl branches in order to patch/attach/fasten [you] on that tree in the garden. In that way, the branches from the tree outside, receive their life from the tree inside. That is the same as you who are not Yahudi, also receiving God2's good liver (=grace), which He wants to give to His Yahudi people. [EXEG: NLT] [NOTE to daughter translations: this is not like there is a beringin tree that happens to be in your garden, and one in the hutan, but one is deliberately planted and cared for, and the other grows wild. The one has larger and sweeter fruit. If a problem, try “dong piara” rather than “ada idop” in the first sentence.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tatanam = 1) buried (uang tatanam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">tatanam = 1) buried (uang tatanam di tana,) 2) unmovable, fixed ; *** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But if some of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: But if some of the branches were broken off, and you, a wild olive shoot, were grafted in their place to share the rich root of the olive tree,</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ma ati-ati, ó! Jang kapala bésar, pikir bosong dari luar tu lebe bae dari itu tangke yang Tuhan su potong buang dong! Kalo lu mau angka-angka diri, lu jang lupa, te lu cuma satu tangke sa! Bukan lu yang bekin kuat itu pohon. Te akar yang bekin pohon jadi kuat na!<bt>But be careful, ó! Don't get big headed, thinking you who are from outside are better than those branches which God2 has cut &amp; thrown away! If you-sg want to lift (=praise) yourself up, don't forget, cuz/for (elaboration) you are only just one branch! It's not you who is making that tree strong. Cuz/for (elaboration) its the roots that make that tree strong [+speaker attitude--it's obviously...]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bastázeis: provide continued assistance (not just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">bastázeis: provide continued assistance (not just physical support) NRSV: do not boast over the branches. If you do boast, remember that it is not you that support the root, but the root that supports you.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo lu mau angka-angka diri, jang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Kalo lu mau angka-angka diri, jang lupa, bilang, bukan lu yang bekin kuat itu pohon. Te lu cuma satu tangke sa! Ko akar yang bekin pohon jadi kuat na!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Lu mungkin mau bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan potong buang satu tangke dari pohon yang idop dalam Dia pung kabón, ko Dia bisa tempel kambali sang beta di situ, ko ganti itu tangke lama.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-sg probably want to say, &lt;&lt;God2 cut &amp; threw away one branch from the tree that lives in His garden, so that He can patch/stick/attach me instead there, to replace that older branch.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: You will say, “Branches were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: You will say, “Branches were broken off so that I might be grafted in.”</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Itu batúl. Ma jang lupa bilang, Tuhan su potong buang itu tangke dong, tagal dong sonde parcaya sang Kristus. Deng lu ganti sang dong, tagal lu ada parcaya sang Dia. Jadi jang kapala bésar! Lebe bae, lu ati-ati, deng jang macam-macam!<bt>That's true. But don't forget that, God2 already cut &amp; threw away those branches, because they did not believe in Kristus. And you replaced them, because you are believing in Him. So (consequently), don't get big headed! It's better, you be careful, and don't do things you shouldn't [+negative value]! [EXEG: SSA, MC; NEB. Gk /phobos/ 1) fear; 2) awe. Note NLT, CEV, TB, and context (the threat of being ‘cut off’) favour going with the primary sense here. Morris accepts the former, but prefers the latter. Moo describes this fear/awe as “and take up an attitude of fear. This basic biblical concept combines reverential respect for the God of majesty and glory with a healthy concern to continue to live out of the grace of God in our lives.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: That is true. They were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: That is true. They were broken off because of their unbelief, but you stand only through faith. So do not become proud, but stand in awe.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te orang Yahudi dong, sama ke tangke asli yang batumbu lebe dolo. Ma Tuhan sonde kasi biar dong batahan lama di situ. Jadi, kalo lu sonde parcaya sang Dia tarús, jang harap Dia mau kasi biar lu batahan di situ!<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) the Yahudi people, are like the orginal branches which grew first. But God2 did not allow them to endure there long. So (consequently), if you-pl don't continue believing in Him, don't hope He will allow you to remain there!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if God did not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if God did not spare the natural branches, perhaps he will not spare you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Jadi bosong musti pikir bae-bae dolo. Tuhan ada pung hati bae. Ma Dia ju tau kasi hukuman yang barát. Dia nanti kasi hukum orang yang su jato, yang sonde babae deng Dia. Ma kasi bosong yang bukan orang Yahudi dong, Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong, asal bosong ta'ika tarús deng Dia, deng kasi biar Dia bekin yang bae kasi sang bosong. Ma kalo bosong sonde kasi biar Dia bekin bagitu, Dia ju mau potong buang sang bosong dari Dia pung pohon.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must think carefully. God has a good liver (=is gracious/kind/generous). But He also knows how to give out heavy punishment. He later will punish the people who have fallen, who are not in a reciprocally good relationship with Him. But for you who are not Yahudi people, God2 shows His good liver to you, as.long as you remain bound/linked with Him, and allow Him to do what is good for you-pl. But if you don't allow Him to do like that, He also will cut &amp; throw away you from His tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Note then the kindness and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Note then the kindness and the severity of God: severity toward those who have fallen, but God's kindness toward you, provided you continue in his kindness; otherwise you also will be cut off.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Bagitu ju deng orang Yahudi dong. Kalo dong tobat, ko mulai parcaya sang Kristus, nanti Tuhan mau tempel kambali sang dong di pohon asli tu. Ko Dia ada pung kuasa ko bisa bekin bagitu na!<bt>Like that also with the Yahudi people. If they repent, in order to start believing in Kristus, later God2 will patch/attach them back on that original tree. Because He obviously has power to do like that! [EXEG: SSA, MC; see vs. 20.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And even those of Israel,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: And even those of Israel, if they do not persist in unbelief, will be grafted in, for God has the power to graft them in again.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Te bosong yang bukan orang Yahudi, sama ke tangke dari saitun utan yang dolu batumbu liar di luar kabón. Ma Tuhan pili ame sang bosong ko Dia tempel di pohon saitun yang bae, yang Dia tanam di Dia pung kabón, biar ko pohon utan laen sandiri, deng pohon kabón laen sandiri. Te kalo orang bukan Yahudi sa bisa jadi bagitu, apalai orang Yahudi. Itu lebe bisa lai, kalo Tuhan tempel kambali sang dong di dong pung pohon asal.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) you-pl who are not Yahudi people, are the same as the branch from a jungle/wild olive that previously grew wild outside the garden. But God2 chose you-pl in order to patch/attach on the good olive tree, which He planted in His garden, even though the wild tree is different/separate, and the garden tree is different/separate. Cuz/for (elaboration) if people who are not just Yahudi can become like that, even.more.so.with Yahudi people. It's even more possible, if God patches/attaches them again onto their original tree.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if you have been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if you have been cut from what is by nature a wild olive tree and grafted, contrary to nature, into a cultivated olive tree, how much more will these natural branches be grafted back into their own olive tree.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nanti orang Yahudi dong babae kambali deng Tuhan<bt>Later the Yahudi people will be in a reciprocally good relationship again with God2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Sodara di Roma dong! Bosong musti mangarti ini hal yang dolu jadi rahasia. Te kalo bosong mangarti sang dia, bosong jang kapala bésar, pikir bilang, bosong pintar. Te bagini: sakarang orang Yahudi dong hati karás, deng sonde mau parcaya sang Kristus. Ma dong sonde bagitu tarús-tarús. Te kalo samua orang bukan Yahudi yang Tuhan su pili dong su parcaya sang Kristus, nanti orang Yahudi dong ju parcaya sang Dia.<bt>Siblings in Roma! You-pl must understand this matter which previously was a secret. Cuz/for (elaboration) if you understand it, you won't be big headed, thinking that, you are smart/clever. Cuz/for (elaboration) it's like this: now the Yahudi people are hard livered (=stubborn), and don't want to believe in Kristus. But they won't be like that forever. Cuz/for (elaboration) if/when all the non Yahudi people who God2 has chosen have believed in Kristus, later the Yahudi people will also believe in Him. [EXEG: SSA, MC, high-level.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***EXEG: all the non-Yahudi people that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">***EXEG: all the non-Yahudi people that he has chosen ...</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So that you may not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: So that you may not claim to be wiser than you are, brothers and sisters, I want you to understand this mystery: a hardening has come upon part of Israel, until the full number of the Gentiles has come in.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Jadi, kalo itu waktu su datang, nanti Tuhan kasi salamat sang samua orang Yahudi dari dong pung sala-sala. Itu sama ke su tatulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>So (consequently), if/when the time comes, later God2 will save all the Yahudi people from their wrongs. That is the same as is already written in the Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti ada satu Orang datang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Later a Person will come,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang kasi salamat sang kotong dari calaka.<bt>who save us-inc from misfortune.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia datang dari gunung Sion, di kota Yerusalem.<bt>He will come from mount Sion, in Yerusalem city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia yang nanti bekin Yakob pung turunan dong bartobat.<bt>He is the one who later will make Yakob's descendants repent.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Te dong ada idop sonde toe sang Beta,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) they are living not caring about Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng dong su bale balakang sang Beta pung jalan idop yang batúl.<bt>and they have turned their backs on My life path that is right/correct/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho rhuomenos: the one delivering, rescuing,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">ho rhuomenos: the one delivering, rescuing, with the implication that the danger in question is severe and acute asebeia: godlessness, ungodliness, live in a manner contrary to proper religious beliefs and practice<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>NRSV: And so all Israel will be saved; as it is written, “Out of Zion will come the Deliverer; he will banish ungodliness from Jacob.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 59:20-21</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="27" />Beta mau hapus buang dong pung sala-sala,<bt>I want to wipe/erase away their wrongs,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te Beta su ika janji deng dong bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) I have bound/tied a promise with them like that.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: NLT -keep a covenant that was established long ago]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “And this is my covenant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: “And this is my covenant with them, when I take away their sins.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 31:33-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Tiap kali orang Yahudi dong dengar Kristus pung Kabar Bae, dong bekin diri ke musu yang malawan sang Dia. Deng bagitu, dong kasi sampat sang bosong yang bukan Yahudi dong! Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan masi sayang sang dong, tagal Dia sayang sang dong pung nene-moyang, deng su pili ame sang dong ko jadi Dia pung orang dong.<bt>Every time the Yahudi people hear Kristus' Good News, they make themselves out to be enemies who oppose Him. In that way, they give opportunity to you who are not Yahudi! But even though that's the case, nevertheless God2 still loves them, because He loved their ancestors, and chose them to become His people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: As regards the gospel they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: As regards the gospel they are enemies of God for your sake; but as regards election they are beloved, for the sake of their ancestors;</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Te kalo Tuhan su kasi pi satu barang, Dia sonde hela ame kambali. Deng kalo Dia su pange orang bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mari iko sang Beta! Mari maso jadi Beta pung orang su!&gt;&gt; Dia sonde usir buang lai sang dong.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if God2 has given away a thing, He doesn't yank it back. And if He has called people saying, &lt;&lt;We! [+get attention] Come, follow Me! Come enter and become My people!&gt;&gt; He doesn't evict them out anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for the gifts and the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: for the gifts and the calling of God are irrevocable.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Dolu bosong yang bukan orang Yahudi sonde mau dengar sang Tuhan. Ma sakarang bosong yang tarima Tuhan pung rasa kasian, tagal orang Yahudi dong yang sonde mau dengar sang Dia.<bt>Formerly you who were not Yahudi people did not want to hear/obey God2. But now you-pl are the ones who have received God2's mercy/pity, because the Yahudi people are the ones who didn't want to listen/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Just as you were once"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Just as you were once disobedient to God but have now received mercy because of their disobedience,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Jadi dong ni, yang sakarang sonde bekin iko Tuhan pung mau. Andia ko Tuhan masi mau kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang bosong. Deng nanti Dia ju mau kasian sang dong lai.<bt>So (consequently), they are the ones who now don't want to follow God2's will. That's why God2 still wants to show his pity/mercy to you-pl. And later He also wants to pity/have compassion on them again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so they have now been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: so they have now been disobedient in order that, by the mercy shown to you, they too may now receive mercy.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Sakarang Tuhan lia orang Yahudi sama deng orang bukan Yahudi. Te dong samua sonde bekin iko Dia pung mau, sama ke dong ada takurung deng sonde tau jalan kaluar. Dia kasi biar bagitu, ko Dia bisa kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang samua orang.<bt>Now God2 sees the Yahudi people the same as non Yahudi people. Cuz/for (elaboration) they all do not follow His will, just as if they were caged/trapped and don't know the way out (of their troubles/dilemma). He allows them to be like that, so He can show His mercy/pity to all people. [EXEG: SSA + higher level resonance with previous chapters]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takurung = stuck, trapped"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">takurung = stuck, trapped</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For God has imprisoned all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For God has imprisoned all in disobedience so that he may be merciful to all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan tu, bae talalu!<bt>The aforementioned God2, is extremely good!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="33" />Tuhan Allah pintar talalu!<bt>God2 is extremely smart/clever/wise!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia ju pake Dia pung pintar ko bekin yang bae.<bt>And He also uses His smartness to do what is good. [explicating ‘wisdom’]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sonde ada orang yang bisa kanál batúl sang Dia.<bt>There is no one who can truly know/be.familiar.with Him. [broad bridge]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada orang yang tau batúl so'al Dia pung putus parkara.<bt>There is no one who can truly know about His judging of cases. [specific]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu orang ju yang mangarti,<bt>There is not a single person either who understands, [specific]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">akurang ko Tuhan bekin satu hal.<bt>why God2 does something.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: O the depth of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: O the depth of the riches and wisdom and knowledge of God! How unsearchable are his judgments and how inscrutable his ways!</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="34" />Sonde ada orang yang tau parsís kotong pung Bos pung pikiran.<bt>There is no one who knows precisely our-inc Boss' thinking.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada satu ju yang bisa kasi nasiat sang Dia.<bt>There is not a single person either who can give advice to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sýmboulos: adviser NRSV: “For who has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">sýmboulos: adviser NRSV: “For who has known the mind of the Lord? Or who has been his counselor?”<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:13</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="35" />Sonde ada orang yang bisa kasi parsén satu barang kasi pi Tuhan,<bt>There is no one who can free.gift (verb) a thing to God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada orang yang bisa paksa Tuhan ko Dia balas kambali!<bt>There is no one who can force God2 so that He [is obliged to] reciprocate back!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proédooken: give somebody something to set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">proédooken: give somebody something to set up an obligation, so they will owe you something NRSV: “Or who has given a gift to him, to receive a gift in return?”<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 41:11</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="36" />Te samua-samua ba'akar di Tuhan Allah!<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) everything is rooted in God1!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua jadi, tagal Dia!<bt>Everything happens, because of Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang kotong bekin,<bt>Everything we-inc do,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kotong karjá kasi sang Dia.<bt>we work for Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong angka puji-puji sang Dia,<bt>We lift up praises to Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe salamanya!<bt>forever!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Batúl bagitu!<bt>That's really true! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For from him and through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For from him and through him and to him are all things. To him be the glory forever. Amen.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 8:6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong ta'ika deng Kristus, kotong pung idop baru musti jadi karmana?<bt>If we-inc are bound/linked with Kristus, what must our new like be like?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Tagal Tuhan Allah su kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang kotong, andia ko beta minta ko bosong sarakan bosong pung diri anteru-anteru pi sang Dia, sama ke korban yang masi idop. Itu yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Pasang kaki ko bekin iko Dia pung mau, deng idop barisi, te itu kasi tunju bosong pung sayang deng hormat sang Dia. Memang pantas bosong sémba sang Dia bagitu.<bt>Beloved siblings! Because God1 has shown his mercy/pity toward us-inc, that's why I request that you-pl hand.over your entire-entire selves to Him, like a sacrifice that is still alive. That is what makes God2's liver happy. Plant your feet (=strive hard) to do according to His will, and live clean/holy, cuz/for (elaboration) that shows your love and respect/ honour toward Him. It is really appropriate that you worship Him like that. [EXEG: SSA; see Message for whole chapter; “strive hard” is explication reflecting the force of “I appeal to you therefore…to present yourself…” which is a very strong exhortation to strive to do s.t. To be “holy and acceptable”, means to do things “according to His will” and “please Him”, among other things. They are not additions.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I appeal to you therefore,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: I appeal to you therefore, brothers and sisters, by the mercies of God, to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to God, which is your spiritual worship.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pasang kaki ko bekin iko Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Pasang kaki ko bekin iko Dia pung mau, te itu barisi, deng kasi tunju bosong pung sayang deng hormat sang Dia. Deng itu memang pantas ko bosong sémba sang Dia bagitu.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jang kasi biar ko orang dunya sakarang suru bosong musti bekin karmana, ko, idop karmana, iko dong pung mau-mau. Jang cuma iko buta-buta sa dong pung pikiran, dong pung idop, ko, dong pung adat. Ma ada lebe bae, bosong kasi biar ko Tuhan bekin bosong pung pikiran jadi baru, ko bosong lia samua-samua iko jalan baru. Deng bagitu, bosong bisa tau Tuhan pung mau kasi bosong. Te Tuhan pung mau tu, bae, sampurna, deng bekin sanáng Dia pung hati.<bt>Don't allow the people in the world now.a.days to order/command/press what you-pl must do, or how to live, according to their desires/passions/requirements. Don't just blindly follow their thinking, their lives, or, their adat/customs. But it is better, you allow God to make your thinking become new, so that you see all those things, according to a new path/way. In that way, you can know what God2's will is for you. Cuz/for (elaboration) God's will, is good, perfect/complete, and makes His liver happy. [EXEG: MESSAGE. Philips. NOTE /suru/ may be a little strong, but we want something that reflects strong social pressure. Keep in mind that “be conformed” has both a weak sense “wind up doing what they do” and a strong sense “allow people to pressure you”. We want to reflect both, if we can.] [NOTE to daughter translations: 1) /sampurna/ can be unpacked as /langkáp/ or /sonde kurang satu apa ju/ (place latter at end). 2) if /bosong bisa tau Tuhan pung mau kasi bosong/ is difficult, try /Deng bagitu, bosong bisa tau apa yang Tuhan mau ko bosong bekin./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="see Message"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">see Message</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not be conformed to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewing of your minds, so that you may discern what is the will of God-what is good and acceptable and perfect.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tagal Tuhan su utus sang beta deng kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta, andia ko beta kasi tau sang bosong, bagini: nilei bosong pung diri deng cara yang batúl! Jang angka-angka diri lebe dari yang batúl. Jang pake nilei yang sonde ada pung dasar. Tiap orang musti coba mangarti karunya yang Tuhan su kasi sang dia, tagal dia parcaya sang Kristus.<bt>Because God2 has commissioned me and shown His good liver to me, that's why I tell you-pl, like this: evaluate your own selves in a way that is true! Don't elevate yourselves up more than what is right/correct. Don't use values/evaluations/assessments which have no basis/foundation. Every person must try to understand the special.gifting God2 has given him/her, because he/she believes in Kristus. [EXEG: NLT] [NOTE to daughter translations: Check carefully if using loan. Some equate /karunya/ with ‘grace’ (=anugerah) rather than ‘special gifting’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="métron písteoos: God helps us trust"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">métron písteoos: God helps us trust him. How far have we gotten in trusting God? That is the measure by which we calibrate our real potential. If you have learned to trust God a lot, then you know what else you can trust him to do. You'll know it's not you that's doing it, so you won't get conceited about it. And you'll be realistic NRSV: For by the grace given to me I say to everyone among you not to think of yourself more highly than you ought to think, but to think with sober judgment, each according to the measure of faith that God has assigned.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tiap orang musti coba mangarti karmana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tiap orang musti coba mangarti karmana Tuhan su tolong itu orang ko dia parcaya sang Kristus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ame conto dari orang pung badan. Satu badan pung bagian macam-macam. Deng tiap bagian pung tugas laen-laen.<bt>Take an example from a person's body. One body has all.sorts of parts. And each part has different jobs/responsibilities.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For as in one body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For as in one body we have many members, and not all the members have the same function,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bagitu ju deng kotong yang ta'ika deng Kristus. Kotong banya orang, ma kotong ta'ika jadi sama ke satu badan. Deng tiap orang pung tugas laen-laen, sama ke badan pung bagian dong. Satu parlú sang satu. Conto ke, tangan yang tapotong putus dari badan, su sonde ada pung guna lai, to?<bt>It's like that also with us-inc who are bound/linked with Kristus. We are many people, but we are bound/linked/tied.together like one body. And each person has a different job/responsibility, just life the body's parts. Each one needs the other. For example, a hand that is cut off (&amp;separated) from the body, doesn't have a use anymore, right? [NOTE: NLT “needs each other”; Message explicates “linked to each other” saying “But as a chopped off finger we wouldn't amount to much, would we.” CHECK with team and UNS's if last sentence (from Message) is required to pull it all together.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so we, who are many,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: so we, who are many, are one body in Christ, and individually we are members one of another.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4-5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 12:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Beta pung maksud bagini: Tuhan kasi kuasa sang kotong samua ko kasi jalan tugas macam-macam, tagal Dia suka kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong. Conto ke, kalo Tuhan kasi kuasa sang lu ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán, na, lu musti kasi tau itu pasán anteru. Ma jang kasi tau lebe dari itu pasán.<bt>My meaning/intent is like this: God2 gives power to us-inc all in order to carry out all sorts of jobs/responsibilities, because He likes to show His good liver (=grace) to us. For example, if God2 gives power to you-sg to tell His message, na, you must tell that entire message. But don't tell more than/beyond that message. [DISCOURSE: intro is discourse driven, shifting from general principle to explanation.] [EXEG: lots of debate re: “in proportion to faith” KM literal /iko lu pung parcaya/ “according to your belief/faith” was too broad/vague. See Morris, Moo, who come down on different sides. SSA gives both, but comes down on same side as Morris, NLT, etc. /cf added to address objections, as explication of “proportion/ analogous”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** refined exegesis; \cf added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** refined exegesis; \cf added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We have gifts that differ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: We have gifts that differ according to the grace given to us: prophecy, in proportion to faith;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Conto ke, kalo Tuhan kasi kuasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Conto ke, kalo Tuhan kasi kuasa sang lu ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán, deng lu parcaya kuat sang Dia, na, lu ju musti kasi tau banya, so'al Dia pung pasán tu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:11, 24; 1 Korintus 14:29; 1 Yohanis 4:1-6</note><v n="7" />Kalo Tuhan kasi karunya sang lu ko layani orang laen, lu musti layani pake itu kuasa. Kalo Dia kasi karunya sang lu ko ajar orang so'al Dia, na, lu musti ajar pake itu kuasa.<bt>If God gives spiritual.gift/talent (loan--see note at end of verse) to you-sg to serve other people, you must serve using that power. If He gives spiritual.gift/talent to you to teach people about Him, na, you must teach using that power. [NOTE: BI word for spiritual.gift has right range of meaning and is widely entrenched, and used when speaking KM. we don't use it across the board for /charismata/ but intersperse it with "power" to strengthen people's understanding in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="didáskoon: teaching not so much as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">didáskoon: teaching not so much as an occupation, like schoolteacher, but having the ability to teach within the church NRSV: ministry, in ministering; the teacher, in teaching;<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Kalo Dia kasi karunya sang lu ko kasi samangat orang, na, lu musti kasi samangat pake itu kuasa. Kalo Dia kasi kuasa sang lu ko lu bisa bantu orang laen deng harta yang lu dapa, na, kasi lu pung harta ko bantu sang dong. Kalo Dia kasi karunya sang lu ko pimpin ame orang ko dong kasi jalan Dia pung karjá lebe bae, na, lu musti rajin ko pimpin ame pake itu kuasa. Kalo Dia kasi lu rasa kasian ko mau tolong orang susa, na, lu musti tolong sang dong deng hati babunga.<bt>If He gives a spiritual.gift/talent to you-sg to give enthusiasm/encouragement to people, na, you must give enthusiasm/encouragement using that power. If He gives power to you so you can help other people with possessions/belongings/wealth which you have, na, give your possessions to help them. If he gives spiritual.gift/talent to you to lead people so that they carry out His work in a better manner, na, you must be diligent/industrious to lead using that power. If He gives you pity/compassion to help people in difficulty/poverty, na, you must help them with a flowering (=joyful) liver. [NOTE to daughter translations: if your lg has a way of saying “give your possessions (generously) to help them”. But be careful not to make it a heavy information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi spirit = (bhs lapangan olaraga)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">kasi spirit = (bhs lapangan olaraga) ; rajin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hilaróteeti: cheerful, happy, feel good about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">hilaróteeti: cheerful, happy, feel good about helping out NRSV: the exhorter, in exhortation; the giver, in generosity; the leader, in diligence; the compassionate, in cheerfulness.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:6-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 12:4-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus pung orang dong, musti idop karmana?<bt>How must Kristus' people live?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Kalo bosong kasi tunju sayang sang orang, na, kasi tunju sayang yang batúl pung; jang muka-balakang. Bale balakang dari samua hal jahat, deng pegang ame samua hal bae.<bt>If you-pl show love to people, na, show love that is really true/correct; don't be front-back (=hypocritical). Turn your back on all evil things, and grab ahold of all good things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let love be genuine; hate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let love be genuine; hate what is evil, hold fast to what is good;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Bosong orang sarani musti basayang manis satu deng satu. Pasang kaki ko kasi tunju bosong pung hormat satu deng satu.<bt>You-pl <span class="Italic">(sarani)</span> people (=Christians) must love each other sweetly/tenderly. Plant your feet (=strive hard) to show your respect/honour to each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: love one another with mutual"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: love one another with mutual affection; outdo one another in showing honor.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kalo bosong karjá, na, karjá deng samangat, jang satenga-satenga. Biar ko bosong pung hati babunga waktu bosong ada karjá. Deng karjá kasi sang kotong pung Bos.<bt>If/when you-pl work, na, work with enthusiasm, don't do it half-half (=half heartedly). Allow your livers to flower (=be joyful) while you are working. And work for our-inc Boss. [NOTE to daughter translations: depending on RL you might be able to combine last to sentences.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tóoi pneúmati zéontes: with great enthusiasm,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">tóoi pneúmati zéontes: with great enthusiasm, letting your spirit shine out, with an attitude of intense devotion NRSV: Do not lag in zeal, be ardent in spirit, serve the Lord.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Bosong pung hati musti sanáng siang-malam, te bosong su tau Tuhan mau bekin karmana kasi sang bosong. Batahan kalo dapa susa. Sambayang siang-malam; jang cape.<bt>Your-pl livers must be happy day-night, cuz/for (elaboration) you already know what God2 wants to do for you. Endure if you encounter/experience difficulty. Pray day-night; don't get tired/weary. [EXEG: Gk is present active participle, which is on-going. This is reflected by “day-night” which means “continually” (See article on doublets in NTT). Aspect also supported by context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Like Philippians 4:4 NRSV: Rejoice in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Like Philippians 4:4 NRSV: Rejoice in hope, be patient in suffering, persevere in prayer.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Pake bosong pung harta dong ko bantu orang sarani yang ada parlú. Kalo ada orang yang datang dari tampa laen, buka tangan ko kasi dong makan-minum, ko, manumpang di bosong pung ruma. Deng bagitu, bosong kasi tunju sayang sang dong.<bt>Use your possessions to help the <span class="Italic">(sarani)</span> Christian people who have needs. If there are people who come from other places, open your arms to give them food-drink, or, stay temporarily in your houses. In that way, you will show love to them. [EXEG: NLT, Message explicating hospitality]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teèn philoxenían dioókontes: going out of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">teèn philoxenían dioókontes: going out of your way to take care of visitors (may be referring to Christians, or just to strangers in general) NRSV: Contribute to the needs of the saints; extend hospitality to strangers.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kalo ada orang yang bekin susa sang bosong tarús, minta ko Tuhan Allah bekin hal bae kasi sang dong. Batúl! Jang kasi kutuk sang dong!<bt>If there are people who continually cause difficulty to you, request that God1 does good things for them. Really! Don't curse them!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Bless those who persecute you;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Bless those who persecute you; bless and do not curse them.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:44, Lukas 6:28</note><v n="15" />Kalo ada orang yang hati sanáng, na, iko sanáng sama-sama. Deng kalo ada orang yang manangis tagal hati barát, na, iko manangis sama-sama.<bt>If there is a person whose liver is happy, na, follow.along (participate in) being happy all.together. And if there is a person who cries because of a heavy liver (=sadness), na, follow.along crying all.together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Rejoice with those who rejoice,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Rejoice with those who rejoice, weep with those who weep.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Idop basayang deng satu hati. Jang tinggi hati. Ada lebe bae, bosong batamán deng orang tar laku-laku dong. Jang angka-angka diri ko pikir bilang, cuma lu sandiri sa yang tau.<bt>Live loving each other with one liver (=in unity, harmony, accord). Don't have a high liver (=be conceited). It's better, if you-pl be friends with the people who are nobodies/socially unacceptable. Don't lift yourself up (=praise yourself) thinking, only you-sg yourself is the one who knows.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lu ke tau-tau sa = conceited,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">lu ke tau-tau sa = conceited, think that you know/understand s.t.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Live in harmony with one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Live in harmony with one another; do not be haughty, but associate with the lowly; do not claim to be wiser than you are.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 3:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Kalo orang bekin jahat sang lu, na, lu jang balas deng jahat. Ma lu musti coba-coba ko cari jalan yang paling bae, yang samua orang bisa tarima.<bt>If people do evil to you-sg, na, you don't reciprocate with evil. But you must keep trying to find the best way, which all people can accept/acknowledge (as good).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akui = CHECK BI? (UNS associate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">akui = CHECK BI? (UNS associate with forgiveness)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not repay anyone evil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not repay anyone evil for evil, but take thought for what is noble in the sight of all.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Kalo bisa, na, cari jalan ko idop badame deng samua orang.<bt>If possible, na, look for way/s to live in mutual peace with all people. [NOTE to daughter translations: SSA, Moo, Morris, Barth, and others all lean on the side of this being about peace in broken relationships with others. Therefore, be careful that your translations hit the side of /badame/ “restored relationships”, and avoid /damai-sejahtera/ that highlights “stability &amp; well-being”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If it is possible, so"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: If it is possible, so far as it depends on you, live peaceably with all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Sodara sayang dong! Jang balas dendam. Kasi tenga ko Tuhan yang ator sa. Te Dia mara kalo orang bekin jahat, sama ke yang ada tulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>[DISCOURSE: vocative sets off new paragraph in RL discourse.] Beloved siblings! Don't reciprocate vengence (=don't take revenge). Just let it be so that it's just God2 who controls/handles it. Cuz/for (elaboration) He gets angry if people do evil, just like what is written in the Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kotong pung Bos sandiri yang omong bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Our Boss himself is the one who spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta yang ada pung hak balas dendam.<bt>I am the one who has the right to take revenge.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Beta yang kasi hukum orang pung jahat dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) I am the one who punishes people's evils.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekdíkeesis: not God taking vengeance on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">ekdíkeesis: not God taking vengeance on people who hurt him or us, but on people who do bad NRSV: Beloved, never avenge yourselves, but leave room for the wrath of God; for it is written, “Vengeance is mine, I will repay, says the Lord.”<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:35</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ada lebe bae, bekin iko apa yang Tulisan Barisi kasi tau dari dolu bilang,<bt>It's better (=polite command), to do according to what the Holy Writings made known from long ago saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kalo lu pung musu lapar,<bt>&lt;&lt;If your-sg enemy is hungry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, kasi dia makan.<bt>na, give him/her food.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo lu pung musu aus,<bt>If your enemy is thirsty,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, kasi dia minum.<bt>na, give him/her drink.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te kalo bekin bagitu, nanti dia malu hati,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if [you] do like that, later he/she will be embarrased/ashamed [/malu hati/ implies change attitude toward you],</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng hormat bale sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>and show respect back to you-sg. [EXEG: SSA, Morris] [NOTE: some suggest change from singular to plural you--representing benefit to whole community of believers, but we couldn't make it work with several groups].&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malu hati implies change attitude toward"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">malu hati implies change attitude toward you bara api = api arang = arang manyala = burning coals? If problems with literal, see discussion in Morris.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Allusion to Psalm 140:10, burning coals?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Allusion to Psalm 140:10, burning coals? NRSV: No, “if your enemies are hungry, feed them; if they are thirsty, give them something to drink; for by doing this you will heap burning coals on their heads.”<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;sama ke taro bara api di dia pung kapala.&gt;&gt; Orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab bilang, itu pung arti &lt;&lt;dia malu hati deng dia hormat bale sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Greek language Alkitab writes saying, “like you were putting burning coals on his/her head.” People who are knowledgeable about the Alkitab say, that means, “he/she is embarrassed and he/she gives respect back to you-sg.”</bt></note><note reference="12:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 140:10, Kata-kata Mutiara 25:21-22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Jang kasi biar hal jahat dong ator sang lu. Ada lebe bae, hal bae dong yang ator sang lu sa. Deng bagitu, lu bisa kasi kala hal jahat dong.<bt>Don't allow evil things to control/manage/have oversight over you-sg. It's better, if its just good things that control you. In that way, you-sg can defeat those evil things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not be overcome by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not be overcome by evil, but overcome evil with good.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dengar-dengar sang orang yang pegang parenta dong<bt>Habituallly listen.to/obey people who hold authority/government/rule</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Tiap orang musti dengar-dengar sang orang yang pegang parenta dong. Te dong ada pung hak deng kuasa ko parenta orang. Ma dong pung pegang kuasa tu, tagal Tuhan Allah yang kasi sang dong. Yang pegang kuasa sakarang, ada pegang bagitu tagal Tuhan su angka sang dong.<bt>Each person must habituallly listen.to/obey people who hold authority. Cuz/for (elaboration) they have the right and the power to command/govern people. But they hold that power/authority, because God1 is the one who gave it to them. Those who hold power now, are holding (power) like that because God2 has lifted them up (=appointed them).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let every person be subject"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let every person be subject to the governing authorities; for there is no authority except from God, and those authorities that exist have been instituted by God.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi, kalo orang malawan orang yang pegang parenta bagitu, itu sama ke dong malawan apa yang Tuhan su angka. Kalo dong bekin bagitu, nanti kaná hukum dari Tuhan.<bt>So (consequently), if people oppose people who hold authority like that, that is the same as if they were opposing what God2 has lifted up/appointed. If they do like that, later they will get punished from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore whoever resists authority resists"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore whoever resists authority resists what God has appointed, and those who resist will incur judgment.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Kalo bosong bekin yang batúl, sonde usa taku sang orang yang pegang parenta dong. Ma kalo bosong bekin jahat, lebe bae bosong taku sang dong! Jadi jaga diri ko bekin yang batúl, ko sonde usa taku sang dong. Deng kalo bosong bekin bagitu, na, nanti dong puji sang bosong.<bt>If you-pl do what is right/true/correct, [you] don't need to be afraid of people who hold authority. But if you-pl do evil, it's better you be afraid of them! So (consequently), watch/guard yourselves in order to do what is right/correct, so [you] don't need to be afraid of them. And If you do like that, na, later they will praise you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For rulers are not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For rulers are not a terror to good conduct, but to bad. Do you wish to have no fear of the authority? Then do what is good, and you will receive its approval;</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te orang yang pegang parenta, dong tu yang Tuhan pili ame ko layani sang bosong. Ma kalo bosong ada bekin sala tarús, lebe bae bosong ati-ati sa! Te dong yang ada pung hak yang sonde parcuma ko kasi hukum sang bosong. Dong tu, sama ke Tuhan pung orang suru-suru ko kasi hukum orang yang bekin jahat dong. Te Tuhan sonde tarima hal jahat yang orang ada bekin; Dia mara sang dong.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) the people who hold authority, they are the ones whom God chose to serve you. And if you are continually doing wrong, it's better you just be really careful! Cuz/for (elaboration) they are the ones who have the right which isn't pointless/ineffectual to punish you. They are the same as God2's servants (people who carry out orders) to punish people who do evil. Cuz/for (elaboration) God2 doesn't accept/put up with evil things which people do; He gets angry at them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for it is God's servant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: for it is God's servant for your good. But if you do what is wrong, you should be afraid, for the authority does not bear the sword in vain! It is the servant of God to execute wrath on the wrongdoer.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Andia ko bosong musti dengar sang orang yang pegang parenta dong. Te bosong su tau di bosong pung dalam hati bilang, itu yang batúl. Deng bosong ju tau bilang, Tuhan mara kalo kotong sonde bekin yang batúl.<bt>That's why you-pl must listen.to/obey the people who hold authority. Cuz/for (elaboration) you already know in your inner livers (=consciences) that, that is what is right/correct. And you also know that, God get's angry if we-inc (general principle) do not do what is right/correct. [DISCOURSE: vs.5 separate paragraph because of 1) its genre as summary, recapitulation, and 2) the way it relates to both preceding and following verses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore one must be subject,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore one must be subject, not only because of wrath but also because of conscience.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Bagitu ju, bosong musti bayar pajak yang sah, tagal orang yang pegang parenta dong ada kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá.<bt>In the same way also, you must pay tax which is legal/legitimate, because the people who hold authority are carrying out God2's work. [NOTE to daughter translations: 1) /pajak/ not same as /bapajak/ “arbitrary financial demands from people in uniform”; avoid sense of have to pay /orang yang bapajak sang lu/. 2) if /sah/ is difficult, try /yang iko atoran/ or /yang batúl/.] [EXEG: Gk is not /doulos/ or other noun for “servant” here, but rather a verb “in close personal attendance”. Avoid “carrying out the will of God”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** note added (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For the same reason you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For the same reason you also pay taxes, for the authorities are God's servants, busy with this very thing.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jadi bosong musti bayar samua yang batúl. Bayar kasi tukang tagi bea dong, samua bea yang bosong musti bayar. Taro hormat sang samua orang yang musti tarima hormat. Deng kalo ada orang yang bekin hal bae tarús, angka dong pung nama ko samua orang tau dong ada bekin yang bae.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must pay everything which is right (for you to pay). Pay the tax collectors, all the tax which you must/are required to pay. (Show) respect for all people who must/ought to receive respect. And if there are people who continually do good things, lift up their names (praise them/say good things about them/promote them) so everyone will know they are doing what is good.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Pay to all what is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Pay to all what is due them-taxes to whom taxes are due, revenue to whom revenue is due, respect to whom respect is due, honor to whom honor is due.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:21, Markus 12:17, Lukas 20:25</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Idop basayang satu deng satu<bt>Live mutually loving each other</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Bayar lunas lu pung utang dong, ko jang idop deng ba'utang. Te kotong cuma mau ba'utang dalam satu hal sa, andia basayang. Kalo bosong sayang orang, na, bosong su bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran dong.<bt>Pay in full your-sg debts, in order to not live in debt. [CHECK /bayar putus/ vs. /bayar lunas/.] Cuz/for (elaboration) we-inc only want to be indebted in just one thing, which is mutual.love. If you love people, na, you are already doing according to God2's Law.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jang idop deng utang ponu panta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">jang idop deng utang ponu panta :-) ; bayar putus = implies somebody else pays off the debt ; bayar lunas = implies we pay off our own debt ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Owe no one anything, except"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Owe no one anything, except to love one another; for the one who loves another has fulfilled the law.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Te itu Atoran dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang maen serong; jang bunu orang; jang pancuri; jang kapingin dapa orang laen pung barang,&gt;&gt; deng laen lai. Kalo mau bekin iko samua Atoran dong, musti bekin iko ini Atoran satu, yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu musti sayang orang laen dong, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) the Laws/Regulations say, &lt;&lt;Don't play around sexually/commit adultery; don't murder people; don't steal; don't desire to get other people's things,&gt;&gt; and more. If you want to follow all those Regulations, [you] must follow this one Regulation which says, &lt;&lt;You-sg must love other people, the same as you love your own self.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapeeseis ...: Matthew 22:39 NRSV: The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">agapeeseis ...: Matthew 22:39 NRSV: The commandments, “You shall not commit adultery; You shall not murder; You shall not steal; You shall not covet”; and any other commandment, are summed up in this word, “Love your neighbor as yourself.”<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="13:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:13-15, 17, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:17-19, 21, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18, Mateos 22:39, Markus 12:29-31</note><v n="10" />Te kalo kotong kasi tunju sayang sang orang laen, kotong sonde bekin jahat sang dia, to? Jadi, kalo kotong kasi tunju sayang tarús, kotong bisa bekin iko samua Atoran dari Tuhan.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if we-inc show love to other another person, we don't do evil to him/her, right? So (consequently), if we continually showing love, we can do according to all the Regulations from God. [NOTE: /kotong/ for genre reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Love does no wrong to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Love does no wrong to a neighbor; therefore, love is the fulfilling of the law.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sonde lama lai, te Kristus su mau datang kambali<bt>It won't be much longer, te2 (sudden or unexpected) Kristus is already wanting to come back</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Tuhan Allah mau angka kasi lapás sang kotong dari orang di ini dunya pung jahat. Deng sakarang, dia pung waktu ko kasi salamat orang, su lebe deka dari waktu kotong baru parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Andia ko kotong musti idop basayang, tagal kotong mangarti itu hal. Tingka ke dolu, kotong ada tidor. Ma sakarang, dia pung waktu ko kotong musti bangun su!<bt>God1 wants to take us up to free/deliver/save us the evil of the people in this world. And now, the time to save people is closer than when we-inc had just believed in Yesus Kristus. That's why we-inc (genre) must live mutually loving each other, because we understand this matter. It's as if formerly, we-inc were sleeping. But now, it's time for us to wake up! [EXEG: on “salvation is nearer”, see Uma, and discussion in SSA and Moo.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Besides this, you know what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Besides this, you know what time it is, how it is now the moment for you to wake from sleep. For salvation is nearer to us now than when we became believers;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah mau kasi salamat sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan Allah mau kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala dong. Sakarang, dia pung waktu ko kasi salamat orang su lebe deka dari waktu kotong baru parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Andia ko bosong musti idop basayang, tagal bosong mangarti itu hal. Tingka ke dolu, kotong ada tidor. Ma sakarang, dia pung waktu ko kotong musti bangun su!</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Sonde lama, te malam su abis, ais siang su datang. Jadi ada lebe bae, kotong barenti su dari kotong pung jahat. Itu sama ke orang yang idop dalam galáp deng bekin hal jahat, te dong pikir sonde ada orang yang lia sang dong. Ma sakarang kotong musti jadi ke tantara yang pake alat paráng, ko pasang kaki bekin hal bae dong, sama ke orang yang idop dalam taráng.<bt>It will not be much longer, cuz/for (elaboration) the night is already ending, and then daylight will have come. So (consequently) it's better/best, if we-inc stop already from our evils [+mild (Yiddish) imperative :-)]. It's like people living in the dark and doing evil things, cuz/for (elaboration) they think there is no one who sees them. But now we must become like soldiers who use war equipment/weapons/armament, in order to plant our feet (=try hard, strive) to do good things, like people who live in the light.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: the night is far gone,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: the night is far gone, the day is near. Let us then lay aside the works of darkness and put on the armor of light;</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Kotong musti idop yang batúl, ko samua orang dapa lia kotong ada bekin hal bae dong. Sonde bae kalo kotong cuma bapesta rame-rame, deng minum mabo sa. Sonde bae kalo kotong hohongge tarús. Sonde bae kalo kotong bakanjar kiri-kanan. Deng sonde bae kalo kotong camburu tagal kotong sonde suka orang lebe dari kotong.<bt>We-inc must live correctly, so that all people can see we are doing good things. It's not good if we only have lively feasts, and just drink getting drunk. It's not good if we play around sexually/promiscuously. It's not good if we argue left-right (=with everyone). And it's not good if we are jealous because we don't like people to exceed (=be better/higher ranking than) us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: let us live honorably as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: let us live honorably as in the day, not in reveling and drunkenness, not in debauchery and licentiousness, not in quarreling and jealousy.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma ada lebe bae, bosong oba bosong pung hati ko jadi sama ke kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang. Deng kalo lu ada kapingin mau bekin hal yang sonde batúl, na, jang kasi biar ko lu bekin iko lu pung mau sambarang bagitu. Tahan diri!<bt>But its better/best, if you-pl change your livers to become like our Boss, Yesus Kristus, whom God2 sent. And if you-sg are desiring/longing to do something that is not right/correct, na, don't let yourself do according to whatever you want like that. Restrain yourself!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tahan diri! = Rem-rem sadiki!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tahan diri! = Rem-rem sadiki!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Instead, put on the Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Instead, put on the Lord Jesus Christ, and make no provision for the flesh, to gratify its desires.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang karitik sambarang sang bosong pung sodara orang sarani<bt>Dont' haphazard/arbitrarily criticize your Christian siblings</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Ada orang yang su parcaya sang Tuhan, ma dia pung parcaya balóm kuat deng dia balóm mangarti banya hal. Buka tangan ko tarima sang dia deng bae-bae. Jang bakanjar so'al dia pung pikiran. Biar ko dia batamán deng bosong sa.<bt>There is a person who already believes in God2, but his belief is not yet strong and does not yet understand many things. Open your arms to receive him/her in a good manner. Don't argue about his/her thinking. Just allow him/her to be friends with you-pl. [NOTE to daughter translations: Evaluate with team a) use /sodara/ throughout this passage to emphasize that the issues are between believers, BUT b) will /sodara/ skew it for some people to think we are only talking about KIN WHO BELIEVE (??), and does not include non-kin?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proslambánesthe: make him feel welcome as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">proslambánesthe: make him feel welcome as a member of the Christian community NRSV: Welcome those who are weak in faith, but not for the purpose of quarreling over opinions.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ada orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan, yang pikir bilang, orang sarani bisa makan apa sa, ke daging ko, apa sa. Ma ada orang sarani laen, yang dong pung parcaya sonde kuat, yang cuma mau makan sayur-sayur sa. Te dong pamali deng daging.<bt>There are people who believe in God2, who think that, they can eat whatever, like meat or, whatever. But there are other Christians, whose belief is not strong, who only want to just eat vegetables. Cuz/for (elaboration) they are in a taboo relationship with meat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="láchana: vegetables, vegetarian diet NRSV: Some"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">láchana: vegetables, vegetarian diet NRSV: Some believe in eating anything, while the weak eat only vegetables.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma dengar, é! Orang sarani yang rasa dia bole makan apa sa, jang anggap reme orang yang sonde mau makan daging. Bagitu ju, orang sarani yang sonde mau makan daging, jang kasi tau orang yang makan daging bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Makan daging tu, sala!&gt;&gt; Tagal Tuhan Allah su tarima dong dua ko jadi Dia pung orang!<bt>But listen up, é! A *Christian (lexicalised: baptised person, used primarily used to distinguish from people of other faiths) who feels he/she can eat whatever, should not look down on people who don't want to eat meat. Like that also, Christians who don't want to eat meat, shouldn't tell people who eat meat saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+attention, + rebuke] Eating meat like that, is wrong!&gt;&gt; Because God1 has already accepted both of them to be His people!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meè exoutheneítoo: let him not treat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">meè exoutheneítoo: let him not treat the other person like that person is not worth anything. A very strong word meè krinétoo: let him not pass judgment on the other person<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>NRSV: Those who eat must not despise those who abstain, and those who abstain must not pass judgment on those who eat; for God has welcomed them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Kalo lu maen karitik lu pung sodara orang parcaya bagitu, lu pikir lu ni, sapa? Lu ada hak apa ko lempar sala sang orang laen? Dia bukan lu pung orang karjá! Deng lu tu, bukan dia pung bos. Te cuma dia pung Bos sa, yang ada pung hak ko kasi tau taráng-taráng, yang dia bekin tu, batúl, ko sala. Ma jang lupa. Dia pung Bos tu, yang nanti tarima bae sang itu orang, tagal dia pung Bos mampu bekin dia jadi kuat ko dia bisa batahan.<bt>If/when you-sg keep criticising/accusing2 your fellow believers like that, who do you-sg think you are? Do you have the right to accuse another person? He/She is not your worker! And you, are not his/her boss. Cuz/for (elaboration) it's only his/her Boss, who has the right to tell clearly/boldly/openly, that what he/she does there, is correct/right, or wrong. But don't forget. His Bos is the one who will accept/receive that person well, because his/her Boss was capable of making him/her strong so that he/she could endure. [EXEG: Morris, SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Who are you to pass"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Who are you to pass judgment on servants of another? It is before their own lord that they stand or fall. And they will be upheld, for the Lord is able to make them stand.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ada orang saparu yang putus bilang, satu hari lebe bae dari hari laen dong. Ada orang laen yang pikir bilang, samua hari sama rata, sonde ada pung beda. Tiap orang musti putus sandiri so'al itu parkara.<bt>There are some people who decide that, one day is better than other days. There are other people who think that, all the days are level (=equal), there is no difference. Each person must decide for him/herself about that matter/issue.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Some judge one day to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Some judge one day to be better than another, while others judge all days to be alike. Let all be fully convinced in their own minds.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Kalo orang yang pikir ada hari yang lebe bae dari hari laen dong, dia bekin bagitu ko kasi tunju hormat sang kotong pung Bos. Orang yang makan daging deng makanan laen dong, bisa makan ko kasi tunju hormat sang kotong pung Bos, te dia minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan. Bagitu ju deng orang yang sonde makan daging. Dia ju mau kasi tunju hormat sang kotong pung Bos, deng dia ju minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>If a person thinks one day is better than the other days, he does like that to show honour to our-inc Boss. People who eat meat and other foods, can eat to show respect to our Boss, cuz/for (elaboration) he/she says thank you to God2. It's the same way also with people who don't eat meat. He/She wants to show respect to our Boss, and he/she also says thankyou to God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Those who observe the day,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Those who observe the day, observe it in honor of the Lord. Also those who eat, eat in honor of the Lord, since they give thanks to God; while those who abstain, abstain in honor of the Lord and give thanks to God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kolose 2:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Naa! Waktu kotong idop, kotong sonde idop cuma kasi sang kotong pung diri sa. Deng kalo kotong mati, kotong sonde mati cuma kasi sang kotong pung diri sa.<bt>So then/Well now! When we-inc live, we don't just live only for ourselves. And if/when we die, we don't die only just for ourselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We do not live to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: We do not live to ourselves, and we do not die to ourselves.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Te kalo kotong masi idop, kotong ada ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos. Bagitu ju, kalo kotong mati, kotong masi ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos. Jadi biar kotong idop, ko, kotong mati, kotong masi jadi Dia pung milik.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if we-inc are still alive, we are bound/linked with our Boss. In the same way also, if we die, we are still bound/linked with our Boss. So (consequently) whether we live, or, we die, we still are His possession.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If we live, we live"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: If we live, we live to the Lord, and if we die, we die to the Lord; so then, whether we live or whether we die, we are the Lord's.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Andia ko Kristus mati, ais idop kambali. Dia bekin bagitu ko Dia bisa jadi Bos kasi sang orang yang su mati dong, deng kasi sang orang yang masi idop ju.<bt>That's why Kristus died, then came back to life. He did like that so He can be Boss to all the people who are already dead, and to all the people who are still alive also.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For to this end Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For to this end Christ died and lived again, so that he might be Lord of both the dead and the living.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Jadi akurang ko lu angka diri ke tukang putus parkara, ko karitik sang lu pung sodara orang sarani? Akurang ko lu pandang enteng sang dia? Te nanti kotong samua musti mangada sang Tuhan Allah, ko Dia pareksa kotong satu-satu pung idop.<bt>So (consequently), why do you-sg lift yourself up/elevate/appoint yourself like a judge, to criticize your Christian sibling? Why do you look down on him/her? Cuz/for (elaboration) later we all must face God1, so that He examines each one of our lives.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Why do you pass judgment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Why do you pass judgment on your brother or sister? Or you, why do you despise your brother or sister? For we will all stand before the judgment seat of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Korintus 5:10</note><v n="11" />Ada tulis dari dolu dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>It is written from long ago in God's Clean/Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kotong pung Bos sandiri yang kasi tau bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Our Boss himself is the one who tells/makes known saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Samua orang nanti tikam lutut ko soya sang Beta,<bt>&lt;All people will kneel to bow to Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kasi tunju hormat sang Beta.<bt>and show respect to Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tiap orang nanti pake dong pung mulu ko mangaku,<bt>Each person will use their mouths to acknowledge/confess,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bilang, Beta jadi dong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang dong,<bt>saying, I am their Boss who has the say-so/ordering rights over them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Beta ni, Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>because I here, am God1.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exomologew: confess, acknowledge, praise, express praise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">exomologew: confess, acknowledge, praise, express praise or honor, with a possible implication of acknowledging the nature of someone or something NRSV: For it is written, “As I live, says the Lord, every knee shall bow to me, and every tongue shall give praise to God.”<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="14:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 45:23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Jadi kotong samua nanti musti tanggong-jawab ko lapor sang Tuhan bilang, kotong bekin karmana, deng kanapa kotong bekin bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), we-inc all must be accountable/ responsible to report to God2 saying, what we did, and why we did like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lógon doósei: give an account of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">lógon doósei: give an account of ourselves, explain why we did what we did NRSV: So then, each of us will be accountable to God.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang bekin ko lu pung sodara orang sarani jato [\s2]<bt>Don't do anything so that your Christian sibling falls [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dolu bosong di Roma maen lempar sala sang bosong pung sodara orang sarani dong. Jang bagitu lai! Ada lebe bae, kotong putus bagini: kotong jang bekin kotong pung sodara dong ta'antok. Kotong jang coba hiki kasi jato sang dong, ko dong bekin sala.<bt>Previously, you-pl in Roma kept accusing/blaming your-pl fellow Christian siblings. Don't do that anymore! It's better/best, if we decide like this: we won't make our siblings stumble. We won't try to trick/ensnare [them] making them fall, so they do wrong. [EXEG: MTTs &amp; UNSs felt this can be read with both weak and strong volition/deliberateness as does the Gk (deliberately trying to cause someone to stumble vs. just being sure that nothing you do causes them to stumble) This vagueness is as we designed it (1st part weak, 2nd part strong). SSA &amp; TH are a bit vague on the degree of volition-both could be read either way. Morris notes “The stumbling block (prçskomma) is an obstacle in the way; when the foot strikes it the person stumbles. The obstacle (skandalon) refers strictly to the bait stick of a trap; when an animal or bird strikes it this triggers off the mechanism that produces entrapment. Many think that the two words are practically synonyms here, but Leenhardt holds that the former word points to something that is “met with by chance” and the latter to “the result of an intention”. It is, however, difficult to think that a strong Christian would intend to trap a weak brother,” Personally I (CEG) find this pretty naïve since warnings about false teachers abound; the context of watching the gay lobby from within the church (in Australia); watching theology lecturers irresponsibly trash the students' confidence in the integrity of Scriptures without providing balance to more radical views (Australia, Kupang), etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meekéti: we were criticizing each other,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">meekéti: we were criticizing each other, but we are supposed to lay off próskomma: stumbling, something that makes someone stumble, occasion to sin<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>skándalon: trigger of a trap, the thing that gets you into trouble, occasion to sin NRSV: Let us therefore no longer pass judgment on one another, but resolve instead never to put a stumbling block or hindrance in the way of another.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang lempar sala lai sang kotong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Jang lempar sala lai sang kotong pung sodara orang sarani dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Tagal beta ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos Yesus, beta tau parsís, bagini: sonde ada satu hal ju yang bisa bekin kamomos orang, sampe dia sonde bisa sambayang sang Tuhan. Ma kalo satu orang pikir satu barang bekin dia kamomos, sampe dia rasa dia sonde ada pung hak sambayang lai, biar itu barang jadi pamali kasi sang dia.<bt>Because I am bound/linked with our Bos Yesus, I know precisely/for sure like this: there is nothing that can make a person defiled, to.the.point that he/she can't pray/worship God2. But if a person thinks one thing makes him defiled, to the point that he/she feels he/she no longer has the right to pray/worship, just let/allow that thing become taboo for him/her. [EXEG: Is this a broad principle, or just talking about food in this context? Morris, Moo, NRSV, and TB keep it broad (which includes the issue of food). I (CEG) think limiting it to food because of the context is unfortunately narrower than the text, and I disagree with SSA, NLT, NIV, and CEV here. Others (mentioned above) include its application to food as part of a broader principle. My bias as a missiologist and cross-cultural scripture use worker is showing through here. If Paul was limiting his discussion to food, he's already using the vocabulary necessary to do so explicitly. But he doesn't. He phrases this as a much broader principle or generalisation. And that's why missiologists can appeal to the broader principle in this verse to apply it to cultural customs and other hot issues (like abortion and embryonic stem-cell research) that the scriptures do not address directly. So narrowing the application here and in vs. 16 to food I think is beyond the text and actually unhelpful and limiting.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I know and am persuaded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: I know and am persuaded in the Lord Jesus that nothing is unclean in itself; but it is unclean for anyone who thinks it unclean.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta tau parsís, te beta ta'ika"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Beta tau parsís, te beta ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos Yesus, bagini:</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Conto ke, kalo lu ada makan daging, deng itu bekin lu pung sodara hati susa, na, lu su sonde kasi tunju lu pung sayang sang dia, to? Tahan diri doo! Jang bekin rusak lu pung sodara, cuma tagal lu mau makan satu barang! Te Kristus ju mati kasi sang itu orang.<bt>For example, if you-sg are eating meat, and that makes your sibling's liver distressed, na, you are not showing your love to him/her, right? Restrain yourself! Don't ruin your sibling, just because you want to eat a certain thing! Cuz/for (elaboration) Kristus also died for that person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lupeitai: cause someone to be sad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">lupeitai: cause someone to be sad, sorrowful, or distressed apollue: ruin, destroy, injure<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>NRSV: If your brother or sister is being injured by what you eat, you are no longer walking in love. Do not let what you eat cause the ruin of one for whom Christ died.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Sonde bae kalo lu bekin satu hal yang lu anggap bae, ma orang laen dong omong bekin busuk lu pung nama, tagal dong anggap lu pung bekin tu, jahat.<bt>It's not good if you-sg do something which you consider good, but other people speak making your name rotten (=slander), because they consider what you did/are doing is evil. [EXEG: See comment at vs.14.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So do not let your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: So do not let your good be spoken of as evil.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Pikir bae-bae! Te Tuhan Allah tu, kotong pung Raja. Ma kotong sonde jadi Raja pung orang cuma tagal kotong makan-minum iko atoran sa. Sonde! Kalo kotong mau jadi Raja pung orang, kotong musti bekin yang batúl, kotong pung hati barisi, kotong idop lurus deng dame, deng kotong pung hati sanáng. Samua ni bisa jadi, kalo kotong ta'ika tarús deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi.<bt>Think carefully! Cuz/for (elaboration) God1 is our Raja. But we don't become the Raja's people only because we just eat-drink following regulations. No! If we want to become the Raja's people, we must do what is right/correct/true, our livers are clean/holy, our lives are straight (=righteous) and peaceful (relationships), and our livers happy. All this can happen/eventuate, if we are continually bound/linked with God2's Holy Spirit. [EXEG: SSA, HCE; NOTE: righteousness &amp; peace have internal &amp; external manifestations]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For the kingdom of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: For the kingdom of God is not food and drink but righteousness and peace and joy in the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Orang yang layani sang Kristus bagitu, bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Deng orang laen ju pareksa bae-bae itu orang pung idop, ais angka itu orang pung nama bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, bae!&gt;&gt;<bt>People who serve Kristus like that, make God2's liver happy. And other people also carefully examine that person's life, then lift up that person's name saying, &lt;&lt;He's good/he's a good person!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: explicated to better reflect full meaning of Gk word and to link better with high level theme.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dókimos: approved after being tested, being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">dókimos: approved after being tested, being respected on the basis of proven worth NRSV: The one who thus serves Christ is acceptable to God and has human approval.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Jadi kotong musti pasang kaki ko idop badame, deng kasi kuat satu deng satu.<bt>So (consequently), we must plant our feet (=strive hard) to live in mutual.peace (relationships), and strengthen/encourage each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireénees: inner peace, or a peaceful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">eireénees: inner peace, or a peaceful relationship with other people (more likely here) NRSV: Let us then pursue what makes for peace and for mutual upbuilding.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Jang bekin rusak Tuhan pung karjá di orang laen pung idop cuma tagal parkara makan-minum. Tuhan su bilang bole makan apa sa, te samua barisi. Ma kalo lu baparkara deng lu pung sodara tagal so'al makan-minum, lu tu, sala. Jang bagitu!<bt>Don't destroy/ruin God2's work in another person's life just because of eat-drink disputes/issues. God2 has already said it's ok to eat whatever, cuz/for (elaboration) everything is clean/holy. But if you are in a mutual dispute with your sibling because of an eat-drink matter/issue, that is wrong. Don't do like that! [EXEG re "the work of God": Morris says "There is wide divergence as to the way we should understand it here. Thus Boylan holds that it refers to what God does in the individual Christian, while Barrett denies this and sees a reference to the church. Wesley combines the two ideas: “Which He builds in the soul by faith, and in the Church by concord.” ... Cranfield to what God does in the weak brother, and Haldane to what he does in the believer. Without some further explanation we cannot be sure of the apostle's full meaning, but he is certainly including what God has done in the weak brother, for it is that that is to be built up or broken down. There may be a fuller meaning, but we cannot be sure."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not, for the sake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not, for the sake of food, destroy the work of God. Everything is indeed clean, but it is wrong for you to make others fall by what you eat;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ada lebe bae, lu tahan diri sa. Sonde usa makan daging, ko, minum aer anggor, ko, makan-minum barang laen yang bekin lu pung sodara ta'antok.<bt>It's better/best, if you-sg just restrain yourself. It's not neccessary to eat meat, or drink wine, or eat-drink other things which make your sibling stumble.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: it is good not to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: it is good not to eat meat or drink wine or do anything that makes your brother or sister stumble.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Beta pung maksud bagini: kalo lu su barunding deng Tuhan, ais lu su putus bilang, lu mau parcaya sang Dia so'al makan-minum karmana, na, lu ontong, te su beres. Sonde usa pikir-pikir ko cari tau lu ada bekin sala, ko sonde. Te lu su putus bagitu.<bt>My meaning/intent is like this: if you-sg already consulted with God2, then you already decided, how it is that you want to believe/trust Him about eat-drink issues, na, you are fortunate, cuz it's fine (=dealt with the issue and come out with acceptable results/made things right). It's not neccessary to keep worrying to find out if you are doing wrong, or not. Cuz (elaboration) you have already come to a decision.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added /ontong/ to better"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) added /ontong/ to better reflect “blessed”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The faith that you have,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: The faith that you have, have as your own conviction before God. Blessed are those who have no reason to condemn themselves because of what they approve.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ma kalo lu pung hati bacabang, ais lu makan satu barang yang lu rasa bisa bekin lu kamomos, Tuhan kasi sala sang lu, tagal lu sonde bekin iko apa yang lu parcaya dalam hati waktu lu ada makan. Te kalo lu ada mau bekin apa sa, ma lu parcaya bilang, itu sonde batúl di Tuhan pung muka, na, itu su sala.<bt>But if your liver is forked (=indecisive, in doubt), then you eat something which you feel can make you defiled, God2 accuses/blames you, because you didn't do according to what you believe in your liver when you were eating. Cuz/for (elaboration) if you want to do something, but you believe/trust that it is not right/correct before God2, na, that's wrong/sin. [EXEG: SSA, NLT, Uma]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But those who have doubts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: But those who have doubts are condemned if they eat, because they do not act from faith; for whatever does not proceed from faith is sin.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kalo lu pung hati bacabang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Ma kalo lu pung hati bacabang, ais lu makan satu barang yang lu rasa bisa bekin lu kamomos, Tuhan kasi sala sang lu, tagal lu sonde parcaya batúl waktu lu ada makan. Te kalo lu ada mau bekin apa sa, ma lu sonde parcaya sang Tuhan, na, itu su sala.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Usaha ko bekin tamba kuat orang laen dong pung parcaya<bt>Make.an.effort to make stronger other people's faith</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Kotong yang parcaya kuat, musti hati bésar ko tolong sang orang yang sonde kuat, ko dong batahan dalam susa. Sonde bae kalo kotong cuma bekin sanáng kotong pung diri sandiri sa.<bt>We-inc whose livers believe strongly, must be patient to help people who are not strong, so that they endure in.the.midst of difficulty. It's not good if we only just make ourselves happy. [EXEG: higher level introducing theme; see v.2,4,5; see also NLT, SSA, Morris]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asthenemata: failings, scruples, weaknesses bastazw: bear"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">asthenemata: failings, scruples, weaknesses bastazw: bear with, endure patiently, help to carry the burden, tolerate<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>areskw: to please LITERALLY: We who are strong ought to bear with the failings of the weak, and not to please ourselves.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta pung maksud bagini: kotong satu-satu musti usaha ko bekin yang bae kasi kotong pung sodara orang sarani dong, ko biar dong pung parcaya batamba kuat. Deng bagitu, dong jadi sanáng deng kotong.<bt>My intent is like this: each one of us-inc must endeavour to do what is good for our Christian siblings, so that their faith becomes stronger. In that way, they can become/be happy with us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plesion: neighbor, Christian neighbor LITERALLY: Each"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">plesion: neighbor, Christian neighbor LITERALLY: Each of us should please his neighbor for good, to build him up.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Te Yesus Kristus sandiri sonde bekin Dia pung karjá ko cuma bekin sanáng Dia pung hati sandiri sa, ma Dia mau bekin sanáng Tuhan Allah pung hati ju. Itu sama ke yang su tatulis memang dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi so'al apa yang nanti jadi di Yesus bilang,<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) Yesus Kristus himself didn't do His work to only just make His own liver happy, but He also wanted to please God. That is the same as what was written beforehand in God2's Clean/Holy Writings about what would later happen to Yesus saying, [NOTE: explicated from UNS confusion at Belu check.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dong pung hojat kasi sang Lu,<bt>&lt;&lt;Their slandering/blaspheme/insulting of You-sg,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jato kaná di Beta ju.&gt;&gt;<bt>falls on Me also.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oneidismos: insult, reproach, abuse LITERALLY: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">oneidismos: insult, reproach, abuse LITERALLY: For even Christ did not please himself, but, as it is written: "The insults of those who insult you [God] have fallen on me [Christ]."<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Samua yang orang tulis dolu dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi dong, ada tulis ko ajar sang kotong. Dia kasi tunju jalan ko bekin kotong jadi lebe kuat, batahan lebe kuat, deng Dia pung Kata-kata ju kasi samangat sang kotong. Deng bagitu, kotong bisa batunggu-tunggu ko mau lia Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang kotong.<bt>Everything which people previously wrote in God2's Holy Writings, are written to teach us-inc. He/It shows the way to make us-inc be stronger, endure stronger, and His Words also give enthusiasm/encouragement to us. In that way, we-inc can wait eagerly in order to see God2 show His good liver to us [STYLE: HCE].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For everything that was written"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For everything that was written in the past was written to teach us, so that through endurance and the encouragement of the Scriptures we might have hope.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tuhan yang kasi kuat orang ko dong bisa tahan banting. Deng Dia yang kasi kuat kotong pung hati. Beta sambayang ko minta Dia kasi tunju jalan ko bosong idop satu hati, iko Yesus Kristus pung mau.<bt>God2 is the one who strengthens people so they can endure being flung.about (=endure abuse). And He is the one who strengthens our livers (=encourages us). I pray to request Him to show the way so you-pl can live with one liver (=united, in harmony, same purpose), according to Yesus Kristus' will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan yang kasi kuat orang ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan yang kasi kuat orang ko dong bisa tahan banting. Deng Dia yang bekin kuat kotong pung hati.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà: according to the standard of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">katà: according to the standard of Jesus, following his example, doing things his way LITERALLY: May the God who gives endurance and encouragement give you a spirit of unity among yourselves in accordance with Christ Jesus.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te kalo bosong satu hati bagitu, bosong bisa sama-sama angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah. Dia tu, kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung Bapa.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) if you are one liver (=united) like that, you can together lift up praises to God1. He is our Bos Yesus Kristus' Father.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homothumadon: with one purpose LITERALLY: That"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">homothumadon: with one purpose LITERALLY: That you may with one mind and one mouth glorify God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Kabar Bae kasi sang orang Yahudi deng orang bukan Yahudi<bt>God2's Good News is for the Yahudi people and for the non Yahudi people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi bosong deng bosong musti tarima satu deng satu, sama ke Kristus ada tarima sang bosong. Te kalo bosong idop bagitu, nanti orang dong angka tinggi-tinggi sang Tuhan pung nama.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must accept each other, the same as Kristus accepts you-pl. Cuz/for (elaboration) if you live like that, later people will lift God2's name up high. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proslambánesthe: same as 14:1 -- let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">proslambánesthe: same as 14:1 -- let each odda come in, accept each other LITERALLY: Accept one another, therefore, just as Christ accepted you, in order to bring glory to God.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Beta kasi tau bagini: Kristus bekin diri sama ke orang suru-suru, ko tolong orang Yahudi ko dong mangarti bilang, Tuhan Allah omong batúl. Deng Kristus ju bekin diri sama ke orang suru-suru ko bekin ganáp samua hal yang Tuhan su janji mau bekin, kasi kotong pung nene-moyang dong.<bt>I'm telling like this: Kristus made himself like a servant/slave (person who gets ordered around) to help the Yahudi people understand that, God1 speaks truth. And Kristus also made himself like a bossed.around.person to fulfill/complete all the things which God2 had promised to do for our-inc ancestors.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bebaióosai: actively make the things promised"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">bebaióosai: actively make the things promised happen (it could have the sense of "assure people that the things God promised really will happen some day", but in this context it's action, not just information) LITERALLY: For I say that Christ became a servant of the Jews on behalf of God's truth, to confirm the promises made to our fathers.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Deng bagitu, samua suku-bangsa laen yang bukan Yahudi dong, angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah. Te dong mangarti bilang, Dia ada rasa kasian kasi sang kotong samua. Itu sama ke Daud su tulis dolu dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>In that way, all other ethnic groups who are not Yahudi, lift up praises to God1. Cuz/for (elaboration) they understand that, He has mercy/pity/compassion for all of us-inc. That is the same as what Daud wrote long ago in the Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Andia ko beta mau angka tinggi-tinggi sang Lu pung nama,<bt>&lt;&lt;That's why I want to lift up Your-sg name up high,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi suku-bangsa laen dong.<bt>for the other ethnic groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta mau manyanyi lagu puji so'al Lu<bt>I want to sing praise songs/psalms about You</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">di bangsa laen dong pung muka.&gt;&gt;<bt>in the other ethnic groups' face (=in front of them).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exomologeésomai: be up front about my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">exomologeésomai: be up front about my relationship to you. But by parallel to the second line, it might be interpreted as "praise" LITERALLY: so that the Gentiles may glorify God for his mercy, as it is written: "For this reason I will praise you among the Gentiles; I will sing hymns to your name."<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 22:50, Lagu Puji dong 18:50</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Di tampa laen di Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;We! Bosong orang luar dari tampa-tampa laen dong.<bt>&lt;&lt;We! [+get attention] You-pl outside people from other places.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin bosong pung hati babunga,<bt>Make your livers flower (=be joyful),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama-sama deng Tuhan pung orang sandiri dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>together with God2's own people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euphrainw: rejoice, gladden LITERALLY: And again"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">euphrainw: rejoice, gladden LITERALLY: And again it says, "Rejoice, Gentiles, with his people."<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:43</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Di tampa laen di Tulisan Barisi, Daud tulis bilang,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings, Daud wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong yang dari suku-bangsa laen dong,<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl from other ethnic groups</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pi kasi tau samua orang so'al Tuhan pung hebat,<bt>go tell all people about God2's amazingness,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko dong ju iko puji sang kotong pung Bos.&gt;&gt;<bt>so that they also follow along/participate in praising our Boss.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: This is a typical parallelism of Biblical Hebrew poetry. The two stanzas are technically classed as “‘synonymous’ (where two lines say the same thing in different ways)” rather than ‘antithetical’ or ‘synthetic’. Don't to force it to be making two different points.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ainew: praise epainew: praise, laud|i(11) (11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">ainew: praise epainew: praise, laud<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: And again, "Praise the Lord, all Gentiles, and let all peoples praise him."</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 117:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Di tampa laen lai di Tulisan Barisi, ba'i Yesaya tulis bilang,<bt>In another place in the Holy Writings, Gf/Ff Yesaya wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dari Isai pung ana, raja Daud,<bt>&lt;&lt;From Isai's child, raja Daud,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti kaluar datang dia pung turunan satu.<bt>later one of his descendants will come out/appear.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia yang nanti pegang parenta sang suku-bangsa laen dong.<bt>He is the one who later will hold authority/govern/rule over other ethnic groups.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong su tau Dia mau datang.<bt>They already know He is coming.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais dong ada tunggu-tunggu sang Dia,<bt>So they are waiting-waiting (=waiting expectantly) for Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te dong tau, Dia tu, sapa.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz/for (elaboration) they know who He is.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="riza: root, like when a ti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">riza: root, like when a ti plant comes out of the ground from a root that was put there a long time ago LITERALLY: And again, Isaiah says, "There will be a root of Jesse, and he will rise to rule over the Gentiles. The Gentiles will hope in him."<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 11:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tuhan jadi akar dari samua yang kotong baharap. Kalo bosong parcaya sang Dia, na, Dia yang bekin bosong pung hati sanáng deng tanáng. Biar ko Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi pung kuasa bekin bosong tamba yakin so'al apa yang Dia mau bekin.<bt>God2 is the root/source of everything which we hope for. If you-pl believe in Him, na, He is the one who will make you livers happy and calm/peaceful. Let the power of God2's Holy Spirit, make you increasingly assured/certain about what it is He wants to do.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: May the God of hope"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: May the God of hope fill you with great joy and peace as you trust in him, so that you may overflow with hope by the power of the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan jadi sumber dari samua harapan."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Tuhan jadi sumber dari samua harapan. Kalo bosong parcaya sang Dia, Dia yang bekin bosong pung hati sanáng deng tanáng. Biar ko Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi pung kuasa tu, bekin bosong tamba yakin so’al apa yang Dia mau bekin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan utus sang Paulus ko jalan pi kasi tau Dia pung Kabar Bae<bt>God2 commissions/ed Paulus to go tell His Good News</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Sodara dong! Beta su yakin bilang, bosong pung hati su ponu deng hal-hal yang bae, bosong su mangarti bam-banya, deng bosong su mampu kasi nasiat satu deng satu.<bt>Siblings! I am assured that, your-pl livers are already full of good things, you already understand many things, and you are capable of giving advice to one another.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="autòs egoò: me, whether anybody else"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">autòs egoò: me, whether anybody else feels that way or not mestos: full<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>plerow: complete, filled nouthetew: advise, instruct, teach (not in a classroom sense), warn, admonish<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: But my brothers, I myself am persuaded that you yourselves are full of goodness, complete in knowledge, and able to advise each other.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Beta tulis taráng-taráng bagini di ini surat, ko kasi inga sang bosong satu kali lai so'al parkara macam-macam. Beta tulis bagini, tagal Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta,<bt>I'm writing clearly/boldly/openly/frankly like this in this letter, to remind you one more time about various issues/disputes. I write like this, because God2 showed His good liver (grace) to me,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apò mérous: from parts, concerning certain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">apò mérous: from parts, concerning certain specific matters teèn khárin: not theological "grace", but a specific privilege spelled out in verse 16: God gave me the privilege of serving Christ to benefit the Gentiles. Disregard the verse boundary<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: I have written you quite boldly on some points, as if to remind you of them again, because of the [grace / privilege] God gave me</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />waktu Dia angka sang beta ko jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan yang musti pi kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae sang orang yang bukan bangsa Yahudi dong. Beta kasi jalan beta pung tugas tu, sama ke satu kapala agama yang mau bekin siap banya orang jadi ke satu persembahan yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati. Te Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi ada bekin dong jadi barisi, ko Tuhan Allah bisa tarima sang dong.<bt>when He lifted me up/appointed me to become Yesus Kristus' commissioned.one (*apostle) who must go tell God2's Good News to the people who are not of the Yahudi ethnic group. I carry out that work of mine, like a religious leader (*priest) who wants to prepare many people to be an offering (not sacrifice) which pleases God2's liver. Cuz (elaboration) that Holy Spirit of God2's, makes them become clean/holy, so that God2 can accept them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tóon ethnóon: the Gentiles are the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">tóon ethnóon: the Gentiles are the offering; not the offering that they bring. Paul presents the Gentiles to God as the results of his efforts LITERALLY: to be a servant of Jesus Christ to the Gentiles, with the priestly duty of proclaiming the Good News of God, so that the Gentiles might become an offering acceptable to God, sanctified by the Holy Spirit.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tagal beta ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus, andia ko beta bisa angka muka di Tuhan Allah pung muka.<bt>Because I am bound/linked with Yesus Kristus, that's why I can lift my face (=not be ashamed, justifiably proud) in front of God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Therefore, I glory in Christ"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Therefore, I glory in Christ Jesus in my service to God.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Beta sonde barani omong hal laen. Beta cuma carita kasi tau apa yang Kristus bekin sa, deng karmana ko Dia ada pake sang beta. Sakarang ada orang bukan Yahudi dong yang dengar sang Kristus, tagal Tuhan pake sang beta, ko kasi tunju jalan pake beta pung omong deng beta pung jalan idop.<bt>I don't dare speak of other things. I only speak explaining just about Kristus' deeds, and how He is using me. Now there are non Yahudi people who listen to/obey Kristus, because God2 used me, to show the way using my speaking and my deeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For I will not dare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For I will not dare to speak of anything except what Christ has done through me in leading the Gentiles to obey him by what I have said and done,</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-16 01:41:41Z">jalan i</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kristus su kasi kuasa sang beta dari Tuhan pung Roh, ko beta bisa bekin tanda heran macam-macam. Dia kasi itu kuasa sang beta ko mau kasi tunju bilang, Kristus tu, sapa. Deng bagitu, beta su kasi tau orang di mana-mana, samua-samua so'al Kristus pung Kabar Bae. Andia, beta kasi tau dari kota Yerusalem, kuliling sampe di da'era Ilirikum deka Italia.<bt>Kristus has given power to me from God2's Spirit, so that I can do all.sorts of amazing signs (=miracles). He give that power to me in order to show, who that Kristus is. In that way, I have told people everywhere, everything about Kristus' Good News. That is, I tell from Yerusalem city, going around until the region of Ilirikum near Italia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: by the power of signs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: by the power of signs and wonders, through the power of the Spirit. So that from Jerusalem all the way around to Illyricum, I have fully proclaimed the Good News of Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dari dolu-dolu, beta ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta rindu mau kasi tau so'al Kristus sang orang yang sonde parná dengar Dia pung Kabar Bae!&gt;&gt; Te beta sonde suka ajar di tampa yang orang laen dong su ajar na.<bt>From long ago, I was thinking that, &lt;&lt;I yearn to tell about Kristus to the people who have never heard His Good News!&gt;&gt; I don't like to teach in places where other people have already taught. [+emphatic]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Thus it has always been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Thus it has always been my ambition to preach the Good News where Christ was not known, so that I would not be building on someone else's foundation.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, ada tatulis bilang,<bt>In God2's Holy Writings, it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Suku-bangsa yang balóm parná dengar so'al Tuhan,<bt>&lt;&lt;Ethnic.groups which have not yet ever heard about God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong tu, yang nanti dapa lia sang Dia.<bt>they are the ones who later will get to see Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang yang sonde parná dengar apa-apa,<bt>People who have not yet ever heard anything,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong tu, yang nanti mangarti so'al Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>they are the ones who later will understand about Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But just as it has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But just as it has been written, "Those who were not told about him will see, and those who have not heard will understand."</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus susun rancana ko mau pi kota Roma<bt>Paulus compiles a plan to go to Roma city</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Tagal beta pung tugas bagitu, andia ko beta balóm jadi-jadi pi lia sang bosong.<bt>Because my job/responsibilities are like that, that's why I have not yet been able to actually go see you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: That is why I have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: That is why I have often been hindered from coming to you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 1:13</note><v n="23" />Ma sakarang beta pung tugas di sini dong su abis. Su taon-taon, beta rindu mau pi lia sang bosong.<bt>But now my jobs/responsibilities here are finished. For years, I have been yearning to go see you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But now that there is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But now that there is no more place for me to work in these regions, and since I have been longing for many years to see you,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Nanti kalo beta pi negrí Spanyol, beta mau singga lia sang bosong. Ais, kalo beta su singga tahan di bosong, bosong ju bisa bantu sang beta deng ongkos jalan pi Spanyol.<bt>Later if I go to Spanyol country, I will stop off and see you. Then, if I have stopped off temporarily with/at you, you also can help me with the cost of travelling to Spanyol.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="propemphthéenai: be sent onward -- they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">propemphthéenai: be sent onward -- they will help out with his travel expenses LITERALLY: when I go to Spain, I will come to you. I hope to see you on my trip and to have you assist me on my journey there [to Spain], after I have stayed with you [enjoyed being with you] for a while.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma sakarang beta mau pi Yerusalem dolo, ko layani sang Tuhan pung orang parcaya dong di situ.<bt>But now I want to go to Yerusalem first, to serve God's believers there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakonóon: probably refers to delivering the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">diakonóon: probably refers to delivering the collection Paul took up that he talks about in 2 Corinthians, an in the next verse LITERALLY: But now I go to Jerusalem to [minister to / serve] the saints.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te kotong pung sodara dong di propinsi Makedonia deng propinsi Akaya, su kasi doi kolekte ko tolong orang kasian yang parcaya sang Kristus di Yerusalem.<bt>Cuz/for (elaboration) our siblings in Makedonia province and Akaya province, have given collection money to help the poor people who believe in Kristus in Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** Tuhan &gt; Kristus (2009)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** Tuhan &gt; Kristus (2009)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: For Macedonia and Achaia were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: For Macedonia and Achaia were pleased to make a contribution for the poor among the saints in Jerusalem.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 16:1-4</note><v n="27" />Dong mau bekin bagitu, tagal dong rasa ada utang kasi kotong pung sodara di Yerusalem. Te orang dari suku-bangsa laen di mana-mana dong ju su tarima hal bae yang Tuhan pung Roh kasi sang orang Yahudi dolo. Jadi pantas kalo orang sarani yang bukan Yahudi dong mau pake dong pung harta ko bantu dong pung sodara orang Yahudi.<bt>They wanted to do that, because they felt there was a debt owed to our-inc siblings in Yerusalem. Cuz/for (elaboration) people from other ethnic groups all over the place also have received good things which God2's Spirit gave to the Yahudi people first. So (consequently), it's appropriate if the <span class="Italic">(sarani)</span> people (=Christians) who are not Yahudi want to use their possessions/belongings/wealth to help their Yahudi siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Does bantu imply financial?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Does bantu imply financial?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They were pleased to do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They were pleased to do it, and indeed they owe it to them. For it the Gentiles have shared in the Jews' spiritual blessings, they owe it to the Jews to share with them their material blessings.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 9:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jadi, kalo beta su bekin kalár ini tugas, ko kasi ini bantuan sang kotong pung sodara di Yerusalem, beta mau singga lia sang bosong waktu beta jalan pi Spanyol.<bt>So (consequently), if/when I have finished this job, of giving this (financial) assistance to our siblings in Yerusalem, I want to stop over and see you when I travel to Spanyol.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: So after I have finished"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: So after I have finished this job, and have made sure that they have received this fruit [benefit], I will go to Spain and visit you on the way.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Nanti kalo beta datang, beta mau bawa berkat bam-banya dari Kristus.<bt>Later if/when I come, I want to bring lots of blessings from Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I know that when I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I know that when I come to you, I will come in the full measure of the blessing of Christ. / bringing an abundant blessing from Christ</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Sodara dong! Tagal Yesus Kristus jadi bosong pung Bos, deng tagal Tuhan pung Roh bekin bosong basayang satu deng satu, andia ko beta minta ko bosong sambayang batúl-batúl ko Tuhan tolong sang beta.<bt>Siblings! Because Yesus Kristus is your Bos who has say-so/ordering rights over you, and because God2's Spirit makes you love one another, that is why I request that you really pray for God2 to help me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="/kasi sayang/ has noise from BI"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">/kasi sayang/ has noise from BI ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I urge you brothers, by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I urge you brothers, by our Lord Jesus Christ, and by the love of the Spirit, to join me in my struggle by praying to God for me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta minta ko bosong sambayang batúl-batúl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">Beta minta ko bosong sambayang batúl-batúl ko Tuhan tolong sang beta. Sambayang bagitu, tagal Yesus Kristus jadi bosong pung Bos, deng tagal Tuhan pung Roh bekin bosong basayang satu deng satu.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Minta ko Tuhan jaga sang beta di propinsi Yudea, ko orang yang sonde mau parcaya sang Tuhan jang bekin jahat sang beta. Deng minta ko kalo beta pi layani sang orang sarani di Yerusalem, na, dong tarima bae sang beta.<bt>Request that God2 protect me in Yudea province, so that people who do not want to believe in God2 don't do evil to me. And request that if I go serve the Christians in Yerusalem, na, they will receive me well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeithoúntoon: not simply &quot;unbelieving&quot;, but &quot;refusing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">apeithoúntoon: not simply "unbelieving", but "refusing to act in faith, rejecting the faith", a more negative idea LITERALLY: Pray that I may be rescued from the unbelievers in Judea, and that my service in Jerusalem may be acceptable to the saints there.<span class="Italic">(31)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ais kalo iko Tuhan pung mau, beta bisa datang lia sang bosong deng hati sanáng. Beta mau barenti cape sadiki di bosong situ.<bt>Then if it is according to God2's will, I can come see you with a happy liver. I want to rest a bit at/with you over.there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunanapauswmai: experience restorative rest together with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">sunanapauswmai: experience restorative rest together with someone else LITERALLY: Then by God's will I can come to you with joy, and together with you be refreshed.<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Beta sambayang ko minta Tuhan ada sama-sama deng bosong. Te Dia yang bisa bekin orang idop aman deng dame. Batúl!<bt>I pray requesting God2 to be with you. Cuz/for (elaboration) His is the one who enables people to live safely (situation) and peacefully (relationships). Really!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The God of peace be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The God of peace be with you all. Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus titip salam kasi sodara dong di Roma<bt>Paulus sends greetings to the siblings in Roma</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Lewat ini surat, beta mau kasi kanál kotong pung susi Febe sang bosong, deng minta ko bosong tarima sang dia. Dia yang dong su angka ko pimpin jama'at di kota Kengkrea.<bt>By means of this letter, I want to introduce our-inc older-sister Febe to you, and request that you accept/receive her. She is the one whom they lifted up/appointed to help lead the congregation in Kengkrea city. [NOTE: It has been observed for over 100 years that the female Phoebe in this verse is described in Gk as a “deacon”, rather than using the grammatical feminine “deaconess”. Most authorities agree that this implies she was in a leadership role of a congregation. A few have tried to argue that she was not an office-bearer, but that has been shown to be a reflection of their own worldview and values, not of the Biblical text. See any good commentary, as well as articles on CBE website. I (Chuck) have an article by a Baptist minister in the 1890s that I can send you. He was an off-sider to D.L. Moody. Even Tran Handbook and NEB says she was an ‘office holder’ (ie. not a helper of office holders). See Nyland for a pg long footnote on the term.] [NOTE to daughter translations: some of our lgs have an ‘older sister’ term of respect they can use. Others have a female honorific. Others have an “opposite sex sibling (male speaking)” term. Use what is appropriate to your language for Paul showing both affection and respect to an unrelated female.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="synísteemi: I give you a recommendation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">synísteemi: I give you a recommendation for Phoebe. Used in letters of recommendation. NRSV: I commend to you our sister Phoebe, a deacon of the church at Cenchreae,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta minta ko bosong buka tangan ko tarima sang dia deng bae, sama ke yang pantas kasi orang sarani dong, tagal dia ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos. Dia parlú apa, na, tolong bantu sang dia sa. Te dia sandiri su tolong sang beta deng banya orang dari dolu.<bt>I request that you open your arms to receive her well, like what is appropriate for Christians, because she is bound/linked with our Boss. Whatever she needs, na, just help her. Cuz/for (elaboration) she herself has helped me and many people from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prosdéxeesthe: welcome, take into your group,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">prosdéxeesthe: welcome, take into your group, make her feel at home hymóon: from you<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>prostátis: benefactor, patron, protectress, helper, of great assistance NRSV: so that you may welcome her in the Lord as is fitting for the saints, and help her in whatever she may require from you, for she has been a benefactor of many and of myself as well.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="3" />Titip salam manis dari beta kasi susi Priskila<bt>Pass on sweet (=warm, tender) greetings from me to sister Priskila</bt><note reference="16:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Priska&gt;&gt;. Priska deng Priskila tu, andia satu nama.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes saying, “Priska”. Priska and Priskila are the same name.</bt></note>deng dia pung paitua, bu Akila. Botong su sama-sama kasi jalan Yesus Kristus pung karjá bam-banya.<bt>and her husband, elder.brother Akila. We-exc have together carried out lots of Yesus Kristus' work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Prisca and Aquila, who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Prisca and Aquila, who work with me in Christ Jesus,</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:2</note><v n="4" />Dong dua su amper mati ko kasi salamat sang beta. Ma bukan beta sandiri sa yang minta tarima kasi sang dong. Te orang bukan Yahudi yang su jadi orang sarani dari samua jama'at di mana-mana, ada minta tarima kasi tagal dong pung jasa ju.<bt>The two of them have almost died in order to save me. But it's not just me myself who reciprocates thank you to them. Cuz/for (elaboration) non Yahudi people who have become Christians from all the congregations all over the place, also are reciprocating thank you because of their commendable.service.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tón heautóon trákheelon hypétheekan: they put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">tón heautóon trákheelon hypétheekan: they put their life on the line for me, they stuck their necks out to save my life ethnóon: churches made up of Gentiles<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>NRSV: and who risked their necks for my life, to whom not only I give thanks, but also all the churches of the Gentiles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="5" />Titip beta pung salam kasi samua orang yang bakumpul ko gareja di Priskila deng Akila pung ruma.<bt>Pass on my greeting to all people who gather to do church in Priskila and Akila's house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi beta pung tamán, bu Epenetus. Dia tu, orang partama yang parcaya sang Kristus di propinsi Asia.<bt>Pass on greetings to my friend, elder.brother Epenetus. He is the one who was the first person to believe in Kristus in Asia province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet also the church in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet also the church in their house. Greet my beloved Epaenetus, who was the first convert in Asia for Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="6" />Titip salam kasi sus Mia. Dia su karjá banting tulang di bosong pung teng-tenga.<bt>Pass on greetings to sis Mia (Mary nickname). She has worked throwing her bones down (=extremely hard) in the midst of you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Mary, who has worked"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Mary, who has worked very hard among you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Titip salam kasi bu Andronikus deng susi Yunia.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Andronikus and elder.sister Yunia.</bt><note reference="16:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani yang paling bae deng yang paling tua ada tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Yunia</span> (nama parampuan). Ada saparu lai yang tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Yulia</span> (nama parampuan). Mulai dari abad ke-13, ada saparu lai yang tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Yunias</span> (nama laki-laki). Tua-tua Kristen dari dolu-dolu anggap bu Andronikus deng susi Yunia tu, laki-bini yang karjá kasi sang Tuhan, sama ke bu Akila deng susi Priskila.<bt>The best and oldest Yunani language Bibles write saying, <span class="Italic">Yunia </span>(name of a woman). There are some others which write saying, <span class="Italic">Yulia</span> (name of a woman). Beginning from the 13th century, there were some others with wrote saying, <span class="Italic">Yunias</span> (name of a man). Christian leaders from long ago considered this older brother Andronikus and older sister Yunia to be husband-wife who worked for God2, just like older brother Akila and older sister Priskila.</bt></note>Dong tu, orang Yahudi, sama ke beta. Dong su parcaya sang Kristus waktu beta masi balóm parcaya. Dolu dong ada dalam bui sama-sama deng beta. Dong ju jadi Tuhan pung utusan, deng banya orang kanál sang dong.<bt>They are Yahudi peple, just like me. They had already believed in Kristus when I still had not yet believed. Long ago, they were in jail together with me. They also became God2's commissioned.ones (apostles), and many people know/recognize them. [EXEG: Morris, NRSV, NLT support feminine Junia [common name] (Moo says unanimous before 13th century, supported by recent scholarship). NIV, CEV, TB support masculine Junias -said to be contracted form of Junianus (13th cent mss onwards), but no attestation of such a contraction outside this verse. Some discussion in CBE about a later change to the text that didn't support assumptions/ biases of the time.] [EXEG: Gk is ambiguous here, so it could be /sama-sama deng beta/ “together with me” OR /sama ke beta/ “like me”.] [EXEG: on “notable among the apostles” Morris says, “which might mean that the apostles held them in high esteem or that they were apostles, and notable apostles at that. The former understanding seems less likely;” We go with the latter, as do many others (see SSA, Moo, TH). Morris also notes an early church father on Junia, “Chrysostom's comment: “Oh! how great is the devotion of this woman, that she should be even counted worthy of the appellation of apostle!”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sungeneis: 1) kinsman, relatives, person who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">sungeneis: 1) kinsman, relatives, person who belongs to the same extended family or clan, 2) fellow countryman (Morris, SSA, LN argues for #2, also TB2, HCE; but NIV, NRSV, NLT, CEV take #1 en tóis apostólois: either "they are well known by all the apostles, or even more likely, "they are apostles, and everybody knows them" or "they are important apostles"<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>NRSV: Greet Andronicus and Junia, my relatives who were in prison with me; they are prominent among the apostles, and they were in Christ before I was.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />Titip salam kasi bu Ampliatus. Beta sayang sang dia, tagal dia ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Ampliatus. I love him, because he is bound/linked with our Boss.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Ampliatus, my beloved in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="9" />Titip salam kasi bu Urbanus. Dia ju kasi jalan Kristus pung karjá sama-sama deng botong.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Urbanus. He carrys out Kristus' work together with us-exc.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi bu Stakis, yang beta sayang.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Stakis, whom I love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Urbanus, our co-worker in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Urbanus, our co-worker in Christ, and my beloved Stachys.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="10" />Titip salam kasi bu Apeles. Dia kaná uji, ma dia lolos. Ais su jalás dia parcaya batúl sang Kristus.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Apeles. He was tested, but he escaped/got.through (came out the other end in one piece). So it is clear that he really believes in Kristus. [EXEG: Gk dokimon (LN) “pertaining to being genuine on the basis of testing”; MESSAGE picks this up with “a tried and true veteran”; HCE also reflects this with “da tings dat wen happen to him, dass jalike one test fo make proof dat he stay tight wit Jesus fo real kine.” I think English “approved” used to have this meaning about the time the KJV was done (or before) but it no longer means what the Gk word here does. Morris says “This man was tested and approved. We have no way of knowing what test he had undergone, but he was a man of tested excellence and Paul approves of him accordingly.” Moo says “Paul honors him by saying that he is “approved” in Christ. By this Paul might mean that he had proved himself in a difficult test of faith…”. SSA says “The word dçkimov means “approved (by test)” (BAGD, p. 203.1). It entails three separate events: (1) being tested by trials of some kind, (2) successfully enduring those trials, and (3) being approved by God as a result.”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi bu Aristobulus pung kelu samua.<bt>Pass on greetings to all of elder.brother Aristobulus' family.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimon: genuine, sincere, approved NRSV: Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">dokimon: genuine, sincere, approved NRSV: Greet Apelles, who is approved in Christ. Greet those who belong to the family of Aristobulus.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="11" />Titip salam kasi bu Herodion. Dia orang Yahudi, sama ke beta.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Herodion. He is a Yahudi person, just like me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi Narkisus pung kelu samua yang su parcaya sang Kristus.<bt>Pass on greetings to all of Narkisus's family that has believed in Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet my relative Herodion. Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet my relative Herodion. Greet those in the Lord who belong to the family of Narcissus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="12" />Titip salam kasi susi Trifena deng susi Trifosa. Dong ju kasi jalan kotong pung Bos pung karjá.<bt>Pass on greetings to sister Trifena and sister Trifosa. They carry out our Boss' work.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi beta pung tamán, susi Persis. Te dia ju karjá banting tulang kasi kotong pung Bos.<bt>Pass on greetings to my friend, sister Persis. Cuz/for (elaboration) she also works throwing her bones down (=very hard) for our Boss.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet those workers in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet those workers in the Lord, Tryphaena and Tryphosa. Greet the beloved Persis, who has worked hard in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="13" />Titip salam kasi bu Rufus. Kotong pung Bos yang pili ame sang dia.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Rufus. Our Boss is the one who chose him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Titip salam kasi dia pung mama ju. Te dia tu, su sama ke beta pung mama sandiri.<bt>Pass on greetings to his mother also. Cuz/for (elaboration) she, is like my own mother.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eklektòn: chosen, choice, outstanding NRSV: Greet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">eklektòn: chosen, choice, outstanding NRSV: Greet Rufus, chosen in the Lord; and greet his mother-a mother to me also.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 15:21</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="14" />Titip salam kasi bu Asinkritus, bu Flegon, bu Hermes, bu Patrobas, bu Hermas, deng samua sodara yang ada tenga deng dong.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Asinkritus, elder.brother Flegon, elder.brother Hermes, elder.brother Patrobas, elder.brother Hermas, and all the siblings who stay with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Asyncritus, Phlegon, Hermes, Patrobas, Hermas, and the brothers and sisters who are with them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="15" />Titip salam kasi bu Filologus, susi Yulia, bu Olimpas, bu Nereus deng dia pung adi parampuan, deng samua orang sarani yang ada sama-sama deng dong.<bt>Pass on greetings to elder.brother Filologus, sister Yulia, elder.brother Olimpas, elder.brother Nereus and his female younger sibling, and all the Christians who are together with them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Greet Philologus, Julia, Nereus and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Greet Philologus, Julia, Nereus and his sister, and Olympas, and all the saints who are with them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kalo bosong bakumpul, basambut satu deng satu pake ciom manis yang pantas kasi orang parcaya dong. Kristus pung jama'at samua di sini dong ju ada titip salam manis kasi sang bosong.<bt>If/When you gather together, greet each other with sweet kisses which are appropriate for believers. All of Kristus' congregations here also send sweet greeting to you. [EXEG: SSA]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phileémati hagíooi: an appropriate, warm, Christian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">phileémati hagíooi: an appropriate, warm, Christian greeting, not a sexual advance. NRSV: Greet one another with a holy kiss. All the churches of Christ greet you.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 16:20, 1 Tesalonika 5:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus kasi nasiat sang dong<bt>Paulus gives advice to them</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Sodara dong! Beta minta bosong ati-ati, ó! Jaga bae-bae, te ada orang bekin bosong tapica-pica, yang mau hiki kasi jato sang bosong. Apa yang dong kasi tau sang bosong tu, ada malawan deng apa yang botong su ajar sang bosong. Jadi jang batamán deng orang macam ke dong!<bt>Siblings! I request that you-pl be careful! Guard carefully, cuz/for (elaboration) there are people who make you divided (into groups/factions), who want to trick/ensnare you and make you fall. What they are telling you, is in opposition to what we-exc have taught you. So (consequently) don't be (close) friends with people like them! [NOTE to daughter translations: Be careful to phrase this last sentence so that it is not directly at odds with a number of commands of Jesus, and of Paul himself (e.g. Gal. 6, Rom ). What we are aiming for is something that allows ostracism, discipline, reconciliation and restoration, without being influenced and corrupted in the process. KM actually achieves this.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dichostasias: divisions, discord, division into opposing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">dichostasias: divisions, discord, division into opposing groups, skandala: obstacle, trap, offense<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>NRSV: I urge you, brothers and sisters, to keep an eye on those who cause dissensions and offenses, in opposition to the teaching that you have learned; avoid them.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dong sonde karjá kasi kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus. Dong cuma karjá ko dong sandiri yang dapa dia pung hasil. Dong bamulu minya deng orang yang balóm mangarti mana yang bae deng mana yang jahat. Dong bamulu manis ko tipu orang.<bt>They don't work for our Boss, Yesus Kristus. They only work so that they themselves can get results. They oily mouth (speak slippery-flatteringly to be deceptive) with people who do not yet understand which is good and which is evil. They sweet mouth to deceive people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akákoon: inexperienced as far as evil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">akákoon: inexperienced as far as evil is concerned, innocent-minded NRSV: For such people do not serve our Lord Christ, but their own appetites, and by smooth talk and flattery they deceive the hearts of the simple-minded.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Samua orang su dengar bilang, bosong ada iko tarús Tuhan pung mau. Andia ko beta hati babunga tagal bosong. Beta mau ko bosong jadi pintar so'al hal bae dong, deng jang bacampor deng hal jahat dong.<bt>All people have heard that, you are continually following God2's will. That's why my liver flowers (=rejoices) because of you. I want so that you become knowledgeable about good things, and don't mix/get involved with evil things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akeraíous: not mixed up in what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">akeraíous: not mixed up in what is evil NRSV: For while your obedience is known to all, so that I rejoice over you, I want you to be wise in what is good and guileless in what is evil.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Tuhan Allah tu, yang bisa kasi kotong idop aman, dame, deng tanáng. Dia yang nanti kasi ancor setan dong pung bos pung kuasa, deng kasi tunju bilang, bosong yang manáng. Itu su sonde lama lai. Beta sambayang minta ko kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong.<bt>God1 is the one who can enable us to live safely, peacefully, and calmly. He is the one who later will destroy the evil spirit's big boss' power, and shows that, you are the ones who win. That's not much longer. I pray requesting that our Bos Yesus Kristus shows his good liver (grace/kindness/favour) to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaan: da Devil hypò toùs pódas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">Satanaan: da Devil hypò toùs pódas hymóon: under your feet, make him subject to you<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>NRSV: The God of peace will shortly crush Satan under your feet. The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="21" />Adi Timotius, yang karjá sama-sama deng beta, ada titip salam kasi bosong.<bt>Younger.sibling Timotius, who works together with me, is sending greetinigs to you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bu Lukius, bu Yason, deng bu Sosipater ju titip salam. Dong tu, orang Yahudi sama ke beta.<bt>Elder.brother Lukius, elder.brother Yason, and elder.brother Sosipater also send greetings. They are Yahudi people just like me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Timothy, my co-worker, greets you;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Timothy, my co-worker, greets you; so do Lucius and Jason and Sosipater, my relatives [/fellow countrymen--see above].</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 16:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="22" />(Beta ni, Tertius, yang ada tulis ini surat iko apa yang bu Paul suru beta tulis. Salam manis dari beta ju, te beta ni, ju kotong pung Bos pung orang.)<bt>(I, Tertius, am the one who is writing this letter according to what elder.brother Paul orders me to write. Sweet greetings from me also, cuz/for (elaboration) I am also our Boss' person.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I Tertius, the writer of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: I Tertius, the writer of this letter, greet you in the Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="23" />Beta, Paulus, manumpang di bu Gayus pung ruma. Samua orang sarani di sini biasa bakumpul ko gareja di dia pung ruma. Dia ju titip salam.<bt>I, Paulus, stay.temporarily in elder.brother Gayus' house. All the Christians here usually gather to do church in his house. He also sends greetings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) Paulus here to signal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) Paulus here to signal ‘I’ is no longer Tertius</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bu Erastus, yang jadi bendahara kota, deng kotong pung sodara Kuartus, ju ada titip salam.<bt>Elder.brother Erastus, who is the city treasurer, and our sibling Kuartus, also are sending greetings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Gaius, who is host to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Gaius, who is host to me and to the whole church, greets you. Erastus, the city treasurer, and our brother Quartus, greet you.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:29, 1 Korintus 1:14, 2 Timotius 4:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />[Beta minta ko kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong samua. Bagitu sa!]<bt>[I request that our Bos Yesus Kristus show His good liver to all of you. That's all!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: [The grace of our Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: [The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with all of you. Amen.]</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:24" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae sonde mua ini ayat 24 ni.<bt>The oldest and best Yunani language Bibles don't carry this verse 24 here.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah tu, hebat talalu!<bt>God1 is amazing/incredible!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Puji Tuhan! Te Dia yang ada pung kuasa ko bekin bosong jadi kuat. Dia pung Kabar Bae bilang bagitu, deng beta ju ajar orang bagitu, waktu beta kasi tau sang dong so'al Yesus Kristus. Tuhan yang su buka kasi tau sang kotong samua hal so'al Kristus, yang orang dolu-dolu sonde tau, tagal masi rahasia.<bt>Praise God2! Cuz (elaboration He is the one who has the power to make you become strong. His Good News says that, and I also teach people like that, when I explain to them about Yesus Kristus. God2 is the one who has revealed to all of us-inc matters concerning Kristus, which people long ago didn't know about, because it was still secret.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) added “praise God” at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z">*** (2009) added “praise God” at beginning to signal genre of 25-27 as a doxology.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now to God who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now to God who is able to strengthen you according to my gospel and the proclamation of Jesus Christ, according to the revelation of the mystery that was kept secret for long ages</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ma sakarang, hal-hal yang Tuhan pung jubir dolu-dolu dong su tulis dalam Tulisan Barisi, su jalás. Tuhan, yang sonde tau mati, Dia yang ator ko orang dari samua suku-bangsa bisa tau hal-hal yang dolu tasambunyi. Deng bagitu, dong bisa parcaya sang Dia, deng bekin iko Dia pung mau.<bt>But now, matters/issues which God2's *prophets (spokepeople) have written about in the Scriptures (Holy Writings), are now clear. (The) God2 who cannot die, He is the one who arranged for people from all ethnic groups to be able to know matters which were formerly hidden. In that way, they can believe in Hims, and do according to His will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: but is now disclosed, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: but is now disclosed, and through the prophetic writings is made known to all the Gentiles, according to the command of the eternal God, to bring about the obedience of faith-</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Cuma Dia sandiri sa, Allah. Cuma Dia sandiri sa yang mangarti samua hal. Beta suka angka puji-puji sang Dia, tagal apa yang Yesus Kristus bekin! Batúl tu!<bt>Only He alone is Allah. Only He alone is the one who understands all things. I like to lift praises to Him, because Yesus Kristus' deeds. Really! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: to the only wise God,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:48:49Z" status="Information">NRSV: to the only wise God, through Jesus Christ, to whom be the glory forever! Amen.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta pung surat sampe di sini sa,<bt>My letter just reaches this point,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saloom,<bt>Saloom, (assimilated loan)</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>